title: old fashioned egg custard(this recipe is at least 100 years old.)
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer at least 5 minutes or until eggs are a light yellow color and slightly thickened.
Add sugar that has flour mixed in.
Pour in scalded milk, slowly stirring, as you pour.
Add oleo and pour into an unbaked shell.
Cook in a preheated 350° oven until browned and still shaky in the middle.

title: gingerbread
directions: Pour boiling water over margarine.
Add brown sugar, molasses, egg and flour sifted with salt, baking powder, soda, ginger and cinnamon.
Beat until smooth.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan in 350° oven for 35 minutes.
Cool in pan.
Top with warm Lemon Sauce.

title: zesty mexican lasagne
directions: Brown the beef, onion, 1 1/2 chiles and garlic in a large skillet until meat is crumbly.
Add the tomatoes, seasonings and olives.
Stir well.
Reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, then flour.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop cookies on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork.
Cook until light brown at 350°.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar together.
Beat in egg yolks.
Sift together cake flour and salt.
Stir in alternately with mixture of buttermilk and soda.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° in 3 greased, floured and wax paper lined 8-inch round layer pans. Cool on racks.
Frost.

title: golden chicken 'n noodles
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken parts in margarine or butter. Remove chicken and set aside.
In drippings, saute onion, garlic and thyme for a few minutes.
Stir in soup and tomatoes.
Return chicken to skillet, cover and cook over low heat 45 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over noodles.
Serves 4. Great 1 dish meal.

title: hearty polish stew
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meats quickly over high heat in 2 tablespoons butter.
Reduce heat to medium.
Add remaining butter, onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Stir in kraut and tomatoes. Gradually stir in broth.
Add potatoes, caraway and pepper. Cover and simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.

title: raspberry jam
directions: Chop tomato pulp into small pieces and put into a large kettle.
Add no water.
Boil for 15 minutes stirring frequently. Add dry gelatin and sugar.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Watch carefully so as not to scorch the mixture.
Pour into sterilized jars.
Seal with paraffin wax.

title: "ham" burger-macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Fry hamburger in pan until done; drain.
Mix macaroni and cheese according to package directions.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Put kidney beans on top of macaroni.
Then sprinkle hamburger on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter with brown sugar.
Spread evenly over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange slices of pineapple on sugar mixture.
Pour cake mix over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Invert onto cardboard covered with waxed paper.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix sugar and sour cream together.
Break cookies into small pieces and fold into sour creamed mix.
Chill several hours.
Serve with apple wedges, cantaloupe, honeydew, strawberries, grapes, etc.

title: hot fruit punch
directions: Steep tea;
add
sugar	and
fruit juice and bring to a boil. Serve hot.	Makes 30 servings.

title: herb consomme
directions: Have broth steaming hot.
Add the herbs and let stand, covered, for 3 to 5 minutes.
Strain.
Serve with a lemon slice in each bowl.

title: amish turtle candy
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil for 12 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Using 1 pound crushed pecans, lay by tablespoon on wax paper. When candy is cool, pour over nuts with spoon. Let sit and cover with melted coating chocolate.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Cut up cheese.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: potato salad
directions: Use Marzetti's cole slaw dressing for desired texture to the peeled and finely diced cooked potatoes and chopped hard-boiled eggs plus above ingredients. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 18 to 22.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears, peppers and onion in food processor until coarse. Add everything else to this mixture and let it sit for at least 30 to 40 minutes.
It will be okay overnight.
Bring to a boil and let simmer until thick.
Pack into hot jars and process in water bath for 20 minutes after caps are adjusted.

title: my friend (helen's) coconut cake
directions: Make cake in layers according to directions on box.
Cool. Mix sour cream, sugar, vanilla and coconut and place between layers and on top.
Refrigerate for 4 days.
If not eaten, freeze.

title: bruna kakor cookies
directions: Mix in order given. Divide dough into 4 rolls, each one like a long hot dog (about 12-inches long). Put on ungreased cookie sheet, 2 rolls to a sheet. Bake at 350° until golden brown (about 10 to 15 minutes). Slice diagonally while still warm.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter and cook onion until tender.
Add potato and broth.
Simmer.
Add broccoli and return to simmer.
When tender, puree in batches in blender.
Return to pot and add cream.
Season to taste.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Coarsely chop onions and cut Big Franks into 1-inch pieces. Saute onions and celery in small amount of oil until tender.
Stir in canned tomatoes and tomato paste.
Add cabbage and sauerkraut and cook on low until tender.
May add water as needed.
Stir frequently and add beans and Big Franks.
Add seasoning to taste. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain vegetables, layer the ingredients.
Pour crushed crackers on top and dot with butter.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° until golden brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and 8 ounces Cheddar together with French onion dip.
Spread in 9 or 10-inch pie plate and refrigerate. Brown ground beef and add taco seasoning; spread on cream cheese layer.
Next, sprinkle shredded lettuce and cut-up tomatoes on meat layer and sprinkle with 8 ounces Cheddar cheese.
Pour taco sauce or salsa over lettuce and tomato layer.
Use tortilla chips for dipping.

title: low calorie hot dish
directions: Cook hamburger and onion; pour off fat and stir in raw rice, 1 can tomato soup plus 1 can of water and pepper.
Place cabbage in bottom of a greased baking dish.
Add meat mixture on top and cover all with 1 can of tomato soup and 1 can of water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Watch so it doesn't get dry.
Contains 120 calories per serving.

title: cherry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease loaf pan.
In small saucepan bring orange juice to simmer.
In large bowl, combine cherries, softened butter and hot orange juice and stir the mixture until butter is melted.
In separate bowl, beat the eggs until they are light and lemon colored.
Add sugar and grated lemon rind and beat until mixture forms a ribbon when beaters are lifted.
Add egg mixture to cherry mixture.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Fold flour mixture into cherry mixture and stir until combined.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased pan and bake 1 hour.
Serve with lemon butter or cream cheese.

title: party pizzas
directions: Brown pork sausage and beef together.
Drain.
Add cheese (cut into small pieces) and melt in hot meat.
Stir in herbs and mix well.
Mound mixture on cocktail rye.
Freeze on cookie sheet and store in plastic bags in freezer.
Party time, heat in 350° oven 15 minutes.
(Half of this recipe covers 28 slices cocktail rye). English muffins can also be used.

title: sweet mustard
directions: To 2 ounces dry mustard add enough vinegar to equal 1 cup. Beat eggs, salt and sugar together.
Add mustard mix.
Stir.
Heat on High in microwave for 3 minutes.
Stir.
Heat on High 30 to 60 seconds.
Stir.
After cooling, refrigerate (ready to use).

title: barbecue beef
directions: Add water, onions, green pepper, celery and garlic to chuck roast.
Cook over low heat 4 hours.
Drain liquid, reserving 1 1/2 cups of broth.
Shred meat and return to pot.
Add reserved broth, catsup and next 9 ingredients.
Stir well.
Bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes.
Uncover and simmer another 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve.

title: howard beets
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add vinegar and beet juice.
Mix well. Cook over low heat until thick.
Add beets and butter.
Let simmer until thoroughly hot.

title: cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in the pot you are going to make soup.
Add onions, carrots and celery and saute over low heat until soft. Add flour and cornstarch and cook until bubbly.
Add stock and milk and make a smooth sauce.
Add soda and the cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add parsley a few minutes before serving. Makes 8 servings.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place on a lined broiler pan.
Place the shrimp under the broiler about 3 to 4 inches under flame. Broil about 5 to 6 minutes until done.
You may turn if you like but be careful not to overcook or the shrimp will become tough. Serve at once with rice or pasta.

title: apple dapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Stir in sifted flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix in apples and nuts.
Bake in a greased 8-inch square pan
in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: frankfurters and potato salad casserole
directions: Simmer frankfurters in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Combine potatoes, salt, pepper, oil and vinegar.
Arrange drained string beans in bottom of greased or oiled 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Over the beans arrange potatoes in alternate layers with onions and sliced frankfurters.
Cover and bake in 400° oven 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: super cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour over cabbage.
Store in refrigerator until chilled.

title: strawberry oatmeal bars
directions: In a bowl, combine dry ingredients. Add butter and vanilla; stir until crumbly. Set aside 1 cup. Press remaining crumb mixture evenly into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Spread preserves over crust. Combine coconut and reserved crumb mixture; sprinkle over preserves. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until coconut is lightly browned. Cool. Yield: 3 dozen.

title: herbal spaghetti
directions: In large pot, cook spaghetti.
In another pan in hot olive oil, cook garlic, until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, basil and salt. Heat through for 4 to 5 minutes.
Drain spaghetti and mix with tomato mixture.
Add Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.

title: baked crab salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except buttered crumbs.
Place in seashells or baking dish; do not grease.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes; pack in jars and seal.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by tablespoon on cookie sheet.
Bake until edges start to brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water for 5 to 7 minutes.
Drain. Beat eggs slightly.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix together, then add to broccoli.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes.

title: quick mushroom stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, stir the soups and water until smooth.
Add meat and bay leaves.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in potatoes, carrots, mushrooms and tapioca.
Cover and bake 1 hour longer, or until the meat and vegetables are tender.
Remove the bay leaves before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix together; drop by spoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: festive pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven.
Grease and flour a bread loaf pan.
In a large bowl, stir together oil, eggs, water and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add dry ingredients to mixture; beat until smooth.
Fold in cherries and nuts.
Pour batter into pan and bake 1 hour.

title: 5 cup fruit salad
directions: Mix
all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain grease and put beef in a bowl.
Add ketchup, mustard and salt.
Mix ketchup and mustard until it sticks together.
Put on buns and you have a very easy Sloppy Joe.

title: flaky biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream the Crisco and sugar lightly.
Add yeast and remaining ingredients.
Pinch off small pieces of dough and roll into biscuits.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 450° until golden brown.
Dough may be refrigerated for 1 week.

title: hot crab appetizer
directions: Place cream cheese in a mixing bowl and add lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic, salt, pepper and Tabasco.
Work well to blend and soften.
Adjust seasonings as desired.
Add crab carefully; spoon mixture into a small round 3-cup baking dish. Cooking time is 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly at 350°.

title: cheese-and-spinach puffs
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a small saucepan; bring to a boil and cook 10 minutes.
Drain well and squeeze to remove excess liquid.
Combine spinach mixture and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cover and chill 2 hours.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls and place 1 1/2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheets. Chill at least 30 minutes before baking.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; serve warm.
Yield:
4 dozen.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt together 1 (12 ounce) package chocolate chips and 1 stick margarine.
Pour over graham cracker layer.
Chill, then cut into squares.

title: company breakfast
directions: Beat eggs and all other ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake cookie on pizza pan as called for on cookie recipe on box.
Let cool.
Mix Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese together and spread over cookie.
Top with fruit and refrigerate.

title: light custard-like bread pudding
directions: Trim crust from bread and cut remainder into 2-inch cubes. Beat eggs and sugar in a large bowl until pale yellow, then add next 5 ingredients.
Add bread cubes and toss, coating well.
Pour this mixture into a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until set, about 30 minutes.
Transfer baking dish to wire rack and allow to cool slightly.
Ladle Blueberry-Lemon Sauce over top.

title: colorado coffee cake
directions: Generously grease a 10-inch fluted tube pan.
Sprinkle pecans in the bottom of the pan.
Arrange the frozen dough balls on top of the pecans; sprinkle pudding mix over dough balls.
In a small saucepan cook and stir the brown sugar, butter, and cinnamon until butter is melted.
Pour butter mixture over pudding mix and dough balls in the tube pan.
Cover and refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours. Uncover and bake in a 350° oven about 30 minutes or till top is golden brown.
Immediately invert coffee cake onto a serving platter.
Let stand about 15 minutes to cool slightly before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: *I use low fat ham lunchmeat cut up rather than Spam.

title: floating peaches
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar, salt and 1/2 peach syrup.
Mix remaining peach syrup with milk and scald.
Stir in cornstarch mixture slowly. Cook over hot water for 10 minutes, stirring constantly, until thick and clear.
Mix small amount into egg. Return to
remaining hot mixture and blend.
Add lemon rind and 6 marshmallows which have been cut into bits.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Turn into 6 glass custard cups. Top with peaches (hollow side up).
Place remaining marshmallows in peach hollow and place under broiler until browned.
Yields 6 portions.

title: vegetable-beef crock-pot
directions: Put all ingredients into crockery vessel.
Cut meat into large pieces if necessary to fit into vessel.
Cover and cook 8 to 10 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Cut shortening into flour and sugar. Dissolve yeast cake in water and mix into flour mixture.
Set in greased bowl for 1 hour. Knead well and roll out. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar. Roll up and cut into 1/4 to 1/2-inch rolls.
Let set overnight at room temperature.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes and frost with confectioners sugar frosting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Set aside pecans or parsley.
Soak minced onion in 1/4 ??? water or red wine for 15 minutes.
Mix all ingredients, except pecans or parsley.
Form into ball.
Roll in pecans or parsley. Serve with assorted crackers.

title: pork chop suey
directions: Saute pork strips for 5 minutes, but not until browned. Add celery and onions and cook for 2 to 3 minutes longer. Add salt and boiling water. Add molasses and soy sauce;	add cornstarch which has been blended with 1/2 cup warm water. Cook until mixture boils, stirring constantly. Add more hot water, if necessary. Add vegetables until
thoroughly heated. Serve with hot, fluffy rice. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the flour, nuts and sugar in a bowl.
Stir in melted butter until mixture is crumbly.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Pour 2/3 of mixture onto greased pan, reserving the remainder for topping.
Bake 15 minutes, until crisp.

title: raisin crumb cake
directions: Mix
well
the	flour, salt, sugar and shortening (with hands, keep 3/4 cup for
top).
Add
raisins
and	nuts to the rest. Stir soda into
buttermilk	and
add
egg and molasses. Then blend in first mixture.
Pour
into 9-inch cake pan (well greased).
Put the 3/4 cup crumbs	on
top
and bake in a slow 325° oven for 50 minutes.
(Take
a	double portion for larger cake.)

title: mexican meat loaf pie
directions: In large bowl, mix ground beef, egg, bread crumbs, Worcestershire sauce and 1/2 of the salsa.
When thoroughly mixed together, press into 10-inch ungreased pie pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven, leaving oven on. Drain excess grease.
Sprinkle cheese over top of pie and return to oven for 5 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve by cutting in pie wedges and spooning remaining salsa over top. Serves 4 to 6.

title: two in one cake
directions: Cream Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Sift flours together (two times).
Put vanilla in milk.
Combine flour and milk mixtures together a little at a time and beat each time.
Combine with Crisco, sugar and egg mixture.
Beat until really smooth.
Pour into 9-inch cake pans.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Dredge chicken breasts in a mixture of the first 4 ingredients. Melt 1 stick margarine in a baking pan and place chicken breasts therein.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with the soup, wine and mushrooms with liquid.
Bake at 400° until bubbling, then turn oven to 300°.
Cover with aluminum foil and cook for 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Mix well and roll out thin.
Cut in strips.
Have chicken boiling.
Drop in a few at a time until you have all of them. Boil gradually and then turn down on low and cover.

title: bread pudding
directions: Butter bread and put a single layer in a 9 x 10-inch pan. Sprinkle with raisins.
Continue to layer, ending with bread. Heat milk.
Add sugar and stir into beaten eggs.
Add cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour over bread.
Press top layer down.
Sprinkle with additional cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Combine meat with onion, eggs, cornstarch, salt and pepper, 1 tablespoon mustard and 1/2 cup milk. Shape into balls and brown. Place in casserole. Add remaining ingredients to skillet. Heat until thickened. Pour over meatballs. Bake, covered, at 325° for 1 hour. Yields 6 servings.

title: coconut cream cake
directions: Blend shortening and margarine together in large mixing bowl on medium-high speed.
Add sugar gradually and beat until fluffy. Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Sift flour and soda together.
Add alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add 1 2/3 cups coconut to cake batter.
Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form; fold into batter.

title: chinese broccoli
directions: Mix above together in large bowl.
Reserve 1 bunch broccoli. Wash broccoli; trim and cut into medium, uniform pieces.
(Tough stems can be peeled off and used.)
Steam until crisp-tender and still bright green.
Drain off any accumulated water.
Toss immediately with marinade.
Serve hot as a vegetable or chill and serve as marinated salad.
Lasts several days in refrigerator.

title: crunch pound cake
directions: Grease and flour tube cake pan.
Combine all ingredients and beat with mixer 12 minutes.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on rack before dumping from pan.

title: argentine salad
directions: Stir jello, water and juice; stir well.
Fold in pineapple, prunes and nuts.
I double recipe and pour in oiled jello mold (oiling thoroughly allows jello to release easily).

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar, granulated sugar and butter flavoring.
Beat well eggs and extract.
Add flour, soda, salt, oats and pecans.
Mix and spoon onto ungreased cookie sheet or make into a roll to slice and bake.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hot fruit
directions: Drain fruits; add pie filling and brown sugar.
Bake for 15 minutes after adding almond slivers.
Serve warm.

title: five layer casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add seasoning.
Cover bottom of greased baking dish with sliced potatoes.
Spread rice evenly over potatoes.
Spread beef and onions over rice.
Sprinkle green pepper over beef.
Then spoon tomatoes over top evenly.
Mix catsup and water; pour over all.
Cover and bake for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine everything, except the chocolate, in a pan over low heat.
Let cool.
Shape into balls.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Put toothpicks in balls and swirl in chocolate.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Store in freezer until ready to use.

title: confetti cornbread
directions: Heat oil in an 8-inch cast-iron or 8-inch square pan in a 400° oven for 5 minutes.
Combine cornmeal and next 8 ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Set aside.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all together. Form into small balls of same size. Bake at 300° until lightly brown, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: quick cole slaw
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream, vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and onion.
Combine cabbage and carrots.
Pour dressing over shredded vegetables and mix well.

title: biscuit casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; add paste, water, salt and pepper. Remove from heat; add mushrooms.
Grease square casserole dish. Press biscuits on bottom to make crust.
Add meat mixture.
Put cheese on top.
May garnish with sliced tomatoes if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: party rye spread
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot over small rye bread.

title: easy pudding salad
directions: Mix pudding and milk together like you would for instant pudding; add Cool Whip and pineapple.
Stir together. Refrigerate until set up.
Before serving, slice bananas into salad and stir.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in one bowl and all liquid in another bowl. Combine the two and mix well.
Pour in 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Place into greased casserole.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in a saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk and stir to remove lumps.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often, until the mixture boils.
Cook, stirring constantly, 5 minutes more.
Remove from heat.
Stir a small amount of the hot mixture into beaten egg yolks and return to the hot mixture.
Cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla.
Slice bananas into pie shell.
Pour hot milk mixture over bananas.
Top with meringue and bake at 350° for 12 minutes or until meringue just begins to brown.

title: pepper dye pride chicken
directions: Place cut fryer pieces in shallow baking pan, 9 x 13-inch. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add stuffing.
Sprinkle over top of each piece.
Pour mushroom soup over entire area.
Put tiny piece of butter on each piece of chicken.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Peel and seed zucchini.
Cut into chunks or sliced.
Cook until almost done.
Drain, then place in cold water for 5 minutes. Drain, then add all of the ingredients and mix.
Pour in pie shell and dot with butter.
Top with pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Mix cake mix, egg and margarine.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and pat this mixture in the bottom of this pan with wet fingers.
Beat eggs well.
Add cream cheese and beat.
Add confectioners sugar and beat.
Pour this mixture on top of the cake batter.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Substitute for buttermilk: 1/2 cup milk with 1 teaspoon vinegar and 1 teaspoon baking soda.

title: lo-cal stir-fry sweet and sour chicken
directions: Pour pineapple juice in wok or frypan.
Heat; add onion, green pepper and chicken.
Cook and stir about 10 minutes.
Add soy sauce, pineapple and vinegar.
Mix cornstarch with 1/4 cup water; add to thicken mixture.
Serve over hot rice.
Serves 4.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut up cooked and deboned chicken breasts.
Mix with sour cream and cream of chicken soup.
In a small bowl, crush crackers and mix with melted butter; add poppy seed.
Pour over chicken and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cherry rum cake(from 1975 edition)
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Place Bundt pan in oven with butter to melt.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix 2 cups Bisquick baking mix and 2/3 cup milk until soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonfuls onto boiling stew.
Cook uncovered over low heat 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 dumplings.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Use tiny rolls. Open them and spread mixture on both sides of roll.
Top each with a slice of cheese and ham before closing.
Heat in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.
May be prepared and frozen.
Makes 20 tiny sandwiches.

title: creamy butter frosting
directions: Cream the butter or margarine and salt in mixing bowl.
Blend in the confectioners sugar alternately with 1/3 to 1/2 cup hot cream. Add the vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Thin with cream, if necessary.

title: roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Wash chicken. Rub 1/2 stick of butter over chicken. Cut up fresh herbs and butter. Place inside cavity of chicken. Pour 1/4 cup of white cooking wine and 1/2 can of chicken broth inside cavity of chicken. Pour remaining can of chicken broth and 1/4 cup of white cooking wine over chicken. Sprinkle salt, pepper and paprika over chicken. Place in baking pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours. Remove from oven and let rest for 5 minutes before cutting.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix and store in container.
Use 3 or 4 teaspoons in mug of hot water.

title: creamy rice casserole
directions: Place soup, water and butter in a casserole; bring to a boil in microwave (use saucepan for conventional stove).
Stir rice into mixture.
Cook, covered, at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
Stir thoroughly every 10 minutes to prevent sticking.

title: meal in a skillet
directions: In deep frying pan, cut Polish sausage in 1/2-inch, then place cabbage over sausage. Salt, pepper and soy sauce to taste. Cook until cabbage is half done. Place potatoes on top, then add onions. Cook until done.

title: 8 vegetable fry
directions: Good when garden is just coming in and you don't have enough of anything for a dish.
Mix all vegetables together in large bowl.
Salt and pepper.
Mix flour and meal and shake over veggies, turning to coat all veggies.
Dump into large skillet and cover.
Fry until tender and it is brown as you want it.
Yummy good.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into small strips.
Brown lightly in a large frying pan.
Stir in sour cream and stroganoff seasoning mix.
Continue stirring over medium heat until mixture is warm or hot.
Serve over rice with a favorite vegetable or salad.

title: bacon-potato bake
directions: Quarter potatoes and put in shallow 2-quart baking dish with the onions.
Sprinkle with flour and seasonings; toss until vegetables are well coated and press down in dish.
Add water to half the depth of vegetables.
Arrange bacon on top and cover with lid or foil.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in casserole.
Add soup mix, water and rice. Place cut-up chicken on top (may use chicken breasts only if preferred).
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: ole dip
directions: Place all ingredients together.
Bake for 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.
Dip tortilla chips.

title: seafood casserole with mushrooms
directions: Cook rice following package directions; drain. Spoon into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Saute celery, onion and green pepper in margarine in skillet until lightly browned. Blend butter and flour in a saucepan. Cook for 1 minute. Stir in milk and Worcestershire sauce. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Add sauteed vegetables, mayonnaise, shrimp, crab meat, tuna and mushrooms; mix well. Pour over rice. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serves 8.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Put together in layers and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Add breadcrumbs and grated cheese.
Sprinkle on top.

title: crumb cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles a coarse meal.
Remove 1 cup of mixture and combine with cinnamon and nuts; set aside.
To remaining crumb mixture, add milk and baking powder.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle the reserved crumb topping over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with whipped topping and a pecan half, if desired.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: tempting shrimp spread(appetizer)
directions: Combine butter, cream cheese, mayonnaise, garlic salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice; mix well.
Stir in onion, celery and shrimp.
Serve with crackers or party rye bread. Yields about 2 1/4 cups.

title: tuna fish casserole(microwave)
directions: Mix together soup and milk.
Microwave (covered in microwave casserole dish) on High for 3 minutes.
Add Minute rice.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
While waiting, cook vegetables on High for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add to soup and rice mixture.
Add choice of meat now.
Cook on High for 7 minutes (covered).
Top with fried onion rings and put in microwave for 1 minute (uncovered).

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix rice, canned soups and water.
Pour in buttered baking pan.
Place cut-up chicken on top.
Sprinkle with onion soup. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours or at 325° for 3 hours.

title: easy time squares
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Gradually add sugar to margarine in large mixer bowl, creaming at medium speed of mixer until light and fluffy.
At medium speed, add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
At low speed, add flour and lemon juice.
Pour batter into well-greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mark off into 24 squares.
Place 1 heaping tablespoonful of filling in center of each square.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
While warm, sift confectioners sugar over cake.
Cut into squares.
Yields 24 squares

title: bean soup
directions: Add pea beans into large kettle.
Add 1 gallon water and bring to a boil.
Add 1 tablespoon baking soda and bring to boil.
Drain and rinse with water.
Put beans into large kettle and add bacon, tomatoes, carrots, celery, onions, potatoes, pepper and garlic. Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add cornstarch and flour to water.
Mix until smooth.
Add to soup until thickened to desired consistency.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste with 1 cup of water.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring often.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans for 3 hours.
Cook for 30 minutes and pour off liquid.
Put more water in and cook until tender.
Before done, add sugar and salt.
Fry sausage after slicing it and add to beans.
Cook spices in remaining fat from sausage and add to beans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in baking dish.
Place chicken pieces in dish. Top with uncooked rice and onion.
Cover with cream of chicken soup and water.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Cook in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: chinese shrimp and chicken
directions: In a large bowl, toss together shrimp and chicken; add cornstarch and toss to coat well.
In a large skillet, heat corn oil over medium high heat.
Add onion and ginger; stir-fry 1 minute.
Add shrimp mixture; stir-fry 1 to 2 minutes.
Stir in sesame oil until blended.
Add peas, wine, soy sauce and sugar. Stir constantly over medium heat until boiling and thickened. Serve with rice.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams, saving juice.
Cream the cream cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt or onion juice. Gradually add clam juice until dip consistency (will thicken a little after refrigerated).
Add clams and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Good with potato chips.

title: broccoli bars
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients except butter together and pour in pan with butter, spread evenly (do not mix butter in).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Can also be made with spinach.
Substitute spinach for broccoli.

title: angel frost punch
directions: Cut the peel into halves or quarters.
Let them stand overnight in salted water (one tablespoon salt to one quart water).
Drain and wash thoroughly.
Simmer in clear water, changing the water several times, until it has no bitter taste.
When the peel is tender, drain, cut into strips or add whole to the syrup and simmer until it is transparent.
Drain, roll in granulated sugar and allow the peel to dry well before packing.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Add ingredients in order given; beat well with each addition. Drop tablespoon for each cookie onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
When cookies are cool, ice each with chocolate icing.

title: treasure cake
directions: Begin by beating together in large bowl the shortening, sugar, eggs and mashed, cooked carrots.
Next stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread batter into 13 x 9 cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp and cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower and peas in 1/2 to 1 inch boiling salt water just until tender, 3 to 5 minutes; drain.
In saucepan, heat milk, soup, salt and pepper over low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in cauliflower, peas and shrimp; heat through.
If you wish, garnish with toasted almonds.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: shrimp bayou
directions: Bring water to a boil; add shrimp and cook 3 to 5 minutes. Drain well; rinse with cold water.
Peel and devein shrimp. Combine oil and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Add shrimp; toss gently.
Cover and chill mixture 8 hours, tossing occasionally.
Yield:
15 appetizer servings.

title: ginger ale pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and margarine.
Cream sugar into this mixture. Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and mix.
Add ginger ale and lemon flavoring and mix.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mixed bean soup
directions: Wash beans and place in a large kettle.
Cover with water 2 inches above bean line.
Add salt and soak overnight; drain in the morning.
Add 2 quarts of water (8 cups) and ham hocks.
Bring to a boil.
Add 1 onion, tomatoes, chili powder, lemon juice and pepper.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Remove ham from hocks before serving.
Makes 4 quarts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients, including sugar, into a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until smooth.
Grease 3 loaf pans and flour.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Remove from oven and let stand 10 minutes.
Run knife along sides of pan, then remove from pan.

title: chicken divan
directions: Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream together sugar and oil.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Mix well.
Stir dry ingredients together and add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Pour into 2 well greased and floured 9 x 5 loaf pans.
Bake at 350 degrees about 1
1/2 hours or until loaves test for doneness.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Place bread on wire rack to cool completely before slicing.

title: candied yams
directions: Melt butter in skillet over low heat; blend in sugar and salt. Increase heat and bring to boiling; add potatoes and cook over medium heat, turning potatoes several times, about 20 minutes or until potatoes are well glazed and thoroughly heated. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: avocado and crabmeat salad
directions: Peel the avocados; cut them in half and discard the pits.
Cut each half into 6 wedges.
Squeeze the lime juice over the wedges to prevent discoloration.
Sprinkle the wedges lightly with salt. Core the tomatoes and cut each tomato into 8 wedges.
Sprinkle each wedge lightly with salt.
Spoon equal portions of the crab mixture on each of 4 luncheon plates.
Garnish each serving with 6 avocado slices and 4 tomato wedges.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley and serve.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Chop pecans, candy and dates and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar and add eggs, one at a time.
Add candy, nuts and dates which have been rolled in a small amount of flour.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300° in a well-greased and floured pan.
Bring to boil 2 cups sugar and 1 1/2 cups orange juice.
Punch holes in cake and pour mixture over cake, letting it soak into holes.
Will freeze well.

title: harriet's chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Add eggs, vanilla and oil.
Mix together well and add 2 cups boiling water. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: oven baked beef stew
directions: Trim stew meat and place in bottom of casserole dish.
Pour undiluted soup over and mix together.
Slice onion over top.
Cover and bake 2 hours at 300° to 325°.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour to brown.
Serves four.
Serve over mashed potatoes, rice or pasta.
Delicious and easy!

title: meatball casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form small balls out of mixture. Place in skillet with oil.
Fry slowly until brown.
Take out and place in casserole.
Add Ragu sauce.
Heat in oven thoroughly.

title: death by chocolate
directions: *May be made without coffee liqueur if you desire; still just as good!

title: finger jello
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into sheet cake pan.
Let gel.
Cut into pieces.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.
Leave out of broth.
Add 4 to 5 cups of water to broth.
Add soup.
Flour and press out biscuits and cut in quarters.
Add to broth one at a time.
Slowly stir once and awhile.
Leave off cover while cooking.
After dumplings are done, add chicken.
Serves 10 or more.

title: pineapple au gratin
directions: Mix pineapple, cheese, sugar and flour together.
Put in a 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle crackers over this and drizzle margarine over it.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: french style liver
directions: Dip liver slices into French dressing.
Mix together flour, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Dredge liver in seasoned flour. Cook slowly in fat or oil until well browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, salt, cinnamon, baking powder and baking soda.
Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Then add dry ingredients.
Last, add the zucchini.
Bake in a
preheated oven at 350° for 45 minutes in greased and floured 9 x 3 x 12-inch pan.
Test cake for doneness.

title: stir-fried cabbage
directions: In 10-inch nonstick skillet, heat margarine over high heat until bubbly and hot.
Add celery, stirring quickly and frequently for 1 minute.
Add cabbage, bell pepper and onion; continue to stir.
Fry until vegetables are tender-crisp, approximately 2 to 3 minutes.
Add soy sauce and pepper.
Stir well and cook for 1 minute longer.
Makes 4 servings.
Contains only 39 calories.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls out on 15 x 17-inch jelly roll pan.
Pat seams together so dough is a solid sheet.
Bake as directed on package. Cool.
Mix the cream cheese and salad dressing mix; add mayonnaise and spices.
Spread on cooled crust and top with chopped vegetables and grated cheese.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 1 x 3-inch strips and enjoy.

title: hamburger beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Pour into large baking dish.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together into a large bowl.
Add the cold shortening and work all through the flour with finger tips. Every bit of flour should be combined with a bit of the fat.
Add the buttermilk and stir vigorously until the dough forms a ball. Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface, Knead lightly for 10 strokes.
Stop just as soon as the dough begins to look smooth.
Pat the dough out to approximately an 8 x 7 x 3/4-inch rectangle.
Cut into 2 inch rounds.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake in an oven preheated to 500° for 8 minutes.

title: coleslaw
directions: Toss cabbage and onion together in a serving dish.
In a small bowl, combine vinegar, sugar and salt; stir until sugar and salt are dissolved.
Pour over cabbage and stir to blend well. Serve immediately or refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: paula's pizza dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in ungreased 9 x 13 dish.
Pour pizza sauce over cream cheese, then layer onions, cheese, black olives and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.	Serve with Frito Scoops.

title: cousin adie's chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a small bowl, combine sugar, cocoa and flour; set aside. In a big bowl, combine remaining ingredients, except pecans.
Add dry ingredients to the wet mixture.
Stir until smooth. Add pecans. Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: oven paprika potatoes
directions: Butter a casserole; fill with the cubed potatoes.
Dot with butter; sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: easy oven pork chops
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper, stirring well. Combine egg and milk. Dip chops in egg mixture and dredge in crumb mixture. Place in a lightly greased baking dish. Drizzle butter over pork chops. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour or until tender.

title: buttermilk biscuits
directions: Blend all dry ingredients; cut in shortening until crumbly-coarse.
Add milk and stir to form soft dough.
Place onto lightly floured surface; knead gently for 30 seconds.
Roll out. Cut into desired size and bake on ungreased baking sheet for 15 minutes in 450° oven (varies as to altitude).

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Let cool and debone.
Reserve 2 cups broth from boiled chicken.
Mix mushroom soup and chicken soup with broth.
In casserole dish, place 1 pie crust, then deboned chicken, can Veg-All, then mixture of soups and broth.
Top with other pie crust.
Add a little butter on top of pie crust.
Cook until crust gets done.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Place cucumbers in a gallon jug.
Then add the 3 spices.
Fill jug 3/4 full of vinegar and finish with water.
Put lid on; let set for 6 to 8 weeks.
Remove cucumbers, wash and prick holes with a fork.
Place in quart jars.
Add sugar (2 cups) to each jar. Seal and set aside.
Turn jars upside down every day or so until sugar dissolves.
Makes own juice.

title: eclair cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Grease a 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet and spread mixture evenly.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Let cool.

title: filet of beef chateaubriand style
directions: Prepare Maitre d'Hotel.
In a deep bowl, mix softened butter with finely chopped parsley and a few drops of lemon.
Roll into log shape and place in the freezer.
Cut the filet into 4 thick slices; pound slightly to widen.
Trim edges so that slices are round.

Spread with butter and cook on a very hot charcoal grill. Baste with butter occasionally and salt and pepper towards the end. Filets should be well cooked on the outside but pink on the inside. Remove "Maitre d'Hotel" butter from the freezer and cut into round slices.
Place one slice on each filet and serve.

title: lasagne(serves 8)
directions: Step 1:
In a skillet, brown meat; add parsley, salt, oregano, basil, sugar, pepper, tomato paste, tomato sauce and water.
Let simmer 15 minutes.

title: raisin-oatmeal cookies
directions: Grind orange with rind in grinder or blender; add to oil, honey, milk and vanilla and blend together.
Combine remaining ingredients; add to orange mixture.
Stir to blend well together. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheets.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Crumble ground beef in heated frying pan.
Cook and stir until lightly browned.
Finely chop onion, green pepper and celery; add to ground beef and cook until tender.
Add tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and cook slowly, about 1 hour until thickened.
Serve over hot, cooked spaghetti or macaroni.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in small casserole and bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Serve hot with crackers.
Delicious!

title: quick chili rice dinner
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet; add spices, corn, green pepper, tomato sauce and water.
Cover and bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Stir in rice; cover and simmer 5 minutes. Pour into baking dish and cover with cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: easy cherry crunch
directions: Place all the ingredients in 13 x 9-inch pan in the order listed.
Bake at 325° about 1 hour.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Cook broccoli; drain. Add soup, milk and Cheez Whiz to onion; cook 15 minutes.
Add cooked rice and cooked broccoli; mix all together.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: killer brownie
directions: Melt caramels with 1/3 of milk.
Melt butter with rest of milk; add all cake mix to the milk and butter.
Stir well and add nuts.
Spread 1/4 of batter into 2 (9 x 12-inch) pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out and cool 5 minutes.
Put 1/2 chocolate chips on each pan.
Pour 1/2 caramel over each pan.
Put rest of batter over top of each pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Cool 4 to 5 hours before cutting.

title: spicy stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Rinse mushrooms and remove stems.
Place mushrooms, cap side down, on a cookie sheet.
Spoon a bit of sauce in cavity.
Alternate layers of pepperoni and salami on top of the sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake at 350° for 10-15 minutes or until bubbly and cheese has melted.
Serve at once.
Serves 6 (2 mushrooms per person).

title: mostaccioli and sausage
directions: Cook Creamette mostaccioli according to package directions. Drain.
In large saucepan, brown sausage.
Pour off fat.
Add onion and pepper.
Cook and stir until tender.
Add pasta sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Toss hot cooked mostaccioli with oil.
Serve with sauce.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: nina's crab quarters(appetizer)
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Spread on English muffin halves. Then quarter the muffins but not necessarily separated.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon in 1 quart of water.
Add potatoes, celery, onion and carrots; cook 15 minutes. Add the vegetables and cook 6 to 8 minutes. Add your soup and Velveeta cheese. Simmer until cheese melts.

title: coconut kisses
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar at high speed until foamy. Add sugar gradually and continue beating until sugar is dissolved.

title: taco salad
directions: Add Fritos and dressing just before serving.

title: tapioca pudding
directions: Mix sugar, tapioca, milk and egg in a saucepan; let stand 5 minutes.
Stirring constantly, cook on medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Cool 20 minutes.
Stir.
Spoon into dishes.

title: blueberry yum yum
directions: Cut butter into cookie crumbs and mix well.
Press into large glass baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 5 minutes.

title: alavna's e z burritos
directions: Over low flame, in 5-quart cooking pot, add cans of roast beef and gravy, chopped green bell pepper and 2 diced tomatoes (save the last tomato for adding to Burritos when rolled), 1 teaspoon ground cumin, 1 teaspoon garlic powder, 1 teaspoon seasoning salt and 1 teaspoon pepper.
Cook over low flame, covered, until bell pepper is soft.
Stir occasionally.
When meat mixture is cooked, heat tortillas, then one tortilla at a time.
Add meat mixture, 2 tablespoons cheese, 1 tablespoon tomatoes, 1 tablespoon shredded lettuce and roll.
You can also add your own favorite taco sauce.

title: pile-up one dish meal
directions: Put on a large serving plate with 1-inch edge in order listed. Serves 4 to 6.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix well by hand.
Pour into a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate cherry creams
directions: Melt chocolate bits and milk over low heat.
Add powdered sugar, nuts and cherries.
Cool until cool enough to handle.
Roll into balls and in coconut; chill.

title: chocolate town pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell; set aside.
Heat oven to 350°.
In small mixing bowl, cream butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until golden.
Cool 1 hour.
Serve warm.
Garnish with whipped cream.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Combine milk and cheese in saucepan (heat until cheese melts).

title: ham and cheese chicken rolls
directions: Flatten chicken to even thickness using palm of hand or flat side of meat mallet.
Place 1 ham slice and 1 cheese slice on each breast half.
Roll up chicken from narrow end, jelly roll fashion. Tuck in ham and cheese, if necessary; serve with wooden toothpicks.

title: microwave caramels
directions: Microwave on High all ingredients, except vanilla, for 16 minutes.
Stop and stir every 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.

title: scalloped cheese potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and place in baking dish.
Place soup over top of potatoes.
Dice cheese and butter and place on top; add milk. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are tender.
To speed up process, you can boil potatoes for 15 minutes and add ingredients, then microwave for 10 to 15 minutes until tender.

title: scandinavian tomato salad
directions: Arrange tomatoes around edge of plate.
Place onions in center.
Combine oil, dill, horseradish and salt.
Set aside for about 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Add vinegar; mix well.
Spoon over tomatoes and onions.
Serve chilled.

title: meat loaf - barbecue style
directions: Mix the ground beef, bread crumbs, beaten egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce together.
Form mixture into loaf and place in shallow baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over beef loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Baste loaf often and serve remaining sauce at the table with the loaf.
Serves 6.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all together and pour in 9 x 13 pan which has been sprayed with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: famous amos cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and both sugars in large bowl at high speed until creamy.
Add vanilla, eggs and 1 teaspoon water; blend thoroughly.
Stir in flour, baking soda and salt by hand until well mixed.
Stir in raisins and chips.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Cook 8 minutes.
Makes many.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add vinegar and water; boil 5 minutes.
Add beets and let stand 30 minutes to thicken.
Just before serving, heat on low and add butter (5 to 10 minutes).

title: sunset jam
directions: In preserving pot, put pears, pineapple, cherries, sugar and lemon juice.
Mix well. Bring to boiling point, stirring constantly, for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in fruit pectin.
Stir and skim for 5 minutes.
Put in hot jars and seal. Yields 5 pints.

title: maw maw's macaroni and cheese
directions: Grease a 2 quart casserole dish.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly.
Pour macaroni back into pot and add butter.
After butter melts, alternate layering macaroni and cheese in the greased dish, saving some cheese for the top of casserole.
Beat together eggs, milk, and salt.
Pour egg mixture over macaroni and cheese.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.

title: coconut butter balls
directions: Cream butter; add 2 tablespoons confectioners sugar and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy; add flour and mix well.
Mix in coconut.
Chill 15 minutes.
Roll in balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: dill butter
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender; blend until smooth. Chill.
Yields one portion.
This versatile butter is good as a topping for fresh cooked vegetables, or as a spread on crackers.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Set oven temperature at 300°. Mix chicken, soup, sour cream, broccoli and shredded Cheddar cheese. Melt butter and mix with crackers. Place chicken mixture in casserole dish and top with remaining cheese and crackers. Cooking time: 30 minutes.

title: hot spiced apple cider
directions: Put cider into a large kettle and add sugar and spices.
Heat to the boiling point, then reduce and add fruit slices.
Keep just below boiling point.
It will perfume your house for the holidays and be ready to serve guests.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, salt and eggs.
Add yeast and water. Mix and add flour.
You may need to use more flour as you knead the dough.
Put in a greased bowl.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours or until double in size.
Dough may also be put in icebox.
Will keep for 3 days.
Pinch off dough and form a ball.
Dip in melted butter and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease an 8-inch square pan.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar.
Stir well. Sift dry ingredients and all alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in butter.
Bake in prepared pan at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef across grain in thin strips.
Combine soy sauce, garlic, ginger and beef.
Heat oil in pan.
Add beef and toss until brown.
Cover and simmer until tender, 30 to 40 minutes. Add vegetables and cook until tender, about 10 minutes.

title: carrot and raisin salad
directions: Toss carrots with raisins.
Blend in remainder of ingredients, stirring into the carrot mixture.
Chill at least 30 minutes before serving.

title: green and yellow bean casserole
directions: Brown beef with onion, salt and pepper; drain. Mix with remaining ingredients using water from yellow beans. Add chili powder. Bake 45 minutes in casserole dish at 350°.

title: fluffy jello salad
directions: Mix topping and cottage cheese with spoon.
Add dry jello. Mix thoroughly.
Add drained fruits.
Leave in mixing bowl to chill.
Spoon on lettuce leaf to serve.

title: banana turnovers
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in shortening.
Sprinkle with water and mix lightly with a fork.
Divide into 8 balls.
Roll out each ball of dough.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix flour and milk in sauce pan.
Cook over low flame until thick.
Put in bowl and cool.
Cream butter and Crisco for 4 minutes with electric mixer.
Add sugar gradually and beat 4 minutes.
Add flour paste and beat 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and blend.

title: boil cookies
directions: Put first four ingredients together in saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil one minute.
Remove from heat and add very quickly last four ingredients.
Stir well and drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
(Have ingredients measured before you start.)

title: beef barley skillet
directions: Saute in skillet the ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cover and cook until barley is tender.

title: danish cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage and cook in small amount of unsalted water 8 minutes.
Drain well.
Place half of cabbage in buttered casserole.
Sprinkle with half of salt, pepper and paprika.
Dot with half of butter.
Add half of cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with cheese.
Beat eggs slightly with milk; pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: *ravani 2
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add egg yolks and vanilla.
Beat thoroughly.
Mix flour and farina and add, alternating with the milk.
In a separate bowl, beat the egg whites until stiff and fold into the batter.
Pour into a greased 9 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool slightly.
Pour room temperature syrup all over the cake, using only 2 2/3 cups syrup. Garnish with 1/2 cherry on the Ravani.
Cut into squares or diamonds.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Heat oil in frying pan.
Add cubed chicken.
Cook until starting to brown.
Add onion and green pepper.
Cook until chicken is tender, stirring often.

title: crabmeat stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Saute garlic and onion in oil until lightly browned.
Chop mushroom stems and mix with garlic and onion.
Stir in bread crumbs, crabmeat, cheese, parsley and seasonings.
Lightly mound stuffing in mushroom caps and place in 9-inch pie plate lightly wiped with olive oil.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients; mixture should be very moist but not soupy.
Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Place into non-preheated oven.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: *baked noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions. Rinse in cold water and drain.
Place in large bowl. Add cottage cheese and Feta cheese, which has been crumbled.
Add melted butter.
Beat eggs. Add salt, pepper and milk.
Add to noodles.
Toss all ingredients together.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: thin white sauce
directions: Combine butter and flour.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water until thick and smooth.
Add salt and pepper.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread bottom of dish (8 x 8-inch works well) with bean dip. Mix together Miracle Whip and sour cream; spread over dip. Sprinkle taco seasoning.
Next, add chopped green onions and drained black olives.
Sprinkle 8 ounce package shredded Cheddar cheese.
Top with chopped tomatoes.
Serve with dip size Fritos.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Ring in paper towels to get all moisture out.
While still warm, mix all other ingredients well and form into balls (they're a little slimy).
Put on cookie sheet close together and put into freezer for 1 hour.
Then you can put into plastic bags and keep frozen until you need them.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes, frozen, in 350° oven.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Combine lemon juice and cream cheese.
Spread on glass serving plate.
Smooth cocktail sauce over mixture.
Place shrimp on top. Next, sprinkle cheese and small onions.
Serve with Wheat Thins.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Beat in carrots.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla and almond.
Drop by teaspoonfuls.
Bake 8 minutes at 375°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In a greased baking dish (butter flavored Crisco); layer green beans, brown sugar, garlic powder and bacon to the top. Melt butter and mix with crackers; then spread cracker mixture and almonds over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix it all together.
Spoon it over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat oven at 375°.
Stir Cheddar cheese soup until smooth. Add milk.
In buttered casserole, arrange layers of potatoes, onion and sauce.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat and cool completely.
Chop lettuce, tomatoes and onion.
Add beans, cheese, meat and chips. Pour dressing over all and toss well.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together beef, crumbs, onion, bell pepper, beaten egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 cup tomato sauce. Combine the rest of the tomato sauce and all other ingredients. Pour over loaf.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco

and sugar. Add eggs 1 at a time. Add flour and milk and mix until smooth and creamy. Add vanilla and lemon flavoring. Mix well. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: peanut patties
directions: Combine in saucepan the sugar, water, peanuts and syrup. Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Let boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add butter, vanilla, salt and coloring.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased foil.

title: layer dip
directions: Arrange in layers as listed.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: molasses pudding
directions: Mix oil,
molasses and egg.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt, ginger, sugar and baking soda.
Gradually add flour mixture to molasses mixture.
Then add water.
Mix ingredients well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° until sides start leaving edge of pan.

title: truly different cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in heavy pan.
Add pecans and stir.
Remove from heat.
Combine sugar, flour, eggs and vanilla and mix only until blended.
Do not beat.
Add chocolate mixture and mix.
Again, do not beat.
Pour in 18 baking muffin cups and bake at 325° for about 30 to 35 minutes.

title: meatza pie
directions: Mix rice and 1 cup tomato sauce.
Line a large Pyrex pie plate with the mixture.
Mix the rest of the ingredients, except Cheddar cheese.
Spread over rice and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Trim separable fat from steak.
Partially freeze the beef. Thinly slice, across the grain, into bite size strips.
In a small bowl combine yogurt and cornstarch.
Stir in water, tomato paste and bouillon; set aside.

title: triple layer chocolate bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup of cocoa, sugar and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat the remaining ingredients together, except the nuts and chips. Stir in the nuts.
Spread over the prepared crust.
Top with chips.
Bake for 25 minutes or until set.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Brown beef in oil in large saucepan.
Add beef broth, vegetables and seasonings.
Bring to boiling point.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve hot. Recipe yields 3 quarts.

title: cherry ring salad
directions: Drain syrup from cherries and add to water to make one cup. In a saucepan, bring syrup almost to boiling and add to cherry flavored gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Add sherry or Chianti.
Pour into an 8-inch ring mold and chill until mixture begins to set.
Add pitted cherries and marshmallows.
Chill until firm.

title: "smoked lox cheese ball"
directions: Place all ingredients in food processor and blend until smooth. Form a ball and place in small bowl (which has been sprayed with Pam to keep it from sticking). After it has set up, you can easily take it out and put on a plate with crackers for serving.

title: corned beef ball
directions: Mix first five ingredients well by hand. Form into ball; roll in chopped pecans. Chill.

title: dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Put in an oiled pan and bake for approximately 30 to 45 minutes at 400°.

title: mom's brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 x 7 baking pan.
Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored in a medium bowl.
Add sugar gradually, beating well after each addition until mixture is fluffy.
Stir in vanilla, melted chocolate, and margarine.
Fold in flour, salt and 3/4 cup nuts; stir just until blended.
Pour batter into pan and sprinkle remaining nuts over top.
Bake for 18-20 minutes or until top crust is formed.
Cool 5 minutes on wire rack.
Cut into squares.
While still warm, remove from pan.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Combine Crisco and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs 1 at a time. Stir dry ingredients. Add evaporated milk. Add flavoring. Bake in greased tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Leave oven closed until done. Check near end of cooking time. Cooking times may vary.

title: baked chicken with tarragon and fennel
directions: Place chicken breast on foil-lined baking pan.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Cover loosely with foil to help retain moisture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until cooked through.

title: italian filled cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine or Crisco real well.
Add eggs, vanilla and milk.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add liquids.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned.
Cut cookies in half as soon as they come out of the oven.
Let cool; then fill with about 1/2 teaspoon of preserves.
Frost with different colored frostings and sprinkle top with nuts or colored sugars.

title: prairie fire bean dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts and mixture is thoroughly heated.
Transfer mixture to a chafing dish; serve with taco chips.
Yields 2 cups.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Combine flour, 1/2 cup cheese, paprika and oil; stir well. Press mixture into a 9-inch quiche dish.
Microwave at High 4 minutes; remove from oven and set aside.
Combine zucchini and next 4 ingredients in a 1-quart casserole; cover with heavy-duty plastic wrap.
Microwave at High 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain well on paper towels.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup cheese over crust; top with vegetable mixture.
Combine eggs, half and half and seasonings; stir until well blended.

Pour mixture over vegetables; microwave at Medium-high (70% power) 12 to 15 minutes, or until a knife inserted off center comes out clean (center will be slightly soft). Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Cover; let stand on the countertop 10 minutes before serving.
Yields one 9-inch quiche.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs, oil and sugar.
Add flour, baking soda and remaining ingredients.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nacho dip
directions: On a microwave plate spread cream cheese, Hormel chili, green chilies and Monterey Jack and Cheddar cheeses.
Warm in microwave. Dip nachos.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook and debone chicken, reserving broth.
Put in a large baking dish and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix chicken soup and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Cut up eggs for the next layer.
Mix butter, flour and milk.
Pour over top.
Bake at 350° until crust is golden brown, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated pea salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients and toss lightly.
Combine other ingredients in a jar.
Cover and shake.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill 12 hours.

title: cheesecake cupcakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cupcake pan with cupcake papers. Place a vanilla wafer in each cupcake tin.
Beat until creamy the cream cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add cream cheese mixture on top of each vanilla wafer until cupcake tin is 3/4 full.
Bake until set, approximately 25 minutes.
Cool.
Top each cupcake with 1 tablespoon of cherry pie filling.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix the oats in the boiling water and let set for 20 minutes. Add the remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: double apple waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in 1 cup apples, celery and walnuts. Pour into lightly oiled 5-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold.
Garnish with lettuce leaves.
Combine Cool Whip and salad dressing.
Fold in 1 1/2 cup apples.
Spoon into center of mold. Garnish with apple slices and walnut halves.
Serves 8.

title: pinto bean pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
For filling, combine eggs and evaporated milk in large bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Add pinto beans, sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and cloves.
Beat at low speed until well blended.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix together well the first 4 ingredients.
Chill slightly, then roll into 1-inch balls.
Dip into melted chocolate and place on wax paper lined cookie sheet.
Place in cool spot.

title: dirt cups
directions: You will need 8 plastic cups.

title: sausage spaghetti dinner
directions: Cook sausage in a Dutch oven over medium heat until browned, stirring occasionally.
Add onions and cook until lightly browned. Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, bay leaf and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook and simmer about 35 minutes.
Add green pepper; simmer an additional 10 minutes.
Prepare spaghetti according to package directions; drain.
Serve sauce over spaghetti.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Yields 6 servings.

title: english toffee
directions: Mix well.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Use an 8 x 8-inch pan for thicker crust.

title: homemade sloppy joes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except rolls, and cook until heated through and onions and peppers are cooked. Or, put all ingredients, except rolls, in a slow cooker and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours. Serve over rolls.

title: holiday fruit cookies
directions: Combine shortening, brown sugar, and eggs; mix thoroughly. Stir in sour milk, then sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in pecans, cherries, pineapple, and dates.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: danish apple bars
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening.
Beat egg yolk and add enough milk to make 2/3 cup liquid.
Mix well.
Stir in flour.

title: mushroom minute steaks
directions: Sprinkle beef steaks with salt and lemon pepper.
Cook a few steaks at a time in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until brown. Return steaks to skillet.
Add green pepper, onion and mushrooms. Heat over low heat until mushrooms are hot.

title: applesauce(sugar-free and fat-free)
directions: Pare, quarter and core apples. Cut into small pieces. Add water all into saucepan. Cover. When water begins to bubble, stir. Beat almost continuously until apples are soft enough to beat fine. Add spice (if you want). Serve either hot or cold.

title: 7-layer cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter; mix in graham cracker crumbs and press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Layer the coconut, chocolate chips and butterscotch morsels over crumb crust.
Drizzle sweetened condensed milk over top and sprinkle with walnuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool completely before cutting into small squares.

title: picante sauce
directions: Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until thickened as you like it.
Put into pint jars and process 30 minutes in boiling water bath. Makes 10 pints.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix and shape into soft ball.
Place in bowl, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions (in rectangular pan). While still hot, using a wooden spoon, poke holes at 1 1/2 to 2-inch intervals.
Pour condensed milk slowly over cake, allowing it to soak into holes.
Add Smucker's topping (also poured slowly).
Place in refrigerator; allow to cool completely.
Add Cool Whip.
Top with broken Heath bars.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake for 8 minutes at 400°.
Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Drain juice from peaches; add to Jell-O.
Set aside in refrigerator to thicken.
Beat the cream cheese; add sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel crust.
Place drained peaches on top.
Pour thickened Jell-O over peaches.
Place in refrigerator until Jell-O is set.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients together.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Needs to set 2 hours before serving.
Also, can use graham cracker crumbs and sprinkle with chocolate chips.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour and baking powder.
In another bowl, beat the milk, eggs and vanilla together.

Add the flour mixture alternating with the milk mixture to the butter and sugar beating well after each addition. The dough should be easy to handle; if not, chill it for 1 hour. Give your child some dough. Roll it into skinny snakes.
Bend each snake into a design on a foil covered cookie sheet and pinch the ends together. Sprinkle a thin layer of the crushed candy into the enclosed space.
Make sure the ends are sealed so melted candy won't leak out. Bake at 375° for 9 minutes.
Allow to cool and peel off the foil.

title: cottage cheese potato salad
directions: Set aside 1 egg for garnishing. Chop 2 eggs; mix with remaining ingredients except olives.
Chill.
Garnish with egg slices and olives.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken pecan
directions: In saucepan, melt butter; add bouillon.
Stir in flour and seasoning. Add milk and lemon juice.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Stir in chicken, celery, pimiento and all but 2 tablespoons pecans.
Heat well.
Trim with nuts.
Yields 8 servings.

title: grandmas buttermilk cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Put bacon drippings in a baking dish or skillet and let melt while oven is heating.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add corn meal, salt and baking soda; stir until combined. Add buttermilk and stir well.
Remove hot pan from oven, swirl drippings to coat pan (or skillet).
Pour drippings into batter. Stir well, pour batter into pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: In large saucepan, cook squash and onion in boiling water for 5 minutes or until tender.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Add drained squash and onion.
Mix in bread crumbs and cheese.
Spread into buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together and set aside.
Mix oil, eggs and sugar, beating after each addition.
Add dry ingredients, mix well.
Add carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: cut it short torte
directions: Mix and bake cake as directed on package in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or 3 regular cake pans (split tube cake pan in three layers if tube pan is used).
Cool.
Spread 1/3 of Cool Whip, then 1/3 of pie filling between each layer and top.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add liquid drained from blueberries and pineapple and enough water to make 1 cup.
Stir in blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into a 2-quart flat pan (9 x 13-inch).
Cover and chill until firm.

title: sweet tater stuff(the ole family holiday one)
directions: Combine all ingredients; pour into a buttered baking dish (9 x 13-inch).

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for several hours before serving.
Great with raw vegetables and/or crackers.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cream margarine, brown sugar and white sugar.
Beat egg and mix with applesauce.
Combine all ingredients.
Arrange by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool and enjoy!!

title: swedish kringle
directions: Make like pie crust and pat crust into 2 strips 3 x 12-inch long.

title: carrot wine
directions: Have water boiling, then add carrots.
Boil for 3 minutes. Strain and add sugar and yeast.
Put in any type of crock and cover with cloth; allow to set at least 30 days.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix together pie filling and pineapple in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over the top.
Melt butter and pour as evenly as possible over all.
Place in a 350° oven. Bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Slice each egg in half long ways and place yolk in small bowl. Smash yolk with fork until there are no lumps.
Add Miracle Whip and mustard.
Stir until smooth and thick.
Pout one spoonful at a time to each 1/2 egg white.
Sprinkle with paprika or pepper on top lightly.
Makes one dozen.

title: pickled pears
directions: Peel pears.
Mix spices, sugar, water and vinegar.
Bring to a boil and drop in pears.
Cook until tender.
Pack into jars.
Pour vinegar mixture over pears and seal.
Let sit at least 2 months before eating.

title: applescotch rolls
directions: Separate biscuits.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Coat biscuits in melted butter, then cover with sugar mixture.
Arrange in tight circle around pan, filling center also.

title: sweet and sour cabbage and meat balls
directions: Shred cabbage; saute in pan in olive oil with sliced or diced onion.
Add ketchup according to amount being made.
Add ginger ale (1 small bottle or can).
Make meat balls as you normally would. Place on top of cabbage mixture and cook until meat balls are done. Serve with rice.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salted water until just tender.
Mix together soup, pimiento, water chestnuts, milk and sour cream. Add to drained squash and onion.
Melt butter and mix with stuffing mix and chicken flavor.
Line casserole with 1/2 stuffing mix.
Top with squash mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese and remaining stuffing.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Travels nicely. Good hot or reheated.

title: frozen wedding punch
directions: Mix jello and sugar in boiling water until completely dissolved.
Add frozen lemonade plus the water it calls for.
Add pineapple juice.
Freeze in gallon size freezer bags.
Allow to thaw for 1 to 2 hours prior to serving.
Add ginger ale to "chunks" of frozen mixture in punch bowl.
Stir until slushy.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together.
Wilt cabbage leaves.
Roll ground beef mixture into balls.
Put inside cabbage leaves.
