Fold cabbage leaf around ball.
Hold together with a toothpick.
Place in kettle and pour in enough tomato juice to cook until done.

title: dump cake
directions: Empty fresh fruit, juice and all, in cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit.
Dot with butter and oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, put Cool Whip and nuts on top.
I do this as I serve each piece.

title: chicken salad supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill and put on crescent rolls or stuff in tomatoes.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Cook and brown sausage.
Mix in and cook green pepper and onion.
Mix in Italian salad dressing mix.
Unroll crescent roll dough (do not separate).
Place half of sausage mixture in the middle of each roll.
Sprinkle with cheese and roll up.
Brush egg white on the top of the rolls.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make a paste of cocoa and food coloring.
Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs.
Combine sifted flour with salt.
Divide flour into three parts and milk into 2 parts.
Add alternately to cream mixture, beginning with and ending with flour.
Beat well after each addition.
Add vanilla.
If using an electric mixer, remove and fold in vinegar and soda carefully.
Pour mixture in equal portions into two 9-inch pans that have been greased and floured lightly.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: stir-fry veggies
directions: In a large skillet over high heat in hot oil, cook onion, carrots, broccoli and cauliflower, stirring quickly and often, for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add olives, seasonings and water; cover and cook for 4 minutes, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: turtle pie
directions: Place caramel topping in small saucepan.
Heat over medium heat until topping comes to a boil, stirring constantly.
Pour into pie shell.
Arrange pecans on topping and chill.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Cut eggplant into thin slices.
Fry in oil until brown and drain well on paper.
Place 1 layer of fried eggplant in casserole, cover with sauce, sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and cover with a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat procedure until all eggplant is used, ending with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes and serve.
Makes 4.

title: sugarless date nut cookies
directions: Mix flour and oleo.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape in 1-inch balls.
Pat down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
These are good for diabetics.

title: turkey loaf
directions: Mix together all ingredients until homogeneous.
Place in an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water; stir until dissolved and set aside.
Heat cranberries and marshmallows over medium heat until marshmallows melt.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix, chill and serve.

title: dirt(with spring flowers)
directions: Crush cookies in blender or food processor (4 or 5 at a time). Divide crushed cookies into three equal parts.
Using a mixer, cream together cream cheese, margarine and powdered sugar.
Set aside.
Mix the milk and instant pudding.
Add Cool Whip to pudding mixture.
Combine with the cheese mixture.

title: famous dirt pie
directions: In a small mixing bowl, cream together the cream cheese, butter or margarine and powdered sugar.
Set aside until the next mixture is complete.
In a large mixing bowl, blend the vanilla pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Fold ingredients from the first mixture into the second mixture; set aside.
Using the food processor, finely crush Oreo cookies until it resembles dirt!

title: chipped beef cheese ball
directions: Cream all ingredients together; form into a ball and let stand in fridge 2 hours.
Serve on crackers.

title: punch
directions: Mix juice and ginger ale well.
Add sherbet and serve.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and reduce heat at boiling point.
Cook for 6 minutes.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in salted water.
Drain well.
Mash squash; drain any excess water.
Mix in onions, eggs, sugar and 1/4 cup butter. Place in a 2-quart buttered casserole.
Spread cracker crumbs evenly on top.
Drizzle remaining butter evenly over crackers. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until thoroughly heated.

title: date roll candy
directions: Cut dates into small pieces.
Bring sugar and milk to a boil. Add dates and continue cooking to 238°, stirring constantly.
Be careful not to scorch.
Remove from heat and add nuts, salt and vanilla.
Beat until cool enough to handle with hands.
Shape into roll about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and slice when cold.

title: peanut crispies
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil, then remove from heat. Stir in peanut butter until melted, then stir in noodles. Drop onto waxed paper using 2 teaspoons. Let cool.

title: shaker lemon pie
directions: Slice lemons, discard seed, toss with sugar and refrigerate overnight.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Stir lemons into eggs and place mixture into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake until done.

title: baked jarlsberg dip
directions: Combine all wet ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in onion, then cheese.
Put in a 9-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with crackers.

title: dilly dip
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a small bowl, and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for several
hours
to
blend the flavors. Serve with raw vegetables.

title: lemon squares
directions: Melt oleo.
Add 2 cups flour and 1/2 cup of powdered sugar. Press in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 minutes.
Then beat eggs and lemon juice.
Add 2 cups sugar, salt, 4 tablespoons flour and baking powder.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake 25 minutes or more until light brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into bars.

title: iced brownies
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until smooth.
Pour into square Teflon pan.
Bake for about 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: baked rice
directions: Cook rice until tender in salt water.
Mix the rest of the ingredients add rice.
Pour into baking dish.
Dot top with butter. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: chicken and biscuits casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt 2 tablespoons oleo in saucepan.
Add onion, celery and bell peppers until tender.
Combine sherry or water, mushroom soup, broth and 1/4 cup flour.
Add to onion mixture, cook until thick.
Stir in chicken and mixed vegetables. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine 3/4 cup flour, oats and baking powder.
Cut in remaining oleo until crumbly.
Stir in milk and egg white until moistened.
Drop 1/4 cupfuls onto chicken mixture.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cajun chow mein
directions: Brown ground beef in fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Cook 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Grease an 8-inch round cake plate.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: jam dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl.
Set in fridge overnight.
Pour cold over 1 bar of cream cheese.
Serve with Triscuits crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and butter.
Add eggs and pecans.
Fill unbaked pie shell with mixture and bake in moderately hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to moderate (350°) and continue to bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Arrange broccoli in shallow buttered dish; top with chicken.
Blend soup and milk; pour over chicken. Sprinkle cheese on top; bake at 450° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cheese is lightly golden.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Dice apples and add sugar.
Beat eggs and oil.
Add all three mixtures alternately, then add walnuts.
Pour in greased pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tex-mex dip(great for super bowl or pool parties)
directions: Combine avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Layer as follows:
bean dip, avocado mixture, sour cream mixture, onions, tomatoes, olives and Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Set out at room temperature two hours before serving to allow mixture to soften. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Add Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Cool. Add last 3 ingredients; mix well.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine soup and cream; beat.
Blend butter and flour and stir into soup mixture.
Add Worcestershire sauce.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Pour over beans; add pimento and add seasoning.
Pour into casserole. Sprinkle with crumbs or Fritos, very fine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until mixture is hot and crumbs are browned.
Serves 6.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix the egg, flour, corn meal, baking powder and crackers with the salmon. Dip in 1 egg that has been beaten. Roll in some crushed cracker crumbs. Fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.

title: pecan tassies
directions: Mix flour, margarine and cream cheese.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Make into 24 balls.
Mold into small muffin pan.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour into shells almost full. Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs and vanilla.
Add sugar until thick.
Melt butter and cocoa and add to egg mixture.
After well blended, add rest of ingredients.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken in water.
When tender, remove from water and debone.
Cook onion and potatoes where you cooked chicken breast. When onion and potatoes are done, add Veg-All and soup and cut up chicken.
Place in pie shell.
Add second pie shell for top.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: potato bacon frittata(a cross between an omelet and a quiche)
directions: Cook bacon in skillet until browned.
Remove bacon and drain on paper towels.
Pour off all but 4 tablespoons bacon fat from skillet.
Cook potatoes, onion, green pepper, pepper and 1/2 teaspoon salt in bacon fat until potatoes are tender but not soft, about 15 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in bacon.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugars and eggs.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda; add to creamed mixture.
Fold in additional ingredients.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350°.
Use ice cream scoop for large cookie (15 to 20 minutes), 1/2 scoop for smaller cookie (bake 5 minutes less).

title: neapolitan cake
directions: Generously grease and flour 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
In large mixer bowl, combine cream cheese and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Add dry cake mix and milk.
Blend until moistened.
Beat as directed on package.
Divide batter in thirds.
Mix strawberry powder with 1/3 of batter, chocolate powder with 1/3 and vanilla to 1/3.
Pour strawberry batter in pan, pour vanilla on top and chocolate over top of vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes. Cool upright in pan for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar or drizzle glaze over top.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill several hours.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Simmer vegetables in bacon until they are translucent. Add seasonings, clams, melted butter. Bring heat to high, then add chicken stock, potatoes, and light cream. Bring to a boil, then thicken with cornstarch mixture.

title: cheese soup
directions: Simmer all but milk, flour and cheese for 15 to 20 minutes, until tender.
Gradually add 1 1/2 cups milk to 2 tablespoons flour.
Add to veggies.
Cook until thick.
Add cubed Velveeta cheese.
Stir until thick.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup, egg and mayonnaise.
Add steamed broccoli, rice and cheese.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese at low speed until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter at medium speed.
Slowly beat in milk.
Fold whipped topping into mixture.
Divide evenly into the pie shells. Sprinkle each pie with the 1/4 cup finely chopped peanuts.
Freeze until firm, then cut into wedges shortly before serving.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pat into pie pan.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes at 450°, then reduce to 350° until brown.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and broccoli.
Remove from heat.
Layer chicken, broccoli and cheese in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vegetable cream cheese
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Chill 2 hours. Serve on bagels or with assorted fresh vegetables. Makes 2 1/2 cups. Prep time: 10 minutes.

title: honeyed harvest cabbage
directions: Heat oil in a large pot.
Add onion and cook until tender. Stir in honey, vinegar, caraway seed and salt.
Add cabbage and apples.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until cabbage is tender, about 1 hour.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Beat in eggs. Blend in bananas and vanilla. Add flour alternately with buttermilk. Fold in pecans.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute onion in oil until transparent.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Blend well and simmer over low heat.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in a Reynolds oven bag; place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add sugar, vinegar and soy sauce to bag.
Squeeze bag to blend in bag to coat chicken with sauce.
Arrange ingredients in an even layer.
Close bag with nylon tie.
Cut 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: venison steak
directions: Remove any of the white outer edges that may have been left on with a sharp knife.
Place steaks on a large cutting board and tenderize by beating steaks with a knife on both sides or using meat tenderizer.
Sprinkle the steaks on each side lightly with salt and pepper.
Coat steaks with flour.
Heat skillet on medium heat and add
oil.
Gently place steaks in hot oil and cook on medium heat turning as they brown.
Steaks may need to be turned more than once.
When steaks are well done and browned nicely, remove to serving platter.
Garnish with red peppers (cayenne or jalapeno-either fresh or dried).

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut the chicken meat up fine.
Salt and pepper.
Add the other ingredients; mix well.
Serve on lettuce with crackers, or make sandwiches.
Any way it is served, it is delicious.

title: spiced asparagus
directions: Drain asparagus and put in a shallow glass serving dish. Measure spices and add to other ingredients in a saucepan.
Heat slowly until sugar is completely dissolved, 5 to 10 minutes. Pour, while hot, over asparagus.
Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Drain.
Best when left for 24 hours.

title: italian delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef and onion with pepper and garlic.
Cook 10 minutes and drain.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese and place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top and bake 45 minutes.

title: master meat sauce
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Add water or tomato juice to thin, if necessary. Divide into 1 cup portions to freeze.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place string beans in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together the mushroom soup, garlic powder and sour cream with mixer and place on top of green beans.
Place Cheddar cheese on top of mixture.
Mix crumbled crackers with margarine and place on top of cheese.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: carrot soup
directions: Saute carrots in a small amount of oil.
Add chicken stock; simmer for 1 hour.
Puree, if desired.
Turn off heat.
Whip in sour cream.
Add sugar, nutmeg and salt and pepper to taste. Finish with dried tarragon.
You may need to thicken with cornstarch and water.
Makes 1/2 gallon.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In skillet cook onion, celery and garlic in shortening until tender but not brown.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer uncovered 45 minutes.
Mix cornstarch with 1 tablespoon cold water; stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Add shrimp and green pepper.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: spiced cranberry orange mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin with hot water.
Stir in cranberry sauce, cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours until thick.
Stir in orange.
Spoon into 5 cup mold. Refrigerate 4 hours until firm; unmold.
Garnish as desired.

title: no excuse bread
directions: Put ingredients into large mixing bowl; beat for 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir and knead 5 to 10 minutes, until dough stiffens and isn't sticky.
Dough should be smooth and elastic.
Cover with folded towel; let rest for 20 minutes.
Roll out and place in greased pan.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: best potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and cover with water in a saucepan; cook until tender when pricked with a fork.
Place potatoes, whole, in a bowl and refrigerate until cool.
Dice potatoes into 1-inch cubes; add other ingredients and mix well.
Serve chilled or at room temperature.

title: cherry coffee cake squares
directions: Grease jelly roll pan.
Mix together sugar and butter.
Add next 4 ingredients and mix. Spread 2/3 of the batter in pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over batter. Spoon final 1/3 of the batter on top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
While warm, drizzle glaze made of 2 cups confectioners sugar and 4 tablespoons milk.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins and dates in water until water is gone.
Then add applesauce, eggs, sweetener and oil.
Mix well.
Blend in soda and flour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
May be baked in tube pan or 3 small loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: cheese and vegetable lasagne
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Saute garlic and onions in oil until tender.
Add zucchini, mushrooms, basil, oregano and pepper. Cook and stir until tender-crisp.
Add 2 cups tomato sauce; simmer 5 minutes.
Cook 16 noodles until almost fully cooked. Drain and rinse in cold water and drain.
Pour 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Lay a flat layer of 4 noodles over sauce.
Top with half tomato vegetable mixture and sprinkle with 1 cup Mozzarella.
Repeat noodles.
Spread with Ricotta mixture.
Repeat layers.
Top with noodles, 1 1/2 cups tomato sauce and shredded Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Combine jello and water.
Dissolve and cool.
Add fruit and nuts.
Divide in half.
Pour 1/2 into an 8 x 12-inch pan. Refrigerate until set (about 1 hour).
Spread sour cream over top; cover and let it set 1 1/2 hours after topping is added.

title: family favorite
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix rest of ingredients with the ground beef.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lemon squares
directions: Blend ingredients; press into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: crunchy turkey casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with cheese and chips.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: baked turkey
directions: Wash turkey thoroughly; salt outside of turkey.
Wrap in foil. Place in a deep pan lined with foil.
Bake in a 325° oven 25 minutes for each pound of turkey.

title: orange balls
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Roll in balls.
Roll in coconut and chill.

title: harvest turkey soup
directions: Grease a 4-5 qt. saucepan and add the turkey, onion, oregano and Italian seasoning. Cook over a medium heat, stirring often until the turkey is no longer pink and the onion is soft but not brown, about 5 minutes. Add tomatoes, carrots, potato, broth, tomato juice, wine and Worcestershire sauce. Increase the heat to medium high and bring to a boil, reduce the heat, cover and simmer for 20 minutes. Add the pasta, replace the cover and cook for a further 5 minutes or until the pasta is tender. Stir in the hot pepper sauce and serve. Serves 6-8 people.

title: mary's no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Melt together first four ingredients in microwave.
(If you do not have a microwave, then boil for 1 minute.)
Pour this heated mixture over oatmeal.
Add peanut butter or coconut.
Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoon on wax paper until firm.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all this by hand and place in a greased 8-inch or 9-inch pan.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: raspberry fluff
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water and chill until partially set.
Whip partially set Jell-O then add sugar.
Whip chilled evaporated milk and fold in Jell-O mixture.
Pour in dessert glasses.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: cocoa crispies
directions: Beat all ingredients, except flour.
Beat well, then add flour.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: peanut butter muffins
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together. Cut in peanut butter and butter. Add milk and eggs, stirring just until moistened. Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 17 minutes. Brush tops with melted jelly. Dip in peanuts.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Combine melted
butter and Corn Chex; toss to coat well. Put 2 cups into 1 1/2 quart shallow baking dish.
Crush remaining Corn Chex;
set
aside.
In
skillet
brown meat and onion; drain.
Add seasonings,
mix
in sauces.
Layer half the corn, meat mixture and
cheese over Corn Chex in baking dish.
Repeat with remaining corn,
meat and cheese.
Sprinkle reserved Corn Chex crumbs over top.
Bake
at
325° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until edges are bubbly.

title: oriental fried chicken
directions: Mix orange juice and soy sauce together.
Put in a skillet with the chicken pieces.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Remove lid and let liquid cook down.
Watch carefully and turn chicken often while cooking down.

title: skillet lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bring mixture to a boil.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until rotini is tender.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: taco delight
directions: This is practically a no cook meal and great for camping. Brown ground beef with onion in large skillet, stirring occasionally.
Drain off fat.
Blend in ketchup, salt and pepper. Simmer for about 10 or 15 minutes.
Chop the lettuce, tomatoes and shred the cheese.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in heavy (cast-iron) skillet or baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over butter.
Arrange drained fruit in an attractive pattern on butter-sugar mixture.
Sprinkle with finely chopped pecans

title: dinner in a pumpkin
directions: Cut off the top of the pumpkin and thoroughly clean out seeds and pulp.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, saut onions in oil until tender.
Add meat and brown.
Add soy sauce, brown sugar, mushrooms and soup. Simmer ten minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add cooked rice and water chestnuts.
Spoon mixture into cleaned pumpkin shell.
Replace top and place entire pumpkin with filling on the baking sheet.
Bake 1 hour or vary up to 2 hours, depending on the size of your pumpkin.
Place entire pumpkin on serving plate, remove pumpkin lid and serve mixture plus the meat.

title: coca-cola salad
directions: Drain and save juice from fruits.
Add water to make 2 cups. Bring to a boil and pour over gelatin. Stir until dissolved. Cool.
Add Coke.
Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites. Stir in fruits and nuts.
Pour into lightly greased mold and chill until firm, at least 2 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and Jell-O.
Add warm water, Wesson oil, eggs (adding one at a time) and frozen strawberries.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
This makes 3 layers.

title: chex muddy buddies
directions: Pour Chex in bowl.
Set aside.
In a 1-quart microwave bowl, combine Hershey's semi-sweet chocolate chips, peanut butter and butter.
Microwave on High for 1 or 1 1/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute.
Stir in vanilla; pour chocolate mixture over cereal, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated.
Pour into Ziploc bags with powdered sugar.
Seal and shake well until coated.
Spread on wax paper.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Make filling for pumpkin pie according to the recipe on the can.
Pour into sprayed (greased) 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with dry cake mix.
Spoon melted margarine over cake mix.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans and coconut.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: brownie bites
directions: Combine first three ingredients, stirring well (dough will be sticky).
Stir in pecans.
Dust hands with powdered sugar and shape into 3/4-inch balls.	Coat balls with powdered sugar and place 2-inches apart on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: mrs. collin's tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Brown the ground beef and onion in a large skillet. Add salt and stir. Pour the beef mixture into a 9 x 13 glass baking dish. Spoon the mushroom soup over the beef mixture and cover with a layer of cheese. Top with Tater Tots and bake 25 to 30 minutes. Best when baked until Tater Tots are golden brown and cheese and meat are hot and bubbly. This is a wonderful dish for taking to large gatherings and church socials.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter.
Sift sugar and cocoa into large bowl. Pour cheese and butter into sugar.
Mix well and add nuts and vanilla.
Press into pan.
Chill.
Makes 7 pounds of fudge.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together milk and flour, stir until thick.
Add butter and 1/4 cup cold milk to dry ingredients to make paste.
Helps make less lumps.
Serve with toast.

title: apple chip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except walnuts and mix with a rotary beater approximately 5 minutes.
Fold walnuts into batter.
Pour batter into an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
To serve, sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in three 9-inch layer cake pans at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: foltz's salsa
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes; let drain at least 30 minutes.
Add chopped onions, peppers and garlic.
Add other ingredients.
Heat, but do not boil, for 10 to 20 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars; process 15 minutes in water bath or 10 minutes at 5 pounds in pressure cooker. Can in pint jars.

title: mexican kisses
directions: Blend sugar and milk.
Let come to boil.
Add butter.
Cook 5 minutes.
Do not stir.
Remove from fire.
Beat thoroughly.
Add nuts, vanilla and drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper.
If mixture hardens, set pan in hot water.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix egg, oil and milk and add to dry mixture, stirring only to moisten.
Fold in the blueberries. Makes 12 regular size muffins.
Bake at 400° in greased tins or paper lined for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples; put in buttered dish (oblong).
Sprinkle cinnamon and salt over top.
Add water.
Mix the flour, butter and sugar for topping; crumble over top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: taco dip
directions: In a large bowl, combine cream cheese and sour cream; blend well.
Spread mixture into large serving platter.
Smooth taco sauce over mixture.
Next, layer green peppers, onions and tomatoes (black olives may be added also).
Cover veggies with cheese.
Garnish with nacho chips.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sugar and pudding mix, stirring with a wire whisk to remove lumps.
Add oil, water, eggs and sour cream.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in vanilla and chocolate morsels.
Pour into a greased and floured 12-cup Bundt pan or a 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: celery seed dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients with an electric beater.
Add to coleslaw about 1 hour before serving.
May add horseradish to taste.

title: spinach salad
directions: Using a clear glass bowl, if you have one, break up spinach into it.
Add oranges, onion and walnuts; mix thoroughly.
About 1 hour before serving, add raspberry dressing.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix celery, onion and red pepper.
Mix soup, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add celery mixture.
Add chicken.
Bake in square casserole dish for 30 minutes at 350°.
Add butter to crushed chips or crackers and mix evenly.
Spread on top of baked dish and bake for 10 more minutes at 350°.

title: fresh fruit cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in Eagle Brand milk until smooth.
Stir in lemon juice and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell; chill until set.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat; add onions, if using, and let brown slightly. Blend in flour and seasonings. Gradually add water and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened slightly. Stir in broccoli. Simmer 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in Worcestershire sauce. Add cheeses and stir until melted.

title: crab bisque
directions: Marinate sherry and crabmeat overnight.
Next day, add remaining ingredients and heat.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat over to 325°. Beat eggs in large bowl. Add remaining ingredients in order with dry ingredients sifted together. Mix well. Put in 2 well greased and floured loaf pans. Bake one hour.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Pare eggplant and slice.
Beat egg with milk.
Dip the eggplant in egg, then in fine cracker crumbs.
Fry in Crisco and butter until nicely brown.
Do not fry to fast.

title: bill's country sausage
directions: Combine spices in water.
Pour over pork which has been cut to be ground.
Mix spices
thoroughly
with
pork.	Grind seasoned pork.
Ground sausage may be
stuffed into casings or fried slowly in patties.

title: cheese squares
directions: Spread 1 package rolls in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cheese mixture over top.
Cover with remaining rolls; mix 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon together.
Sprinkle on top and add chopped nuts.
Cut slashes on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Recipe from Roberts.

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and milk.
Pour over crust.
Slice bananas on top of mixture.
Spread pineapple on top.
Sprinkle cherries on top.
Cover with whipped topping, then nuts and cherries.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain off fat.
Saute onion in ground beef.
Add shredded corned beef, vinegar, ketchup and brown sugar. Cook until heated through.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
In bowl, beat sugar, margarine and egg until smooth.
Add bananas and milk.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake about 1 hour.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: rosemary potatoes
directions: Dice bacon before cooking.
Reserve drippings.
Scrub potatoes well and cut into small cubes.
Coat potatoes with drippings. Place potatoes and bacon into a baking dish.
Sprinkle rosemary and garlic powder over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover. Turn potatoes and bake for 20 minutes longer or until tender and golden brown.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in a Pam-sprayed 9 x 13-inch pan the pie filling, pineapple, cake mix, melted butter, coconut and chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add garlic salt and chili powder; mix well and let cool.
Mix together with other ingredients except Fritos and dressing.
Add Fritos and dressing just before serving.

title: red and white pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Spread mixture over sides and bottom of crust.
Cover thoroughly.
Prepare jello according to package directions.
Add fruit to crust.
Pour jello over fruit.
Chill until set.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: chili
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Add onions and garlic and saute until tender.
Add beef and brown gradually; add remaining ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Cover skillet and cook on low heat until ready to serve.
Serves 4.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Saut onion and green pepper in butter until tender. Add meat; cook until brown. Add mushrooms, chili sauce and seasonings; cook for 5 minutes and serve on buns.

title: quiche
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Sprinkle bacon, onion, and cheese in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, about 1 minute. Pour into plate.
Bake, uncovered, until knife comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: 2nd best salad dressing
directions: Beat in blender for 10 minutes.
Makes 1 quart.

title: sweet and zesty turkey burgers
directions: Mix together ground turkey burger, corn relish, Italian dressing, salt and pepper.
Form into burgers.
Place under broiler at 325°.
Cook until well done.
Good eating.

title: apple salad
directions: Bring vinegar to boil.
Add beaten eggs, sugar, flour, milk and butter.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Cool and pour over cubed apples.
Add nuts and serve.

title: cindys white chili
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook until cheese is melted and hot.

title: bacon, cheese, onion rolls
directions: Roll frozen rolls in melted margarine.
Then roll in mixture of cheese, onion and bacon bits.
Place in baking pan (which has been sprayed with Pam or substitute).
Let rise in warm place until double in size.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, mixing well.
Add soda to flour; add this to eggs, sugar and shortening, alternating with sour cream.
Add egg whites which have been beaten stiff.
Cook in loaf pan for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: hearty beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and set aside.
Cook macaroni according to directions and drain.
Mix together cottage cheese, cream cheese, sour cream, onion and green pepper.
Put half of macaroni in casserole.
Spread cheese mixture over top.
Add remaining macaroni.
Mix tomato sauce and ground beef; put on top of casserole.
Bake in a 325° to 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine graham crackers, brown sugar and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Press into bottom and halfway up sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Beat peanut butter, sugar, cream cheese, 2 tablespoons butter and vanilla until smooth.
Beat cream in separate bowl. Fold whipped cream into peanut butter mixture.
Spoon into crust. Refrigerate 6 hours.
Melt chocolate and coffee together.
Spread on top of filling.
Refrigerate until set.

title: favorite sweet potato pie
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients, from sweet potatoes through butter.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Divide equally into pie crusts.
Bake on 300 degrees for 45 to 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center of pie comes out clean.

title: microwave barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in medium glass bowl.
Cook at High for 5 minutes and at Medium-low for 8 to 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Sauce should be slightly thickened.
Use as basting sauce on chicken, ribs, hamburgers, etc.
Yields 2 cups.

title: squash fritters
directions: Cook squash in salted water until tender.
Drain and add chopped fine onion and egg; mix well.
Then add enough flour to thicken to a heavy paste.

title: fortune cookies
directions: Write fortunes on small papers.

title: creamy fudge
directions: In double boiler, melt chocolate.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Add milk, salt, vanilla and nuts.
Beat with electric beaters until smooth.
Spread into a wax paper-lined pan.
Chill 2 hours.
Turn out; peel paper off and slice.

title: pecan pesto sauce
directions: Blend at medium speed until well mixed.
Refrigerate.
Mix into cooked pasta to taste.
Additional roasted pecans may be sprinkled on top of pasta and sauce as a garnish.
This sauce may be frozen.

title: hungarian meat loaf
directions: Mix pork, onion, parsley, egg, seasoning, garlic, milk and crumbled bread in mixing bowl.
Form into loaf, roll in bread crumbs.
Bake in oven in fat.
Serve hot or cold.

title: red chili puree
directions: Put chilies in a large bowl and cover with boiling water. Allow to soak 15 minutes.
Wear gloves to rinse and prepare chilies in cold water.
While rinsing, break off stems; run finger inside chilies to find and discard any moldy areas; loosen seeds to be rinsed away.
In a blender, combine seed-free chilies, 1/4 cup hot water, garlic, salt and oregano.
Whirl at high speed until chilies are pureed.

title: fruit and nut salad
directions: Combine fruits and half the nuts in large bowl, mixing well. Mix in half the whipped topping.
Spread remaining whipped topping over top.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.

title: bourbon slush
directions: Mix all together and freeze.
Pour 7-Up over when frozen.

title: peach crunch
directions: Mix well the flour, sugar, baking powder and eggs.
Grease pan with butter. Put peaches in pan. Add the mixture.
Melt butter and pour on top.
Bake at 375° for about 35 minutes or until brown.

title: "dear abby's" pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare the pie crust.
In a large bowl, combine corn syrup, sugar, eggs, butter, salt and vanilla; mix well.
Pour filling into unbaked pie crust; sprinkle with pecan halves.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until center is set. (Toothpick inserted will come out clean when pie is "done.") Cool.
If crust or pie appears to be getting too brown, cover with foil for remaining baking time.

title: yams casserole with pecan topping
directions: In a large bowl, combine yams, egg, 3 tablespoons brown sugar, 3 tablespoons butter, orange juice and salt.
Beat until fluffy. Fold in 1/2 teaspoon pecans.
Spoon into a buttered 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with rest of pecans and sugar on top. Drizzle rest of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hummus
directions: Mince garlic in food processor.
Add garbanzos, tahini, lemon juice, water, olive oil, salt and cumin.
Blend until smooth.
Add lemon juice or water if too thick.
Transfer to serving dish and garnish with olives, chopped red onion and chopped tomato.
Use pita triangles for dipping.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Steam cabbage; let cool.
Separate each leaf to fill with mixture.
Mix together uncooked hamburger meat, cooked rice, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Fill cabbage leaf with about 2 tablespoons of mixture.
Roll up and secure with toothpick.
Lay side by side in casserole dish.
Top with pizza sauce and cheese if desired.
Cook at 325° for about 30 minutes or until done.
Serve with vegetable or salad.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: rolls
directions: Mix flour and shortening like making biscuits.
Mix all ingredients together.
Dissolve yeast in warm water, then add to flour and shortening mixture.
Mix well and let set for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Roll the dough out and cut with biscuit cutter.
Fold each one in half and brush with melted butter.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: salsa dip
directions: In microwave-safe dish, soften cream cheese, usually 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup of salsa and mix thoroughly.
Add another 1/4 cup of salsa; mix again.
Serve with chips.

title: fast cheese sticks
directions: Preheat the broiler.
In a small bowl stir together sandwich spread, Parmesan cheese and Italian seasoning.
Spread 1 teaspoon sandwich spread mixture on cut side of each bun half; bias-cut each in half lengthwise.
Arrange on a baking sheet.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: baked white potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Drain; add oleo and mix well with mixer.
Do not add milk.
In 1 1/2 to 2-quart buttered casserole, layer with 1/2 of potatoes, sour cream and cheese.
Repeat layers with cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Can be made ahead.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix meal, oil and eggs together until well blended. Add corn and milk. Blend. Add peppers, juice, onion, cheese, salt and sugar. Mix well. Pour in large iron skillet or oblong baking pan. Bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes, until nice and brown.

title: new york style macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Add vinegar and sugar, salt and pepper. Let stand 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Drain off excess liquid.
Add pepper, onion and mayo; chill.

title: girl scout s'mores(method:  stick)
directions: Toast marshmallow.
Put on graham cracker square.
Put small square of Hershey bar on top of marshmallow.
Add a "lid" of second graham cracker.

title: pepsi beef
directions: Place brisket in 9 x 13-inch pan (fat side down).
Pour Pepsi so that it comes 2/3 up on beef.
Sprinkle beef with dry soup and garlic powder.
Cover pan during baking.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
After baking, cool completely.
Cut against the grain. Reheat meat when ready to serve, either on rolls or alone.

title: jeannie's corn casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Melt butter with chopped green onions and bell pepper in microwave.
Add corn and Cheez Whiz; melt and stir.
Add rice.
Bake in baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave 10 minutes on High setting.

title: chicken salad
directions: In large bowl toss chicken, onion, celery, parsley and pickles.
Add chopped hard-cooked eggs, salt and pepper to taste and mayonnaise.
Toss again until well mixed.
For each serving, place on shredded lettuce.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with tomato and parsley.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: toffee bar crunch pie
directions: Pour butterscotch sauce onto bottom of pie crust; spread gently with back of spoon to cover evenly.
Pour 1/2 cup cold milk into bowl.
Add pudding mix; beat with whisk until well blended, about 2 minutes.
Let pudding stand until slightly thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir Cool Whip and chopped toffee bars into pudding very gently with rubber scraper until mix is all same color.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Freeze for 6 hours or overnight.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Add extra toffee pieces before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Lightly mix together beef, oats, onion, water, salt and pepper.
Shape into a loaf and place in a lightly greased shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Serves 6.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook noodles; brown sausage and onion.
Mix soups and water in pan.
Mix all together.
Put in oven at 325° until it bubbles.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Mix
spices, onions, garlic and bell pepper with ground meat. Brown
over
medium
heat.	Drain
excess
juice
after browned. Remove from heat.
Add soup, sauce, macaroni, cheese and
water. Stir
well	and bake at 450° for 1/2 hour.	Stir; bake another 1/2 hour until macaroni is done.

title: pineapple pizza
directions: Add milk to Bisquick.
Roll to 1/4-inch.
Place on pizza pan. Spread with melted oleo.
Scatter 1/2 sugar, then pineapple and rest of sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Bake 15 minutes in oven at 450°.
Cut in wedges and serve hot.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, egg yolks, oil and hot water and mix well. Add flour and pineapple to creamed mixture. Fold in beaten egg whites. Add nuts and coconut. Pour into greased tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Mix 1/2 pound confectioners sugar and 1 cup pineapple juice. Pour over hot cake in pan. Turn out when cool.

title: miami ice cooler
directions: Place orange juice and pineapple into a blender.
Pour 4 ozs. (half) of Glucerna Shake into blender.
Cover and mix for 15 to 30 seconds.
Add sweetener, extract, remaining Glucerna Shake, frozen strawberries and ice cubes.
Cover and blend on high until smooth. Serve immediately.

title: aunt doris' salmon mousse, updated(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In a small saucepan, mix water and gelatin.
Let stand 1 minute.
Place over medium heat until gelatin is completely dissolved, stirring constantly.
Pour into blender or Cuisinart. Add lemon juice and onion; cover and mix.
Add mayonnaise, dill, paprika and drained salmon.
Pour yogurt over all.
Cover and mix until smooth.

title: round steak
directions: Mix ingredients except rice or noodles.
Cook all day in crock-pot.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: Place all ingredients in blender and blend until mixed well and smooth.
Cook in double boiler or over medium heat until thick.
This is very good on Pig in Blankets or baked ham.
Hot!

title: english olive appetizers
directions: Combine all ingredients except muffins; mix well.
Spread mixture on muffin halves; cut each in four wedges.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: escargot stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse and drain escargot; pat dry.
Wipe mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop stems fine.
Place mushroom caps on a baking sheet; place escargot in caps.

title: caramel popcorn(healthy)
directions: Pop the popcorn.
Mix rest of ingredients and pour over popcorn.
Bake for 1 hour at 200°.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pierce pie crust and place apples in pie crust.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples. Cut butter and 1/3 cup sugar together.
Add flour, sprinkle over apples.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: mint pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine Eagle Brand, peppermint extract and, if desired, food coloring.
Fold in whipped cream.
Turn into crust.
Cover and freeze 6 hours or until firm.
Garnish as desired.
Freeze leftover.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream eggs and sugar.
Add oil and blend well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts and apples.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: old-fashioned fried pies
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and lard. Add milk. Mix baking powder with flour. Mix all together. Let stand overnight in refrigerator. Roll out and cut around saucer. Wet edges with water; put in fruit and fold. Use damp fork around edges. Deep-fry in Crisco until brown and drain on paper towel. DO NOT STACK.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 225°.
Line a cookie sheet with lightly greased aluminum foil.
In a clean bowl, beat egg whites until peaks are stiff.
Add sugar slowly and continue to beat, adding vanilla and the cream of tartar and beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in chocolate chips and drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: light cream cheese frosting
directions: In a serving bowl, combine yogurt, honey, lemon juice and cinnamon into a smooth dressing.
Add carrots, raisins and pineapple to dressing and stir gently, but thoroughly, until salad is uniform.
Cover and chill for a minimum of 15 minutes.
Toss again before serving and drain liquid, if desired.

title: mennonite corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake in 9-inch square pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese. Pour one half of the batter in large iron skillet which has been greased and heated; sprinkle cheese over batter. Add rest of batter and bake corn bread at 400° until brown.

title: hobo cake
directions: Combine raisins, water and soda.
Let stand overnight.
Add remaining ingredients.
Put in 3 greased and floured 1-pound coffee cans.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn upside-down and shake out.

title: chocolate peanut butter delight
directions: Combine sugar,	cocoa,	butter	and milk in a saucepan. Bring to a
boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; quickly add oatmeal, peanut
butter
and
vanilla.
Stir
and
drop on wax paper or pour out in pan.

title: lime jello and cottage cheese
directions: Dissolve jello into boiling water and pineapple juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Beat until frothy.
Fold in pineapple, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: fudge pies
directions: Melt butter in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat, then dump all other ingredients in.
Pour into 2 small unbaked pie shells or one (9 to 10-inch) pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Blend cream cheese, worcestershire sauce, accent and onion together.
Add 1/2 of chopped dried beef and form into a ball. Press remaining beef on outside.

title: rocky road cake
directions: Put water, butter and oil in pan. Bring to a boil. Pour over dry ingredients; beat until smooth. Add eggs and milk; mix well. Bake in greased 11 x 16 pan 18 minutes at 400°.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Shape loaf into baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: walnut ice cream topping
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan; mix well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat to low and cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let cool; store in an airtight container in refrigerator.
Serve over ice cream. Yields 1 1/2 cups.
May substitute pecans for walnuts.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and cook in moderate oven 350° until sets, approximately 35 minutes or longer.

title: funnel cakes
directions: For batter, in a large bowl, stir eggs, milk and brown sugar. In another bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture.
Beat with a rotary beater until smooth. In an 8-inch skillet, heat cooking oil to 360°.
Hold a funnel with 1/2-inch spout covering the bottom with your finger.
Pour about 1/2 cup of the batter into the funnel.
Remove your finger and carefully release the batter into the hot oil, starting at the center of the skillet and moving the funnel in a circular motion to form a spiral.
Cook batter about 2 1/2 minutes or until golden brown.
Using 2 wide metal spatulas, carefully turn the funnel cake.
Cook about 1 minute more or until golden.
Remove the cake from the skillet and drain on paper towels.
Repeat with the remaining batter.
If desired, sprinkle funnel cakes with powdered sugar or drizzle with Caramel Sauce.

title: low-fat cream of broccoli soup
directions: Saute onions in margarine or broth until clear.
Add flour; stir until light brown.
Add broth and stir well.
Add broccoli and carrots; let cook 25 minutes.
Drain vegetables and save broth.
Puree 1/2 of the vegetable mixture.
Add pureed vegetable back to broth and whisk in to blend.
Add milk while heating on low heat.
Add vegetables that were not pureed.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: the potatoes
directions: Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Layer with hash brown patties.
Mix remaining ingredients and layer with potatoes. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: mahogany chops
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper; grill over medium hot coals, basting with molasses (or ketchup) and teriyaki sauce.

title: chicken in barbecue sauce
directions: Brown cut up chicken in a small amount of cooking oil.
Remove chicken, then saute onion and green pepper until soft.

title: quick swiss dip
directions: Blend all the ingredients together.
Put into a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with crackers and/or vegetables.

title: parsley and bacon sandwiches
directions: Combine parsley, bacon, mayo and Worcestershire.
Mix garlic powder and butter and spread this on bread.
Spread parsley mixture on this at one end and roll slices up.
Wrap in wax paper or Saran Wrap and twist ends closed.
Refrigerate several hours. Can be made several days ahead.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs at high speed 5 minutes.
Slowly beat in sugar.
Stir in pumpkin.
Stir together flour, baking powder, salt, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Grease and flour a paper-lined 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread mixture evenly in pan and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken in sour cream
directions: Line casserole with aluminum foil.
Place chicken in dish and coat each piece with mixture of all other ingredients except crumbs.
Cover tightly.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Next morning, sprinkle completely with crumbs.
Return to refrigerator. Remove one hour before cooking.
Bake in 350° oven for one hour and fifteen minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: In small saucepan, cook garlic in olive oil.
Combine in a large bowl with soup, water and vinegar.
Chill for several hours. Add chopped vegetables just before serving.
Add croutons for garnish.
Serve cold.
Makes 6 1/2 cups.

title: grits casserole
directions: Add salt to water; bring to boil.
Add grits slowly, keeping water at a brisk boil.
Cover and cook slowly for about 1 hour or until grits are soft, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Stir in butter and milk, then cheese, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Cool to lukewarm.
Beat in eggs and pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mom's lemon coconut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream the margarine and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Blend in 1 cup flour, oatmeal, salt and soda.
Press into bottom and sides of a greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: good pink punch
directions: Select large, firm berries of deep red color.
Wash and remove the hulls.
Weigh the berries and add an equal weight of sugar. Mix the berries with the sugar, using a wooden spoon and lifting the berries gently to avoid crushing them.
Place the berries and sugar at once over the fire.
Bring to boiling point as soon as possible and boil rapidly for 8 minutes.
Seal in clean jars.
By this method, the berries keep their shape and the finished product has a clear rich color.

title: light rye bread
directions: Stir the flours together and set aside.
Combine the molasses, water and yeast.
Add 8 ounces (225 grams) of the flour mixture. Stir vigorously for 3 minutes.
Cover the bowl and set aside to rise until doubled and very bubbly, approximately 1 hour.
Stir the milk powder, caraway seed, salt and butter into mixture.
Gradually add remaining flour to mixture.
When dough is too stiff to mix by hand, transfer the dough to a mixer fitted with a dough hook. Continue adding flour until dough is stiff but slightly tacky. Knead for 5 minutes on low speed.

title: white sangria
directions: Get some celery and put peanut butter in it.

title: tropical fruit pops
directions: Cut banana in 4 pieces.
Combine banana, pineapple, strawberries, yogurt and honey in a blender or food processor. Whirl until smooth.
Fill 6 ounce paper drinking cups or plastic popholders with mixture.
Place a wooden stick in each.
Freeze. Makes 8 pops.

title: rainbow shrimp salad
directions: Combine shrimp, rice, celery, olives, pepper and onion in large bowl.
Cover and chill.
Before serving, stir together salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Toss with shrimp mixture.
Spoon shrimp onto lettuce.
Garnish with tomato wedges.
Serve with French dressing and lemon wedges.

title: quick crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, plus 1/2 can of water from each can.
Let simmer for about 15 minutes.
Add crawfish tails and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix
together by hand and pinch off enough to roll into a ball the size of a medium marble.
Bake	on ungreased cookie sheet about 7 minutes at 375°.
This recipe
makes a "slew" of tasty bites.
If you wish, you may use mild sausage.

title: swiss steak
directions: Pound flour, salt and pepper into steak.
Brown steak in oil on both sides; bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 4 servings.

title: frozen grapes
directions: Wash grapes.
Put in a flat tray and put it in the freezer for 1 hour.
Remove from the freezer.
Roll in sugar. Serve frozen.

title: apple marmalade
directions: Quarter unpeeled orange.
Remove seeds.
Slice orange to thick slices.
In a large kettle combine first three ingredients and 2 cups water.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Add sugar and bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking and stirring until thickened and clear.
Remove from heat and add Certo.
Skim off the foam. Pour into hot, sterile jars and seal.

title: walnut crunch
directions: Combine sugar, walnuts and egg. Spread thinly on greased jelly roll pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 18 to 20 minutes at 350°. Cool to room temperature and crush.
Sprinkle half of crumbs in bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Combine pudding mix, sour cream and milk; beat on low speed of electric mixer 1 to 2 minutes.
Fold in sliced bananas.
Spoon over crumbs in pan; top with remaining crumbs.
Chill several hours.
Cut in squares.
Serves 9.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine. Add nuts.
Press into a 9-inch spring-form pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool. Gradually add lemon juice to Marshmallow Creme, mixing until well blended.
Stir in strawberries.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour over crumb crust and freeze.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: dried beef cheeseball
directions: Finely chop the onions and dried beef.
Mix cream cheese, and add 1-2 Tbsp. worchester sauce to taste.
Sprinkle in some dried beef.
In a soup bowl, firmly pack the bottom and 1/2 side of the bowl with the dried beef.
Add the mixture.
Refrigerate.
When ready to serve, get a plate to serve the cheeseball on.
Turn the bowl upside down and gently have the cheeseball come on to the plate.
Serve with crackers of your choice.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed and add pineapple, strawberries and bananas.
Pour 1/2 of contents in pan and congeal.
Next, spread sour cream over this and pour rest of Jell-O over top.
Let congeal and serve.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Place chicken in casserole.
Arrange broccoli over chicken. Mix mayonnaise, milk, soup, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over chicken.
Spread buttered crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until mixture bubbles.

title: meat stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut top but don't peel eggplant; remove pulp leaving 1/2 inch shell.
Parboil shell 3 minutes.
Combine chopped pulp with meat, crumbs and seasonings.
Stuff the eggplant with meat mixture. Replace top with toothpicks.
Brown green pepper, celery, onion and garlic.
Add tomatoes.
Season and simmer for 15 minutes. Pour sauce over and around eggplant in baking dish.
Bake at 350° in oven for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk and dash of pepper.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion, soup mixture and cheese.
Dot top with butter.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover, bake 15 minutes more or until done. Makes about 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: crepes
directions: Just combine all ingredients and beat well.
Fry in thin cakes in hot grease just until brown on both sides.
Fill with your favorite filling.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

title: toffee ice cream pie
directions: Line bottom and sides of buttered 9-inch pie plate with wafers.
Spoon ice cream into wafer shell, sprinkle 1/2 cup of chopped candy between ice cream layers.
Freeze for at least 2 hours.

title: microwave pineapple kiwi fruit jam
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine kiwi fruit, sugar, lime juice and pineapple.
Microwave on High for 11 1/2 to 16 minutes or until mixture comes to full rolling boil, stirring every 2 minutes. Stir in liquid pectin.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture comes to full rolling boil; continue to boil for 1 minute.
Skim foam, stir in food color.
Spoon into 5 clean, hot 8-ounce jars; screw lids on firmly.
Cool several hours.
Store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks or in freezer up to 3 months.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: golden shrimp shells
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In medium skillet over medium-high heat, stir-fry shrimp, garlic, parsley and hot pepper sauce in oil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Remove dough from can in rolled sections; do not unroll.
Cut each roll into 12 slices.
Place, cut side down, 1 inch apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Press half of each dough slice to flatten.
Place about 1 teaspoon shrimp mixture (or 1 large shrimp) on flattened half of each slice.
Fold remaining half of dough over shrimp; do not seal dough.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 13 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with cocktail sauce.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: zesty marinated salad
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in an 8-inch square baking dish. Pour dressing over vegetables, tossing to coat.
Cover and chill 8 hours.
Drain, reserving dressing.
Arrange vegetables over lettuce.
Serve with reserved dressing.

title: miracle cheese cake(no cooking)
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Cream together cheese, sugar and lemon juice.
Add gelatin and blend well.
Fold in stiffly whipped Milnot.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and melted butter together.
Pack 2/3 of mixture on bottom and sides of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Add filling and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: banana cake
directions: Sift together Softasilk, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt. Add shortening, 1/2 of the buttermilk and bananas.
Beat for 2 minutes. Add remaining liquid with the eggs.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or two 9-inch layer pans. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: In double boiler or heavy saucepan, put milk and marshmallows. Cook on low heat until marshmallows melt.
Remove from heat and add Hershey bars.
Stir until candy melts.
Cool well and fold Cool Whip into chocolate mixture and pour into crust (cold). Refrigerate.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Blend soups with half and half.
Heat and add crab meat, shrimp and the sherry.
Serve immediately.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Butter bottom of roasting pan.
Coat pork chops with flour and fry until brown.
Put chops in roasting pan; put apple pie filling and cinnamon on top of chops.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: banana jumbles
directions: Mash bananas with a fork; measure one cup.
Beat together the sugar, peanut butter and margarine; beat in egg and mashed bananas.
Combine oats, flour, baking powder and salt; stir into banana mixture until well combined.
Stir in raisins.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls onto a cookie sheet coated with a cooking spray.
Shape cookies with the back of a spoon.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 14 minutes until lightly browned.
Makes 18 cookies.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine cream cheese and peanut butter. Beat at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Gradually and gently add whipped topping and confectioners sugar.
Continue beating until smooth.
Spoon filling into pie crust.
Freeze 8 hours or overnight.

title: three layer coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix, water, oil and eggs.
Beat 300 strokes by hand, then add nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Bake in 3 round pans at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all together and freeze.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Note:
You can use the cocoa if you wish, but this will overwhelm
the
spices, so you will need to choose whether you wish to use the cocoa.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes.
Put on onions and cheese and bake for 5 minutes uncovered.

title: june's squash-a-roni
directions: In boiling water, simmer squash for 5 minutes.
Drain and return to pan.
Add onions and cheese.
Cover and set aside. Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to directions on box.
Add to squash mixture.
Butter a 13 x 9-inch pan and pour in mixture. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes until lightly brown.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender.
Drain and rinse.
In a skillet melt butter and saute onions.
Add liquid from mushrooms and stir in soup, milk, mushrooms, green pepper, meat, cheese, and spices. Put spaghetti in buttered 9 x 13 baking dish.
Pour sauce over top.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: haroset
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: yum yum layer cake
directions: Whip egg whites. Set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks.
Mix soda and water with buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour to the creamed mixture.
Blend in beaten egg whites and flavoring. Cook at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Makes 3 layers or a 9 x 13-inch sheet cake.

title: cheese crab puffs
directions: Split 6 English muffins to make 12 pieces.
Mix remaining five ingredients.
Spread on muffins.
Chill for 1 hour.
Cut each muffin into six "pie" pieces.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt. Set aside.
In small pan, combine butter, sugar and water.
Bring just to a boil and remove from heat.
Add 6 ounces of chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until smooth and melted.
Transfer to large bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Gradually blend in flour mixture.
Stir in remaining chocolate chips.
Cooking time:
Greased 9-inch square pan 30 minutes or greased oblong pan 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix sugar and cracker crumbs.
Heat butter and peanut butter over low heat until melted; stir in crumb mixture.
Press in ungreased baking pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat together.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: great burgers
directions: In a large bowl beat eggs, then add tomato sauce.
Stir in bread crumbs, onions and garlic.
Crumble in the beef, add salt and pepper. Add cheese or pickles if desired.
Great to fry or to cook on the grill in the summer.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, soup, sour cream and poppy seed.
Top with crushed crackers and melted margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sicilian sausage soup
directions: Cook sausage (without casings) on high; add onion and cook. Add tomatoes, chicken broth and basil; bring to boil; and add orzo and salt and pepper to taste.
Lower heat and simmer 20 minutes. Drain off any excess fat.

title: can't fail quick fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Never stir while cooking.
Cook 5 minutes after candy starts to boil.
Remove from heat.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and vanilla.
Beat until glossy and creamy. Pour on platter.
Cut when cool.
Can add 1/2 cup peanut butter or 1/2 cup pecans.

title: un-mexican haystack
directions: Combine thoroughly the first 8 ingredients.
Stir in ham. Place a tortilla on a plate and spread with mixture.
Repeat layers, ending with mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts and parsley. Cover and refrigerate.
Cut into wedges or cubes and insert decorative toothpick.
May be prepared
1 day ahead if wrapped tightly.

title: french market soup
directions: Sort and wash bean mix; place in Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans; soak overnight.
Drain beans; add 2 quarts water, ham hock, salt and pepper.
Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours until beans are tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Remove ham hock, take meat from bone, chop and return to soup. Yields 2 1/2 quarts.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with oleo.
Add salt, brown sugar and molasses.
Add rye flour and white flour and knead.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: microwave apples
directions: Cut up 5 apples.
Put them in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar and then cinnamon.
Cook in microwave for 7 to 10 minutes.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Cook noodles in boiling salt water until tender, drain.
Place corned beef, cheese, soup, milk and onions in large mixing bowl.
Add noodles.
Place in greased 2 quart casserole dish.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes.
Serves 8-10.

title: sea stix
directions: Melt butter in microwave; add garlic, water and sea stix. Place all in microwavable dish.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Turn stix over and repeat until stix are heated.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Crumble sausage over pie shell. Crumble cheese over sausage. Lightly beat eggs and add remaining ingredients to it. Then pour over pie. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chili con carne
directions: In a heavy Dutch oven, slowly brown beef with onion and garlic until meat is cooked through.
Add tomatoes with juice, tomato sauce, beef broth, chili powder, cumin, salt, oregano and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer beef mixture, covered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Add cooked or canned beans and simmer 30 minutes longer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Add crumbled mincemeat to boiling water and boil for 1 1/2 minutes, being sure there are no lumps.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine yeast and water.
When yeast bubbles, add butter and beaten egg.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Cover and let rise until double in bulk.
Punch down, make into rolls.
Place in greased pan, let rise again until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 20-25 minutes.
Can also be done in a bread maker.
Just follow manufacturer directions.

title: zucchini-pineapple bread
directions: Add the dry ingredients to all the other items.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for about 1 hour.

title: garlic cheese grits casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2 quart baking dish.
Bring water and salt to a boil in a large saucepan.
Slowly stir in grits.
Cover, reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheeses and butter until melted.
Add eggs and Worcestershire sauce; blend well.
Pour mixture into prepared dish.
Sprinkle with paprika as desired. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Cook for 10 minutes before serving.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: Cook all ingredients together, except flour and 1/4 cup water. Cook until meat is tender.
Make a thickening of flour and 1/4 cup water; add thickening.
Pour over the hot noodles to serve. Serves 6.

title: jeanette's cookies
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift again with soda and salt.
Cream butter with both sugars.
Beat eggs into butter-sugar mixture. Add vanilla and mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add nuts, oats and chips; mix thoroughly.
Drop on greased cookie sheet (about 1 tablespoon each cookie) and bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°, until light brown.
Makes about 6 dozen delicious cookies!

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Sift all ingredients together.
Store in airtight container in cupboard.

title: cow pies
directions: In a double boiler over simmering water, melt chocolate chips and shortening, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat and stir in raisins and almonds.
Drop by tablespoons onto tinfoil/wax paper.
Cool.
Yield: About 2 dozen.

title: demarvelous chicken
directions: Roll chicken in lemon juice, then in flour.
Coat with melted butter.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place in baking dish and cover.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until tender and brown.

title: bohemian buns
directions: Let rise once and shape into buns. Brush buns with beaten egg and sprinkle with poppy seed or sesame seed. Bake at 375° 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fun cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Combine flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together butter or shortening and sugars until light and fluffy; beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture slowly.
Stir in M&M's candies and nuts.
Drop heaping teaspoonfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes until browned.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet; place on wire cooling racks.
Makes about 5 dozen cookies.

title: five-cheese lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan, cook lasagna noodles, boiling for 4 to 5 minutes; drain and set aside.
In a medium-sized skillet, cook ground beef or meatball mixture, ground sausage, chopped onion and minced garlic until meat is brown and vegetables are tender; drain off fat.
Set aside.
Combine the cubed cream cheese and light cream or milk with the parsley, basil, oregano, salt and pepper in a medium saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir in dry white wine.
Gradually add the shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese is nearly melted; remove from heat.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: In skillet, saute onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms, olives and oregano.
Add ground beef.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: baked artichoke dip
directions: Combine ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with toast points or Melba rounds.

title: taco casserole
directions: Place corn chips in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown hamburg and onion. Add beans, tomato sauce and taco sauce to hamburg. Spread this mixture over chips.
On top of the meat mixture, place the tomatoes (thinly sliced) and lettuce. Cover with cheese. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: country breakfast or supper
directions: Cook potatoes, green pepper and onion in oleo until lightly browned.
Season to taste.
Break eggs over potato mixture.
Cover and cook on low heat until eggs are done.
Sprinkle cheese over eggs, cover and cook until cheese melts.
Makes 4 servings.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the flour. Add the 4 cups flour
gradually to the mixture until the dough is the right consistency.
Do
not make the dough too dry.
Roll out thin and cut
in desired shapes. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes. Sprinkle sugar on top of each tea cake. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: hot artichoke spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Spoon into a lightly greased 3 cup casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serve with assorted crackers.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: ruth ann's potato or macaroni salad dressing
directions: Cook all ingredients together.
Stir constantly.
Cool.
Add 1 cup salad dressing to cooked macaroni or potatoes.

title: stuffed celery sticks
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients and fill center of celery.

title: colored pasta
directions: You will also need container with lid and cookie sheet.

title: fresh peach crumble
directions: In a mixing bowl, mix 1/2 cup of the granulated sugar, the brown sugar, the flour and nutmeg.
Using a pastry blender, cut in butter until it resembles coarse cornmeal.
Sprinkle with 2 to 3 tablespoons of the water; stir with fork until water is absorbed. It will make a crumbly dough.
Pat half the mixture into the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake in a 450° oven for 10 minutes.

title: grill pork chop sauce
directions: Combine all in blender.

title: sweet potato supreme
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with a mixer until smooth. Pour into a greased 11 x 7 x 1 1/2 inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine butter and next 4 ingredients, stirring with a fork.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Yields 8 servings.

title: crumb-coated chicken
directions: In small bowl, beat together egg, butter and salt.
In shallow dish, place crumbs.
Coat chicken with crumbs, then egg mixture and crumbs again.
In 8-inch square dish, arrange chicken with meatiest pieces near edges of dish.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave at High 12 to 14 minutes.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn after half the cooking time.
Makes 2 to 3 servings.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Dip pieces of cut up and skinned chicken in evaporated milk, then in corn flake crumbs, which have been mixed with 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon garlic powder.
Put in buttered baking dish and turn once to coat both sides.
Sprinkle with black pepper and bake at 350° about 1 hour or until well done.

title: beef and broccoli
directions: Cut beef into strips 1-inch long, 1/4-inch thick and 1/2-inch wide; set aside.
In a small cup, stir together stock, cornstarch, soy sauce and sherry; set aside.
In a heavy skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil until very hot.
Add broccoli, then toss and stir for 2 minutes.
Cover and cook for 2 minutes more over medium heat; remove to side dish.
Return skillet to high heat and add remaining 2 tablespoons oil and heat until smoking hot.
Add beef and cook 2 minutes.
Stir in stock mixture and add along with broccoli.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Cook onion and garlic in oil in large saucepan or Dutch oven until tender, about 6 minutes.
Add broth, tomatoes, picante sauce and basil.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in tortellini; simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir in green peppers.
Continue to simmer until tortellini is tender (3 to 5 minutes).
Makes about 9 cups of soup.
May add lean, cooked and drained ground beef or leftover roast beef, chipped into bite size pieces.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix cornbread according to directions. Add creamed corn and Mexicorn. Mix well.

title: ambrosia fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts.
Pull meat off bone in chunks and line casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers and mix with melted margarine. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Do not cover.

title: mix in the pan carrot cake
directions: In an 8-inch pan with fork mix well flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, baking powder and nutmeg.
Add remaining ingredients to mixture and mix briskly with fork until blended. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until pick comes out clean and cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Cool, frost or sprinkle with 10x sugar.

title: chili
directions: In large pot or Dutch oven, fry up onion and green pepper. Next, brown the ground beef.
When brown, add salt, red pepper, chili powder and garlic salt.
Stir to blend seasonings.
Add chili beans (rinsed in colander under running water).
Then add tomatoes, tomato soup, tomato sauce and sugar.
Add water.
Stir occasionally.
Cook very slowly for 3 hours.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place softened cream cheese, lemon juice, Tabasco sauce and crab liquid in bowl and mix with mixer until creamy.
Fold in minced onions, horseradish and crab meat. Put into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Garnish with chopped chives.
Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable soup
directions: In a large 4-quart kettle place soup bones and 4 quarts of water until boiling.
Turn flame down and boil slowly for 2 hours. Chop all vegetables into bite-size pieces and place in kettle; boil until vegetables are tender, about 1/2 hour before serving.
Add 1/2 cup barley to soup and cook for 1/2 hour more.
Serve with corn bread.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chocolate peanut oatmeal cookies
directions: Put sugar, cocoa, milk and oleo in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir until smooth.
