Add oats; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto foil or wax paper and cool.

title: jelly dot cookies
directions: Mix ingredients separately and then mix together and roll into balls and chill.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.
Indent center with jelly.
Bake 3 to 5 minutes more. (Grape jelly is Chris' favorite.)

title: microwave idaho potato supreme
directions: In a 1-quart microwave-safe casserole, combine broccoli, mushrooms, green onion, red pepper and 2 tablespoons water. Micro-cook, covered, on 100% power (High) 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Drain well.
Add turkey ham.
Cook, covered, on High 2 to 3 minutes or until heated through.
Stir together yogurt, milk, cornstarch, mustard and nutmeg.
Add to broccoli mixture.
Cook, covered, on High 2 to 4 minutes or until mixture is thickened, stirring every 30 seconds.
Spoon over hot potatoes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries in
water.
Soak gelatin in hot water. Add sugar to gelatin
while
hot.
Add rest of ingredients and mix all together while hot.

title: asparagus congealed salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water, vinegar and Worcestershire.
Chill until thickened.
Meanwhile, line 4-cup straight sided mold with asparagus spears.
Trim to height of mold.
Dice remaining asparagus, pimiento and onion into gelatin.
Spoon into mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.

title: apple pizza
directions: For crust:
Mix 2 cups flour and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt, then add oil and milk.
Mix until dough is smooth, then spread out on a large pizza pan.
Cover with peeled, cored and sliced apples, arranged in circles.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Sprinkle over apples.
Cover with streusel made by mixing 3/4 cup flour, 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 pound butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: graham cracker bars
directions: Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Boil together 1/2 cup milk, egg, 1 cup sugar and 1 stick oleo for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add graham cracker crumbs, nuts and coconut.
Spread over whole graham crackers in the pan.
Top with whole graham crackers and press firmly.
Spread with mixture of powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons milk, 3/4 stick oleo and lemon juice.
Set in refrigerator until used.

title: cream of broccoli soup(serves 4)
directions: Bring water to boil in medium saucepan over medium heat. Dissolve bouillon cube in boiling water.
Add the broccoli; cook 5 to 6 minutes, until bright green and fork-tender.
In a small saucepan, warm evaporated milk over low heat, just until bubbles form around the edge.
Remove pan from heat.

title: fried rice
directions: Prepare 2 cups of instant rice.
In a bowl, beat eggs.
In a wok or wide frying pan, fry bacon until done.
Add onions and stir fry about one minute.
Add eggs; cook and stir until set.
Add rice and soy sauce; stir through.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Put caramels and 1/3 cup evaporated milk in a saucepan and melt on low.
Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Combine cake mix, oleo, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and pecans.
Stir until dough holds together.
Press 1/2 of dough mix in pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle chocolate pieces over baked crust.
Spread caramel mix over this.
If chocolate melts and smears, it's okay.
Put reserved dough over this.
Crumble with hands.
Flatten pieces and lay over mixture in pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly and refrigerate 30 minutes to set caramels.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Mix together the cooled potatoes and all other ingredients. Spread in greased pan.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for an additional 15 minutes.

title: ann's orange cookies
directions: Add sugar, shortening, baking powder, flour and eggs.
Add soda and buttermilk.
Add to flour mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar and flour; add to egg mixture.
Add milk and butter and heat until hot, not boiling.
Place in partly browned pie crust and finish baking in 350° oven.
Pie is done when you can insert kitchen knife in and it comes out smooth.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: Cook and stir ground beef and onion in 4-quart Dutch oven until meat is light brown; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover; simmer, stirring occasionally, until spaghetti is tender, about 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: spaghetti and meat sauce
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients except spaghetti and cheese.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, adding more water if necessary.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Serve with meat sauce and Parmesan cheese.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: zesty broccoli spears
directions: Trim off large leaves of broccoli and remove tough ends of lower stalks. Wash broccoli thoroughly and cut into spears.
Cook broccoli in a small amount of boiling water for 10 to 12 minutes or just until tender. Drain. Place broccoli in a serving dish.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Stir up and make into balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: all-bran rolls
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine first 4 ingredients, then add remaining ingredients.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Pour out on floured board; knead slightly.
Make into rolls and place in greased pans.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip bites
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a cookie sheet.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan. Bake at 425° for about 45 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Heat milk, oil, and flour.
Mix well when sauce begins to thicken.
Add tuna and eggs.
Put in casserole.
Put in a layer of 3/4 of the potato chips.
Sprinkle the rest over the top and bake for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Work
shortening into flour until mealy. Dissolve yeast in
a little
lukewarm
water.
Add to flour with the rest of ingredients.
Mix
well. Roll out to about 1/2-inch thickness. Cut with
biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. Makes about 7 dozen.

title: good anytime fruit bread
directions: Mix dates, nuts, soda & water.	Set aside to cool.
Cream sugar, egg & butter.
Stir in the flour & salt.
Stir in the date mixture, plus the well drained pineapple and cherries.
Bake in greased bread pan at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.	Makes 1 loaf.

title: onion cake
directions: Cook bacon crisp; drain skillet.
Cook onions in oleo. Combine sour cream, flour, salt and eggs in a bowl.
Stir in bacon and onions.
Pat 4 crescent rolls in pan, stretching as needed, pinching to seal.
Pour mixture over dough.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour; add milk and chicken broth. Cook and stir until thickens.
Cook and stir 1 minute; add snipped parsley, lemon juice, grated onion, salt and dash each of nutmeg and pepper.
Cool.
Then add chopped, cooked chicken, salt and pepper to taste.
Chill thoroughly.
With wet hands, shape mixture into 8 balls.

Roll in cup of fine crumbs (crackers or dry bread); lightly shape balls into cones, dip in mixture of 1 beaten egg and water and roll in crumbs and fry in deep hot fat for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes. Drain and serve.
Serves 4.

title: microwave p-nut brittle
directions: Combine in a large bowl sugar and Karo syrup.
Cook for 4 minutes on High.
Remove and stir. Add nuts and salt.
Return to microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Remove and add 1 teaspoon of butter.
Stir.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla and stir.
Return to microwave.
Cook 1 minute on High.
Remove and add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Pour into greased cookie sheet.

title: corn cakes
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add fat and egg.
Pour boiling water over mixture and mix.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drop by tablespoon on lightly greased skillet.
Brown on one side, turn and brown. Serve hot with butter.

title: cashew casserole
directions: Saute the celery, onion and mushrooms in the oil for a few minutes.
(Do not brown.)
Add the liquid to the mushroom soup and stir until smooth.
Combine all ingredients an blend thoroughly. Pour into a greased casserole and bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: slowly deviled beef
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot; stir to mix.
Cover and cook about 10 hours on low or 4 to 5 hours on High.
Serve with rice or noodles.
(Can also be baked in casserole for 2 to 2 1/2 hours in 325° oven.)

title: chicken with walnut sauce
directions: Cut chicken in pieces; fry to light brown in a saucepan with 1/2 the butter; add chopped onions and fry together a little longer.
Add a little water and seasoning.
Cover and simmer. When chicken is tender, mix flour with milk and pour over chicken. Cook 5 minutes more.
Stir until sauce is very smooth.
Add chopped walnuts and 1 tablespoon butter.
Simmer 5 minutes and serve.
Garnish with boiled potatoes sprinkled with melted butter and chopped parsley.

title: recipe for a long marriage
directions: Stir all ingredients together and mix well.
Let stand for 80+ years.

title: biscuit coffee cake
directions: Place nuts and cherries in round cake pan.
Melt butter.
Roll biscuits in butter then in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Lay biscuits on side in pan.
Dribble pancake syrup over biscuits. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Pour salt, alum, oil and food coloring into boiling water and stir.
Add flour; stir well, then knead until well blended. Mixture will be hot.
Store in plastic bag when cool.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and turn into 9-inch unbaked pie shell. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until set.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Mix the first five ingredients and put in baking dish.
Place chicken on top of this mixture and sprinkle it with Lipton onion soup mix.
Bake, covered with aluminum foil, at 350° for 2 hours.

title: lasagna pizza supreme
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Reserve 1 tablespoon sauce mix; add remaining mix, tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water to beef.
Simmer for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: delicious deer steak
directions: Heat butter and Crisco in skillet. Beat eggs well; add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Dip steak into eggs, then into the flour and fry until crust is formed and meat is done.

title: bayou baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pour ingredients into a small casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes.
This is better when just baked.
Do not reheat.
Serves 2-4.

title: scalloped eggplant
directions: Peel eggplant; cut into 1-inch cubes.
Boil in salted water until tender.
Drain well and mash.
Add egg, milk, onion and 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Mix and pour into a greased 1-quart baking dish.
Top with the cheese.
Spread 1/2 cup Ritz cracker crumbs over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: olive sauce
directions: Heat oil in small saucepan.
Add garlic, but do not brown. Add olives and parsley; saute for 2 to 3 minutes or until olives are heated.
Immediately toss with hot pasta or cool and add to cold pasta of your choice.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: country chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in large baking dish. Empty chicken soup, mushroom soup, 2 cans of water in boiler and heat.
Pour over chicken and cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is good served over rice.

title: qualla blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add pineapple and pie filling.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and chill until set. Cream together cream cheese, sour cream and sugar.
Spread over chilled Jell-O.
Chopped nuts may be added.

title: 5 bean hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Brown bacon; drain off fat and break up into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients in a large pan. Bake in 350°
oven 1 1/2 hours.

title: smoked sausage casserole
directions: Wash and cube potatoes. Cut smoked sausage into pieces.
Add to potatoes and mix. Heat cheese soup and milk in pan.
Pour over potato mixture.
Bake at 425° until potatoes are tender.
Add Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake in oven until cheese is melted.

title: rice oven dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in iron pot.
Cover with foil and bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Onion tops and parsley may be added at last 15 minutes for more distinct flavor.

title: quick gumbo style beef sausage soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes, or until okra is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in pepper sauce. Place 1/2 cup rice into 4 individual soup bowls.
Ladle equal amounts of soup into bowls.

title: bread pudding
directions: Core and peel apples.
Cut apples into small chunks.
Beat eggs then add remaining ingredients.
Combine with bread pieces. Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: island potato salad
directions: Toss together salad ingredients.
Then add seasoning.

title: veg-all italian soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Stir in onions and cabbage.
Heat 2 minutes.
Add water, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in Veg-All, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: southwestern salad
directions: In a serving bowl or platter, toss chips, lettuce, cheese, beans, tomato, salad dressing, onions and chiles. Top with avocado.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot cross buns
directions: In a large bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups flour, sugar, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and butter until hot to touch (125° to 130°).
Gradually add to dry ingredients. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add eggs and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
With spoon, stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Knead on lightly floured surface until smooth and elastic, about 6 to 8 minutes. Cover and let rest on board 20 minutes (10 minutes for RapidRise yeast). *

title: pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir together first 5 ingredients until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 325°.

title: green bean stew
directions: Clean and peel potatoes; cut green beans into about 1/2-inch slices.
Cut potatoes and kielbasa into squares.
Chop onion and saute in margarine.
Add potatoes, green beans and sausage.
Pour water over it; add broth, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer at medium heat for about 20 to 30 minutes.
Then add marjoram and thyme.
If needed, add salt and pepper to your taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: peanut brittle(microwave high setting)
directions: Stir
together peanuts, sugar,	syrup
and
salt
in
a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place in oven
and
cook
for
to 8 minutes, stirring well after
4 minutes.
After 8 minutes, add butter and vanilla, blending
well.
Return
to
oven and cook for 1 to 2 minutes.
Peanuts will be lightly browned and syrup very hot.
Remove from oven
and
add soda.
Gently stir until light and foamy.	Pour
mixture
onto
lightly
greased cookie sheet. Let cool for 1/2 to 1 hour.
Break in small pieces and store in airtight container.

title: fruit sauce on ham
directions: Melt jelly in saucepan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend. Heat and serve hot over ham.

title: eclair squares
directions: Make pudding and set aside.
Combine water and butter in saucepan; simmer.
Add flour and mix 1 minute.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Spread this mixture in a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 425°, until lightly browned.
Press out bubbles after it cools.

title: fish creole(low calorie recipe)
directions: Rinse fish and pat dry with paper towels.
In 9 x 12-inch dish, arrange in dish with the thickest pieces to the outside edge of dish.
In 1-quart glass measure, stir together tomato sauce, mushrooms, green peppers, celery, water, minced onion and bouillon.
Pour evenly over fish.
Cover tightly.
Bake in 350° oven for about 30 to 40 minutes, until fish is opaque.

title: monkey bread
directions: Mix sugar and brown sugar with cinnamon.
Coat rolls broken in half with mixture.
Place in Bundt pan.
Mix left over sugar mixture with melted butter and pour on top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes, then turn out onto plate while still warm.

title: chocolate crackles
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, stir until well mixed.
Stir in pecans.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar. Place 1 1/2 inches apart on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies will be soft when removed from oven.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add to hash browns, sour cream and chicken soup.
Mix well.
Put in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken and cut in pieces.
Saute onion in butter.
Add chilies and simmer. Add soup, chicken and half and half.
Lay tortillas in the bottom of the dish.
Layer chicken mixture, tortillas, chicken mixture, then cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: petite cherry cheesecakes
directions: Put vanilla wafer in the bottom of 12 to? cupcake foil papers, flat side down.
Cream together cream cheese, lemon juice, sugar and flavoring.
Add eggs and mix well. Pour mixture over the vanilla wafers in the foil cupcake papers.
Fill each 3/4 full. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool and top with cherry pie filling.

title: plum cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar and spices in large mixing bowl. Make a nest in mixture; add oil, eggs and baby food.
Mix well. Add nuts.
Cook in tube or Bundt pan that has been well-greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
While cake is still warm, use 1 cup powdered sugar and juice from large lemon to make glaze. Pour on top of cake.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs alternately, two at a time, with flour and baking powder.
Stir in vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 325° for 1 hour.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 300°, then turn temperature up to 325° and bake for remainder of the hour.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice.
Dice apples (do not peel). Add apples to mayonnaise and lemon juice; stir to coat well.
Add sliced celery, walnuts and raisins; toss until mixed well.
Serve in bowl or arranged on lettuce.

title: christmas coffee cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add 1 cup sugar and the eggs.
Beat well.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Mix well.
Beat in flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Pour half of the batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Mix the remaining 1/4 cup sugar, cinnamon and nuts for the topping.
Sprinkle 3/4ths of the topping over batter in pan.
Add remaining batter; sprinkle with remaining topping mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Do not open oven during baking.
Yield:

title: old fashioned granny dumplings
directions: Boil chicken and make broth.
Remove chicken and season the broth. Sift flour into a bowl and make a hole in the middle.
Beat eggs and cooled broth together.
Add to flour and mix with your hands.
Knead dough until smooth.
Roll the dough out to about 1/4 inch thickness.
Slice dough into desired size pieces and drop in boiling chicken broth.
Cook until tender. Remove chicken form the bones and add to dumplings, reheat and serve.

title: mildred sloan's hamburger chop suey
directions: Saute beef, celery and onion; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Stir in 2/3 can of chow mein noodles; pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 30 minutes, then, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle balance of noodles on top; bake 15 minutes more.
Let rest 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: oyster pie
directions: Melt margarine and mix with broken saltines.
Heat oysters in juice until edges curl.
Use slotted spoon and dip out oysters and layer with crackers.
Use liquid from oysters and add enough milk to make 3 1/2 cups liquid.
Pour over oysters and crackers.
Bake at 350° till it bubbles.

title: lil's sausage soup
directions: In large pot, heat oil.
Add sausage, breaking up with a fork.
Cook until no longer pink.
Remove sausage to a bowl.
Add carrots and celery; cook until almost tender. Add onions and cook for a minute or so more.
Add the sausage and the chicken broth, then the potatoes and cook until vegetables are tender.
Then add beans and cook for another 10 minutes.
Serve with crusty bread and sprinkle Romano cheese on top of soup.
6-8 servings.

title: nut bars
directions: Blend eggs and sugar.
Stir in dry ingredients and walnuts. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: old fashioned sugar pie(makes 2)
directions: Mix the ingredients and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells and bake until golden brown (about 30 to 35 minutes at 350°).

title: mushrooms marsala
directions: Wash mushrooms in warm, salted water and pat dry.
Cut off stems; leave caps whole.
Heat butter in skillet and saute mushrooms until lightly browned (still firm).
Add lemon juice, Marsala wine, salt, pepper and parsley.
Serve.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Mix together.
Reserve 1 cup.
Press remaining in 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes.

title: turkey and dressing
directions: Turkey:
Remove giblets and neck from turkey.
Wash turkey. Spread melted shortening on turkey and then shake on salt.
Cover; leave some air.
Add 3 cups water and cook in a 325° preheated oven for 20 to 25 minutes per pound.
After about 1 hour, uncover to brown.
(Cook giblets in pan with turkey.)

title: chocolate syrup brownies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and eggs until very creamy and well blended. Add salt. Stir in flour until well blended. Add chocolate syrup, vanilla and chopped nuts.

Pour mixture into well-greased and lightly floured 9-inch square pan. Smooth top. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until stick inserted near center comes out clean. Cool pan on wire rack, but loosen cake at edges. Cut into squares. Garnish with walnuts or dust with powdered sugar.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 32 squares.

title: cole slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, onion, green pepper and sugar in a bowl.
Boil vinegar, oil, mustard, salt, pepper and celery seed for 3 minutes. Pour over vegetables while hot.
Cool and refrigerate overnight. Will keep for 30 days.

title: tweedy's delicious potato dish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pizza
directions: Skin and cut breasts in 1-inch pieces.
Unroll crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Press dough into lightly oiled cookie sheet, sealing perforations well.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat. Add chicken, onion, green pepper, mushrooms and olives.
Cook, stirring 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken is fork-tender and almost all liquid is absorbed.

title: raisin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in saucepan.
Sift together sugar and flour; mix with eggs.
Add milk and raisins; cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into pre-cooked (lightly browned) deep dish pie shell and put small pie shell on top.
Pat with butter, and sprinkle of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake until brown.

title: baked hash brown potatoes
directions: Mix the ingredients together in dish and top with 1/2 cup Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for about 1 1/2 hours.
(Use a 9 x 12-inch dish.)

title: doughnuts
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and nutmeg; add sugar. Mix to a light soft dough with beaten egg, milk, melted shortening and vanilla.
Turn onto floured board; roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter and cook about 3 minutes in deep, hot fat (360° to 375°), turning as they rise to top of fat.
Drain on paper and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: frozen coconut pie
directions: Beat the cream cheese and sugar in a large bowl.
Gradually add milk; beat until smooth.
Stir in coconut, whipped topping and vanilla.
Spoon into crust.
Freeze for 4 hours or until firm. Garnish with toasted coconut and maraschino cherries, if desired. Let stand at room temperature for 15 minutes, or until pie can be cut easily.
Store leftover pie in freezer.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender before measuring.
Drain.
Add butter, salt, pepper and milk.
Mix well.
Add beaten eggs, onion, cheese and crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: brickle
directions: You will also need 1 large baking sheet (lined with aluminum foil); should fit 1 sleeve of saltine crackers lined.
Do not overlap (8 down and 5 across).

title: dump cake
directions: Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Dump all ingredients in large oblong pan.
Cook until done.
Takes about 30 minutes.

title: breakfast bars
directions: Combine.
Press into Pam-sprayed 10 x 15-inch baking pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Cut into squares and chill.

title: oatmeal-apple bars
directions: Sift flour,
baking
soda
and nutmeg onto waxed paper. Beat softened
butter,
sugars
and
egg
in a large bowl with electric mixer
at
high speed until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Stir
in
flour mixture alternately with applesauce, blending well to make a thick batter.
Stir in oats and dates.

title: gourmet pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops.
Heat fat in skillet until you have 2 tablespoons.
Remove trimmings.
Coat chops in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown.
Put chops in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch dish. Combine soup, water, ginger and rosemary.
Pour over chops. Sprinkle with 1/2 of onions.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with rest of onions and bake for 10 minutes.
Put meat on platter.
Blend sour cream into sauce in pan.
Mix and pass sauce with meat.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat sugar and eggs.
Heat milk and butter.
Add milk, flour and baking powder to eggs and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350°.

title: anise cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients and place onto a greased cookie sheet by heaping teaspoonful. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift the flour three times to fluff and place in a bowl.
Add the baking powder, salt, sugar and cream of tartar.
Cut in the shortening until the size of lima beans.
Stir in the milk.
Do not handle too much.
Turn onto a bread board, knead gently to finish mixing.
Pat out till 1 inch thick.
Cut 8 biscuits.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: minnesota wild rice soup
directions: Saute rice in oil just to lightly toast.
Add water and bring to boil.
Continue cooking until almost done (the rice will start to open up).
Do not overcook.
Drain and reserve rice and stock. Melt butter; add onion and cook slowly until transparent.
Add flour and mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, about 10 minutes.
(Do not let mixture brown.)
Gradually add the two stocks.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Add rice and half and half.
Do not let soup come to boil.
Simmer about 20 minutes.

title: my own cottage pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Add tomato sauce.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Pile mashed potatoes on top of mixture and simmer until sauce starts to cook up sides of pan.

title: roll-ups
directions: *Can use 2 packages of frozen, chopped broccoli instead of spinach.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased foil.
Place in oven.
Turn off oven and leave closed overnight.
Store in airtight containers.

title: english muffin loaves
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar, salt and soda. Heat liquids until very warm (120° to 130°). Add to dry mixture; beat well. Stir in rest of flour to make a stiff batter. Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch pans, that have been greased. Cover; let rise in warm place for 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and margarine.
Add milk, eggs and rest of ingredients, folding in pecans.
Pour in pie crust.
Put in cold oven, then turn on to 300°.
Cook 1 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk, water, oil and egg.
Beat well. Fry in hot oil until brown and done in middle.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in glass bowl; microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add peanuts.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir in baking soda.
Quickly spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool.
Break into pieces.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients together except cashews; form into one or two balls (whichever you prefer).
Roll each in chopped cashews.
Chill and serve.

title: make-ahead mexican casserole
directions: Do not dilute the soups, use as is.

title: pecan-orange rice
directions: Heat chicken broth and orange juice to boiling.
Add rice, cover and wait 5 minutes.
Toss with pecans.

title: better than guess what(large party cake; serves 20)
directions: Mix cake according to directions on package.
Bake in large pan (13 x 9-inches).
While cake is baking, mix in saucepan: pineapple, sugar, cornstarch and butter.
Bring all to boiling. When cake is done, remove from pan to platter.
Spread pineapple mixture over cake while cake is hot.
Let cake cool.
Slice bananas lengthwise.
Spread over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas.
Next, spread coconut evenly.
Last, spread or spoon pudding.
Decorate with walnuts and maraschino cherries.

title: scrumptious vegetable casserole
directions: Mix butter, oregano, basil and sage with the crackers (save a little of the crackers for the top).
Make two layers of the crumbs, vegetables, tomatoes and cheese.
Sprinkle the remaining cracker mix over the top. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Remove cover and cook for another 15 minutes.

title: baked beef stew
directions: Place meat in oven roaster.
Put in vegetables.
Pour juice over meat and vegetables.
Sprinkle tapioca over top.
Bake at 350° for 5 hours.

title: better than sex cake(it is)
directions: Bake cake by box directions.
Combine in saucepan the pineapple and sugar.
Cook until sugar is dissolved.
Poke holes all over cooked cake with large plastic spoon handle.
Pour pineapple over cooled cake.
Mix pudding by directions on box. Spread over cake; spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle top with nuts, if desired.
Cake gets better the longer it stays in refrigerator.

title: best ever rump roast
directions: In summer, I like fresh herbs best!

title: green salad vinaigrette dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; top with cover and blend well.
Cover and chill dressing thoroughly.
Serve over salad greens.

title: apple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot cider.
Add salt and shredded apples. Whip chilled milk with electric mixer at high speed until stiff. Fold into Jell-O mixture; pour into 4 to 6 individual molds or cups.
Unmold; serve at once on lettuce leaves.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Pour the apple juice concentrate into a saucepan.
Sprinkle with gelatin and allow to soften for several minutes.
Meanwhile, finely chop blueberries, 1 cup at a time.
Add lemon juice, spices and 2 cups of chopped berries to gelatin; heat over medium-low until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from the heat.
Stir in remaining berries and mix well.
Pour into jars or plastic container.
Store in the refrigerator up to 3 weeks.
Yields 4 cups.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Mix together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla. Mix together dry ingredients. Slowly mix dry ingredients into first mixture. Fold in zucchini. Add chocolate chips and pecans, if desired. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 3 loaves.

title: becky's banana cake
directions: Slice bananas in a large electric mixer bowl and beat until well mashed.
Add remaining ingredients and blend, then beat at medium speed for two minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured, fluted tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes for the tube pan, 50 to 55 minutes for the oblong.

title: jo jo potatoes
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients.
Use 7 potatoes (peeled or unpeeled), quartered lengthwise.
Dredge slices in mixture.
Place in Pyrex dish.
Cut margarine over potatoes.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: jelly roll
directions: Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with greased waxed paper.
Turn up edges to make proper size in pan.
Beat eggs and sugar together.
Add water and beat all at once.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture, beating just until smooth (don't overbeat).
Pour into prepared pan and bake in a preheated oven at 375° for approximately 20 minutes or just until done (don't overbake).
When done, loosen edges and immediately turn upside down on a towel sprinkled with powdered sugar.
Remove paper quickly by pulling off.
Spread with jelly and roll up.
Wrap in the towel and cool approximately 1/2 hour.

title: water chestnut canapes
directions: Cut bacon in half crosswise.
Wrap 1/2 slice bacon around chestnut and secure with toothpick.
Place on foil lined cookie sheet and bake in 400° oven until bacon is done, pouring off excess grease during baking.
Thoroughly combine sugar and catsup (this will be grainy).
When bacon is done, dip each chestnuts into sauce and return to cookie sheet.
Place under broiler until sauce bubbles and browns slightly.
Watch carefully!
The sauce burns easily.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat and onion. Add sauces on low heat for 15 minutes. Line bottom of casserole dish with Doritos. Add meat, sauce, then top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken
directions: In a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, arrange breast pieces.
Top with a slice of Swiss cheese.
In small bowl, combine soup and water. Mix.
Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions.
Pour soup over chicken and cheese.
Arrange prepared stuffing over top. Bake for an hour at 350°.

title: strawberry chiffon pie
directions: Crush strawberries (about 1 1/4 cups).
Add 1/2 cup of sugar. Let stand 30 minutes.
Soften gelatin in water; dissolve over low heat.
Cool.
Add strawberries, lemon juice and dash of salt. Chill, stirring occasionally, until partially set.
Beat egg whites to soft peaks; gradually add 1/4 cup of sugar, beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold in strawberry mixture, then whipped cream.
Chill until mixture mounds.
Pile into graham cracker shell.
Chill until firm, about 5 hours.
Trim with whipped cream.

title: southwestern rice with beef
directions: In medium saucepan, combine rice with water; bring to boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Stir in beef, corn and green chiles; heat through. Evenly spread 1/2 cup rice mixture onto each tortilla, then roll and place on serving plate.
Makes 8 tortillas.

title: gwen's hamburger casserole
directions: Add butter, celery and onion to water and boil until vegetables are tender.
In a large bowl mix stuffing mix and poultry seasoning; mix in broth with celery and onion.
Pat beef lightly onto bottom of baking dish; sprinkle with salt and pepper. Layer stuffing mixture over meat, and cover all with the undiluted soup and the mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to sugar mixture.
Add nuts and mix well. Spoon into two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttery cookies
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening, using electric mixer.

title: italian beef sandwiches
directions: Cook roast with garlic and onion.
Then drain and pull apart. Add 1 or 2 packages of dressing.
Serve on kaiser rolls, cut in half, or hamburger buns.

title: easy rocky road
directions: Butter 8-inch square pan.
In a large microwave-safe bowl, place chocolate chips, butter and shortening.
Microwave on High 1 to 1 1/2 minutes or until chocolate chips are melted and mixture is smooth, when stirred.
Add marshmallows and nuts; blend well. Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Cover; refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Yields 16.

title: artichoke spinach dip
directions: In food processor, blend artichokes, romano cheese, garlic and parmesan cheese for about 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Artichokes and cheese should be minced, but should not be pasty.
In a mixing bowl, add drained spinach, cream, sour cream, mozzarella. Stir well.
Spoon into mixing bowl mixture from food processor.
Blend all ingredients.
Mixture should have a medium thick consistency. Spray an oven proof shallow serving dish.

Pour artichoke mixture into baking dish and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 350 degrees. Artichoke dip should be a little bubbly and cheese melted through. Remove from oven and serve with your favorite heated tortilla chips, sour cream and salsa and enjoy.

title: fresh berry tiramisu
directions: Mix berries with 2 tablespoons each of sugar and liqueur. Whisk 1/3 cup of Amaretto with egg yolks.
Stir in cheese.
Beat egg whites with mixer until soft peaks form.
Continue beating and gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, until whites will hold soft peaks.
Stir 1/4 of whites into cheese.
Then fold in remainder.

title: spanish rice
directions: Cook hamburger, green pepper and onion until done.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add rice and simmer for 15 minutes longer.

title: cottage cheese fruit
directions: Mix quickly and serve cool.

title: delicious lime pie
directions: Blend limeade and condensed milk together. Fold in Cool Whip. Pour into 2 graham cracker pie crusts. Chill.
Top with Cool Whip and chill again.
(If you want to reduce calories, use lite cool whip and fat free sweetened condensed milk.) This pie is so easy, yet so delicious.

title: raisin cake
directions: Mix and set aside raisin juice and soda.
Mix eggs, sugar, shortening, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add raisin juice.
Then add flour, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in greased and floured Bundt pan.
No icing needed.

title: bonnie's potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
When potatoes are done, peel and slice into bowl.
Peel eggs and set aside.
Season potatoes with salt and pepper.
Generously pour dressing over potatoes; mix together and refrigerate.
Before serving, add onion and just enough mayonnaise to bind all together.
Garnish with eggs, sliced thinly.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crusts from bread; spread with margarine.
Place in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Cook sausage until browned, stirring to crumble; drain well.
Spoon over bread slices.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard (optional); mix well.
Pour over cheese.
Cover; chill overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: chicken dinner
directions: Spread uncooked rice in a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish. Mix and heat soups, milk and onion soup mix.
Place chicken on rice and pour soup mixture over it.
Cover and bake at 325° for about 2 hours.

title: chocolate logs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients into peanut butter.
Pour melted butter over mixture and blend well.
Shape dough into 2 x 1/2-inch logs and chill.
Melt paraffin and chocolate chips together over boiling water.
Dip logs into chocolate mixture and put on waxed paper.

title: french vanilla cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except glaze in a large bowl; beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes and pulls away from sides of pan; do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes; remove and cool on rack.
Top with Sugar Glaze.

title: mimere's meat pie(la tourtiere)
directions: Choose pork butt as lean as possible.
Boil the bones in 1-quart of boiling salted water for 20 minutes and set this liquid aside.
In large heavy skillet, saute onion in butter and oil until golden.
Add ground pork and about 1 cup of liquid from the bones. Simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add as much liquid as necessary to prevent sticking.
Simmer as slowly as possible.
Boil and mash potatoes.
Add a little salt, pepper and butter.
Drain cooked pork mixture and add to potatoes.
Divide well mixed pie filling between the 2 pie bottoms (9 or 10-inch pie plates).
Sprinkle cracker or bread crumbs on pies to absorb the fat.
Add top crusts.
Slash to let steam escape.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then 350° until crusts are nicely brown.
(You may freeze before baking, then thaw before baking, at 350° for 1 hour or browned nicely.)

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix flour and nuts.
Melt oleo and mix into flour mixture. Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.
Cream sugar and cream cheese together.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread evenly over the crust and chill.
Mix puddings, add milk and beat until it thickens.
Spread over cream cheese layer and chill.
Spread Cool Whip over top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together. Combine flour, salt, soda, powder and spices. Add and mix well with first ingredients. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Yields 2 large loaves.

title: never fail dill pickles
directions: Place garlic, dill, sugar, salt and vinegar in sterilized jar. (Place ingredients in jar in order.)
Pack cucumbers in jar. Fill with cold water.
Put in boiling water bath.
Boil for 5 minutes (no longer). Take jars out and turn upside down for 24 hours.
Do not use pressure canner.

title: layered tortillas
directions: Place 3 tortillas in pan on bottom to cover.
Fry and drain beef or turkey, onion and taco seasoning.
Place on top of tortillas.
Add 3 more tortillas.
Top with beans and cheese.
Add 3 more tortillas.
Top with can of nacho soup.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool, add lettuce, sour cream, tomatoes and hot peppers.

title: benedictine spread
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Add a few drops food coloring; stir well.
Spread cheese mixture on bread slices.
Serve as finger sandwiches.

title: dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package, using a large mixer bowl.
(The milk called for on the envelope is not part of the 1 1/4 cups milk listed.)
Add 1 1/4 cups milk and the pudding mix.
Blend; then beat at high speed for 2 minutes, scraping bowl occasionally.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill at least 4 hours.

title: chow mein cookies(haystacks)
directions: Melt butterscotch and peanut butter on medium heat.
Heat until melted; stir in chow mein noodles and nuts.
Spoon on wax paper. Let stand until dry.

title: heavenly hash cake
directions: Melt butter.
Mix eggs, sugar, butter, vanilla, flour and nuts.
Bake in a greased 9 x 13 inch pan at 350° for 35 minutes. Five minutes before cake is done, have icing ready.
Top cake with marshmallows as soon as it comes out of the oven.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over the first 4 ingredients; stir. Let stand until cool.
Add yeast.
Add flour and knead.
Let rise until double in bulk in a warm place.
Knead and make into 2 large loaves; let rise again until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
(This also makes about 20 large rolls.)

title: cherry tarts
directions: Mix sugar and flour together; add to cherries.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.
Take off heat and add 1 tablespoon butter and 1/4 teaspoon almond extract.
Let cool.
Fill medium sized tart shells and top with whipped cream.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill several hours before serving.
Serves 12.

title: white trash
directions: Mix together chips and oil. Drizzle over cereal mixture. Chill and break apart.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, squash and vanilla.
Cream together.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to creamed mixture and mix thoroughly.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in 325° oven for about 50 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Cook 50 minutes at 350°.

title: cocktail wieners
directions: Saute onion and green peppers in margarine until tender.
Add soup, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and vinegar. Cook on medium for 5 to 10 minutes.
Chop wieners into 1-inch pieces and drop into mixture.
Bake in oven for 20 minutes at 300°.

title: grandma's homemade biscuits
directions: Set the oven at 425°. Sift dry ingredients in a bowl. Cut shortening in. Pour in milk. Turn out on floured pastry board and knead. Pat or roll dough in 1/2 thickness wanted.
Cut biscuits. Place 1/2 inch apart on an unoiled pan. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: calzone
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Roll out bread dough to size of cookie sheet. Put a layer of ham, and cheese and spot with pepperoni. Fold up length-wise 3 inches. Then fold in edges, and complete folding long end. Brush with beaten egg. Make 3 small slits on top. On Cookie sheet bake for 30 min.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix first four ingredients in a separate bowl. Beat egg, vinegar and water slightly.
Combine two mixtures.
Makes 2 double crust 10-inch pies.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix dry pistachio pudding in medium to large bowl with crushed pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows.
Mix well and chill before serving.
Refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cream cheese, Cracker Barrel, onion, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well.
Chill.
Shape into a ball; roll in pecans.

title: salsa
directions: Mix ingredients in food processor.
Use less jalapeno peppers for a mild salsa.

title: wild rice mushroom soup
directions: Saute carrots and onion in butter or margarine until tender/crisp, then add broth, rice mix (including seasoning package) and water.
Add mushrooms, including juice, and chicken or turkey.
Simmer until rice is cooked.
You may need to add water.
A quick hearty soup!
Yield:
4 servings.

title: beau monde dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill several hours.
Makes an excellent bread dip or for chips.

title: crispix mix
directions: Be careful in the selection; do not choose one too ripe or old.
Best results are obtained if reared in a Christian atmosphere.
Some insist in keeping him in a pickle, others in hot water.
Such treatment, however, keeps sour, hard and sometimes bitter.
Many housewives found that poor varieties can be rendered sweet and tender.
Garnish with patience, sweeten with a smile and flavor with a kiss to taste.
Wrap him in charity.
Place over warm fire of devotion.
Serve with peaches and cream.
Prepared as such, will keep for years.

title: pumpkin bread(don't wait until halloween to try this bread recipe.)
directions: In a large bowl, mix shortening, sugar and cream.
Add eggs, water and pumpkin; mix well.
Blend in remaining ingredients and place in a lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: bacon-tomato bagel melt
directions: *Can be different kinds of fruit such as raisins, orange-flavored cranraisins, banana chips, apricots, dates or whatever you like.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter; add chocolate chips.
Keep over low heat until chips are melted.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour into uncooked pie shells (makes 2 pies).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no mix meat loaf
directions: Shape meat into a loaf 3 inches high on sheet of foil. Sprinkle dry mix over top of meat.
Cover with the can of soup. Seal in foil.
Bake in shallow pan for 1 hour and 20 minutes at 350°.

title: dedra's vegetable beef soup
directions: In a large pot, add water, beef base, tomato paste and beef. Cook these ingredients for 30 minutes over high heat.
Next add the processed onions, bell peppers and celery.
Cook for another 30 minutes or until beef becomes tender.
Lower heat to medium temperature. Add diced potatoes, sliced carrots, celery, shredded cabbage and parsley flakes.
Cook for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Add broccoli, cauliflower and squash. Allow to cook for 10 minutes. Remove from heat.
Serve hot with crackers or cornbread. This soup may be frozen.

title: irish cream
directions: Blend all together until smooth.
Store tightly covered. Keeps in refrigerator for a month.
Shake before using.

title: swiss chicken
directions: Lay chicken on bottom of greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top of chicken.
Mix together soup and 1/4 cup wine; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle stuffing on top.
Pour butter and other 1/4 cup wine over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: dump salad
directions: Mix it all together in a bowl and serve.

title: refrigerator sandwich cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream butter; gradually add sugars and beat until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg yolk and vanilla.
Gradually add flour.
Chill for ease in handling.
Form into 2 rolls, each 7-inches long and 1 1/2-inches diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper and chill several hours.
Cut into 1/8-inch slices and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool.
Put 2 cookies together with vanilla frosting; place dollop of frosting on top of sandwich and top with pecan half.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Brown peppers, celery and onions in butter. Add soup, water, mushrooms and olives. Add chicken and precooked noodles, then grated cheese. Put in casserole dish and top with more cheese. Bake 30 minutes until cheese is melted.

title: beef-a-la-lu-lu
directions: Roast beef.
Discard all fat.
Slice thinly or shave.
Place in a large skillet that has been sprayed with Pam.
Add all remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Cover and simmer over low heat until vegetables are soft.
Place chunks of cheese on top to melt slightly.
Serve on hoagie buns for lunch or over rice for dinner.

title: grass soup(polish kvas)
directions: Wash and chop lettuce.
Put into container.
Put 4 tablespoons (to be deducted from amount in ingredients) of vinegar, 12 ice cubes and 1/2 cup water over lettuce.
Chill (if time permits, overnight).
Combine lettuce, cucumbers and onions.
Add water until it starts showing through the vegetables as you press on vegetables with a spoon.
Add sour cream.
Add salt and vinegar. Amounts listed are what I used.
You may want to start with less and add to taste.

title: coffee pot punch
directions: In bottom of pot, place water, cranberry juice and pineapple juice.
In basket, put sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Perk through full cycle.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Cream the cream cheese and margarine together using electric mixer.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well and frost cake.

title: strawberry crowns
directions: Combine ingredients in the order given.
Spoon into muffin liners and freeze until firm (can do days ahead).
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 16 medium size crowns.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli for 1 to 2 minutes.
Blend soup, sour cream, onion, carrot, flour, salt and pepper.
Add to broccoli and mix well.
Add buttered crumbs to top.
Bake at 350° uncovered 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork steak
directions: Bake pork steak at 350° for 15 minutes.
Turn down to 300°. Bake 15 minutes more.
Turn meat and drain.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
To make the sauce, combine sugar and flour and blend with egg.
Stir into reserved juices. Cook and stir over moderate heat until thickened.
Arrange pineapple chunks in a buttered shallow casserole.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top, then add cheese.
Spoon on sauce and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.
This dish is good served with ham.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Brown ground beef and stir in spaghetti sauce.
Cook 3 minutes.
In a medium bowl, stir sour cream, 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese and egg.
Stir in spaghetti.
Place in a pan and sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Spread meat mixture over entire surface.
Cover with foil and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove foil.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: wieners in sauce
directions: Mix together in a crock-pot.

title: peach (jam or preserves) cake
directions: Sift together soda and plain flour.
Cream margarine, sugar and egg yolks.
Add flour and soda mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Add preserves and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Bake in 2 layers 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Toast almonds in butter.
Mix all ingredients except Rice Krispies.
Top with Rice Krispies.
Bake until hot and bubbly and cereal is browned.
Bake at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon and apples together lightly.
Pour into pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust.
Flute. Sprinkle with sugar.
Vent.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes (test apples with fork).

title: holiday salad
directions: Dissolve jello and candies in boiling water; stir in remaining ingredients except for cream cheese and milk.
Pour into square (approximately 6 x 6-inch) dish.
Chill until firm.
Beat cream cheese with milk to spreading consistency.
Spread over top. Chill and cut into squares.

title: oil pie crust
directions: Mix oil and water together.
Mix with flour.
Press in pie pan.
May tear, but is easily repaired.
Makes a flaky crust.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 pie crusts. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour to 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: christmas 3 layer salad
directions: Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in 1 1/4 cup boiling water and add frozen strawberries.
Let this layer harden in refrigerator before adding second layer, made by dissolving lemon jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water, adding cream cheese and mixing until soft, then adding nuts.
When this layer has set, add the third, made by dissolving lime Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups boiling water and adding crushed pineapple.
Use a 9-inch square glass pan.

title: waffles
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk which has been mixed with egg yolks.
Add melted butter.
Beat until all lumps have disappeared and you have a smooth creamy mixture.
Fold in beaten egg whites.

title: sour cream chicken enchiladas
directions: One hour ahead:
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, spread 1 cup sour cream and set aside.
In 2-quart saucepan, flake chicken; add 1/2 cup sour cream, mushrooms, green chilies, onion flakes, chili powder, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Cook on low, stirring occasionally, just until heated.
Heat oven to 450°.
In 8-inch skillet on medium-high heat in about 1/2-inch of oil, fry 1 tortilla a few seconds on each side until soft.
Along center of tortilla, spread 1/4 cup chicken and fold sides over filling and place, seam side down in pan.
Repeat until all tortillas are used. Spread enchiladas with remaining sour cream and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 8 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: macaroni supper salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except eggs; mix well.
Garnish with eggs.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger. Tear tortillas into pieces. Use 1/2 to line bottom of casserole. Layer with 1/2 of hamburger.

title: refrigerator all-bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over Post Bran and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Add Kellogg's Bran, add dry ingredients.
Fold in soaked Post Bran.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Combine flour, butter and cream cheese well.
Pinch small amounts of dough off and pat out on wax paper the size of silver dollar or larger.
Place in small tart muffin tin and flute edges.

title: puppy chow
directions: In small saucepan, boil first 3 ingredients for 2 minutes. In large bowl, pour this mixture over cereal and nuts.
Mix well with buttered spatula.
Immediately spread mixture onto wax paper and let harden for 1 hour.
Store in airtight containers or Ziploc baggies.

title: easy chicken salad(number of servings: 2)
directions: Combine all ingredients except chicken and salad greens in large bowl. Mix well. Stir in chicken. Refrigerate at least 1 hour. Serve on salad greens.

title: lemon lust
directions: Combine
the
flour,
margarine
and
pecans.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Use hands to press dough evenly. Bake 15 minutes in a 375° oven.
Cool until warm.

title: lettuce with grilled pine nuts
directions: Combine vinegar, mustard, oil, salt and pepper.
Arrange salad in bowl.
Add chopped chives.
When ready to serve, melt butter over low heat.
Add pine nuts; stir well to avoid burning the nuts.
Pour on salad.
Add dressing; serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: holiday candy
directions: Mix peanuts, cereal and marshmallows.
Melt cocoa and peanut butter. Pour over dry ingredients.
Pour in buttered dish.
Let chill.

title: baked apple squares
directions: Beat together sugar and eggs.
Add the sifted flour with cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Add the oil and vanilla.
Fold in chopped nuts and the 2 cups of apples.
Bake in greased pan, 9 x 13-inch at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with mixture of sugar and cinnamon right after baking.
Good this way.
Delicious with ice cream or cream over it.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain well. (Spinach should be undercooked). Mix spinach with sour cream and onion soup.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: 1st Layer: Mix and pat into pan the flour, butter and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Let cool.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, make an even layer of the lettuce.
Mix onion and celery.
Sprinkle over lettuce.
Sprinkle water chestnuts, then unthawed peas for next layer.
Spread mayonnaise evenly over top and sprinkle with sugar.
Refrigerate overnight. The next day, layer remaining ingredients over mayonnaise.

title: mozzarella chicken
directions: Lightly salt and pepper chicken.
Dip chicken in egg batter. Roll heavily in Italian bread crumbs.
Brown in butter on low. Cover and fry until tender.
Dip heated spaghetti sauce over chicken while still in frypan (about 1 to 2 tablespoons).
Melt a couple thick slices of Mozzarella cheese on top of sauced chicken. Serve in a casserole dish layered:
1) spaghetti, pressed in dish, 2) sauce heated on top and 3) next, arrange chicken closely.
Serve like a casserole with spatula.
Great with marinated vegetables in Ranch dressing and bread sticks.

title: onion blossoms
directions: Leaving the root end intact, peel the outer skin of the onions. Cut a small slice off the top.
Starting at the top of the onions and on one side, make a cut downward toward the root end, stopping 1/2-inch in from the bottom.
Make additional cuts 1/8-inch from first until there are cuts completely across top of onions.
Turn the onions a quarter turn so the slices are horizontal to you. Repeat cuts 1/8-inch apart from each other until there is a checkerboard pattern across entire top of onions.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix in larger bowl oats, brown sugar, peanut butter, powdered sugar and butter.
Not too wet and not too dry (then mix honey if you want).
Now take and roll into little balls.
After you are done, roll into powdered sugar.
Refrigerate and they are so good.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions.
Pour milk over hot cake. Spread ice cream topping over cake.
Spread Cool Whip on cake. Sprinkle candy bars over cake.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Cut chocolate in thin threads and put in 1 1/2 cups water. Boil on medium-high for four minutes.
Add sugar, Karo syrup and vanilla.
Stir and boil for four more minutes.
Add butter.
Whip to make thick.
Store in refrigerator.
Heat to serve.

title: applesauce jar cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, applesauce and 2/3 cup sugar.
Then sift together dry ingredients and add to applesauce mixture.
You may add 2/3 cup chopped nuts and raisins if you like.
Pour into well-greased wide mouth pint canning jars, filling only 1/2 full.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Remove jars one at a time.
Wipe sealing edge clean.
Put on lid (that's been in boiling water) and tightened with ring.
Screw tight.
As cake cools, jars will seal.
Store as you would regular canned goods. Make a nice gift to keep on hand anytime.

title: chocolate covered pretzels
directions: Melt chocolate with shortening in a small bowl over simmering water; remove from heat, but keep over water.
Drop pretzels, one at a time, into chocolate.
Lift pretzels out with a fork, lightly tapping fork against side of bowl to let excess chocolate drip into bowl.
Place pretzels on wire rack over wax paper.
Allow to dry before removing from rack.
Store in a cool place.

title: stir-fry vegetables
directions: Parboil chicken.
(May use just white meat.)
Cool and cut into chunks (quarter size).
Fry in 2 to 3 tablespoons oil until tender, stirring often, 5 to 10 minutes.
Add celery first and cook for awhile and add other ingredients.
I make my chicken broth with boiling water and chicken crystals, then add teriyaki sauce and thicken.
Add to vegetables and stir often.
Vegetables should be crunchy.
Fresh vegetables can be used instead of frozen and canned.
Makes enough to fill a 12 x 2 x 2-inch electric frypan.

title: bachelor's delight
directions: Crumble hamburger meat in skillet and fry.
Cube potatoes and add to hamburger.
Add enough water to cook potatoes.
When potatoes are almost tender, add pork and beans, chili powder and other seasonings to taste.
Cook until potatoes are done and juice has cooked down and slightly thickened.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked carrots and onions
directions: Slice carrots diagonally.
Cook 3/4 of the way in 1 cup water with bouillon cubes.
Slice onions thickly.
Cook in butter until translucent.
Add flour and stir quickly.
Add to carrots and place all in a buttered casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together. Add oil, buttermilk and eggs. Mix.
Let stand 2 hours in refrigerator before using.
Keeps in refrigerator 6 weeks or more.

title: vegetables romano
directions: Saut zucchini and onions in margarine for 10 minutes.	Add tomatoes.
Cook on low heat for 5 minutes.	Sprinkle with Romano cheese.
Serves 4.

title: beet salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add all other ingredients. Chill in refrigerator until set.

title: fresh cranberry sauce
directions: Boil; cook on low for 15 minutes.
Stir until thick for 1 1/2 hours.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream Crisco and add remaining ingredients; beat until smooth.

title: divinity
directions: Bring sugar and water to a soft-ball stage. Pour over the marshmallow cream in a large mixing bowl. Add nuts and vanilla. Mix well and pour in a buttered dish. Cool. Cut and enjoy.

title: big t's oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oatmeal, nuts, and raisings.
Shape dough into 2 1/2 inch diameter roll.
Place in freezer for 2 hours.
Cut dough into 1/4 inch slices, place on ungreased cookie sheets 2 inches apart.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven 12 to 15 minutes until lightly browned.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple (using all the juice), Cool Whip, marshmallows and pecans in large bowl.
Add (dry) pudding and blend thoroughly. Chill and serve.

title: beef stew(microwave oven)
directions: In 4-quart casserole, combine beef, 1 1/2 cups water, soup mix, carrots, potatoes and bay leaf.
Cover with lid.
Cook at High 7 to 8 minutes and at Medium-low 55 to 60 minutes, or until tender.
Stir occasionally.
Add peas and flour, blended with remaining 1/2 cup water.
Cook at High 5 to 7 minutes, or until stew is thickened; stir occasionally.

title: oil pastry
directions: Sift flour and salt.
Stir in oil and water.
Roll 1/2 dough at a time between 2 pieces of waxed paper; dampen bottom piece of paper slightly.
Peel off top paper, flip into pie plate.
Yield: Pastry for one 2-crust pie.

title: fruit pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and preserves with electric mixer on medium speed until smooth. Fold in whipped topping with electric mixer on low speed. Spread evenly over bottom of crust. May top with fresh fruit or whipped topping. Chill 30 minutes.

title: deluxe sour cream corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into greased, hot black iron frying pan.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spice tea
directions: Mix all together.
Store in a container.
Use 3 teaspoonfuls in a cup of hot water.

title: zucchini cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugars together.
Beat in egg.
Add zucchini.
Add dry ingredients.
Stir in raisins and chopped nuts. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and 2 cups marshmallows in heavy saucepan.
Heat over medium-low heat until melted.
Pour in lime jello; stir until dissolved.
Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Cut cheese up and put into hot mixture.
Heat until smooth.
Remove from heat and pour over pineapple and chopped nuts.
Chill until partly set and thick.
Fold in whipped cream; return to fridge and chill thoroughly.
Can be made a day ahead of time.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add to sifted flour gradually with other ingredients.
Place in greased bowl to rise 1 to 2 hours. Make into rolls.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Butter and sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: spicy hot chili
directions: Brown meat in Dutch oven.
Add garlic and onion while browning, stirring occasionally.
When brown, drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients to Dutch oven.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, one hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve hot.
Yield:
4 (1 1/2 cup) servings.

title: lazy chicken
directions: Mix rice, potato soup, and 1 cup milk. Put in a 9 x 13 pan, add broccoli. Put chicken on top of rice and broccoli. Mix 1 can of cream of chicken soup with 3/4 can of milk. Pour over chicken. Bake covered at 300° for 2 hours.

title: buttermilk braid
directions: In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in warm water and add a pinch of sugar.
Do not stir.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: pork chops 'n stuffing
directions: Brown chops on both sides.
Place in shallow baking dish. Lightly mix bread crumbs, onion, butter, 1/4 cup water and poultry seasoning.
Place a mound of stuffing on each chop.
Blend soup with the 1/3 cup water and pour over chops and stuffing.
Bake in a 350° oven, covered, for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes until tender, but not soft.
Peel and slice the long way.
Arrange in buttered baking dish and cover with maple syrup and dot with butter; add a little water and bake until potatoes are glazed.

title: italian zucchini casserole
directions: Saute zucchini with onion and margarine in skillet for 10 minutes.
Add pepper; mix well.
Mix eggs and cheese in bowl. Stir in zucchini mixture.
Line 10-inch pie plate or casserole dish with crescent roll dough, pressing edges to seal.
Spread with mustard.
Spoon zucchini mixture into crust.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 8 servings.

title: baked chicken with rice
directions: Cut up chicken.
Pepper to taste; no salt.
Spread rice evenly in bottom of well-greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of onion soup mix.
Place chicken on rice.
Sprinkle with remaining soup. Mix soup and water; blend well.
Pour over chicken; dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours or until chicken is done.
If it gets too dry, add more water.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: crabmeat a la poogan's(from poogan's porch, charleston, sc)
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a bowl and mix thoroughly. Cover and refrigerate until needed.

title: okra and tomatoes
directions: Let tomatoes get hot, then drop cut okra in.
Add oleo, onion, salt and pepper with a pinch of sugar.
Cook until done.

title: lime delight
directions: Combine gelatin, water, sugar and salt.
Let mixture stand until cool and begins to congeal.
Add gelatin mixture to whipped topping.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: zesty party mix
directions: Pour margarine over combine popped corn, cereal and peanuts; toss until well coated. Sprinkle with cheese; toss lightly. Place in 15 x 10 x 1 inch jelly roll pan. Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Mix marshmallows into sour cream.
Drain fruit and add into marshmallow mixture; blend well.
Fold in coconut and nuts. Refrigerate at least 4 hours.
A bowl or a mold serve just as well.
If a mold is used, loosen the mold by letting set in a pan of warm water.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: quick italian vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Stir in onion and cabbage and heat 2 minutes.
Add water; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in vegetables, tomatoes and seasonings.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: rodney's favorite no bake cookies
directions: Blend and boil sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk.
Take pan off of stove and blend in peanut butter.
After mixed well, add the oatmeal.
Mix and drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: alpine swiss chicken
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, milk and salt.
Add to other ingredients and cover with almonds.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, uncovered.

title: corn pudding
directions: Thaw corn.
Melt butter.
Beat eggs and add sugar, salt, flour and milk.
Pour into butter.
Add corn and pour into baking dish. Place baking dish in larger baking dish with water in it.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until firm and golden.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine butter, evaporated milk, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat, stirring occasionally. Bring to full boil. Cook 4 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in marshmallows, chocolate pieces, vanilla and nuts. Stir vigorously for 1 minute (until marshmallows melt and blend). Pour into 8-inch square buttered pan. Cool. Cut into squares. Makes 2 pounds.

title: mother's soup
directions: Thin condensed soups with the chicken broth.
Add paprika, heavy cream, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Let simmer for 2 more minutes.
Turn off heat and add 1 to 2 tablespoons sherry.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: percolator punch(witch's brew)
directions: Combine juices, water and brown sugar in bottom of electric percolator.
Put cloves, cinnamon and salt in perk basket.
Perk for several minutes or until punch is piping hot.

title: peaches and cream cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 10-inch pie pan.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Make white sauce.
When boiling, add the stock, then 1/4 cup cut-up lobster meat.
Simmer mixture 3 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain, if necessary.
To make grease pie plate and press 1 package of crescent rolls.
Put a layer of crushed taco or corn chips on crust.
Layer alternately with meat mixture, cheddar cheese, mozzarella cheese, sour cream and olives, if desired.
Top with small amount of crushed chips. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: christmas breakfast sausage
directions: Brown sausage; drain fat.
Add onions and cook a minute.
In dripper pan, place bread on bottom.
Put meat and onion on top of bread.
Cover with cheese.
Beat eggs in separate bowl, along with mustard, salt, pepper and milk.
Pour over cheese.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Just before baking, add milk to soup and pour over top.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour.

title: german slaw
directions: Alternate layers of cabbage and onion.
Sprinkle sugar over the top of mixture immediately.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Boil 1 minute.
Pour over cabbage mixture immediately.
Stir to blend. Cover and refrigerate for at least four hours before serving. Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: soft gingerbread
directions: Stir the molasses, sugar and shortening together; add the water, then the flour, salt, soda and spices sifted together, and beat hard.
Bake in two well-greased pans in a moderate oven about half an hour.

title: chocolate chip pecan pie
directions: Use prepared pie crust (Pillsbury all ready pie crust works great).
Heat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over bottom of pie crust.
Top with pecan halves.
Combine brown sugar, corn syrup, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Pour over pecans.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes or until top is deep golden brown. Cool.
Serve topped with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt; cut in shortening, making mixture crumbly. Add water 1 tablespoon at a time until desired texture.
Roll out on a floured board.
Bake at 425° until brown.
Makes one double or two single pie crusts.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Melt margarine and transfer to a 2-quart bowl.
Thoroughly combine other ingredients except chocolate.
Add to margarine. Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat peanut butter mixture evenly in pan.
Melt chocolate and spread over the peanut butter.
Cool in refrigerator and then cut into squares.

title: amanda's punch
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding ginger ale last.
Serve over ice. Great for parties and fellowship dinners.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl and beat for 2 minutes. Pour into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool in pan 5 minutes before turning out. Let layers cool completely before icing with Strawberry icing.

title: ratatouille
directions: Heat oil gently, add onions and cook until well softened. Add tomatoes. Cook until yielding juices, then add the eggplant, peppers and flavorings and cook gently on top of stove or in preheated
oven at 350° for 45 minutes. Add zucchini and cook 45 minutes more. Drain off juices and boil to reduce to syrupy liquid. Pour over vegetables, add the chopped basil or parsley and serve hot or cold.

title: rosie's spinach scoop
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate for a minimum of 2 hours. Cut lid out of a loaf of round egg, Sheepherder or pumpernickel bread.
Scoop out insides in bite-size pieces.
When hollow, fill with chilled mix.
Dip to eat with pieces of the bread basket.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Stir flour, salt and baking soda in one bowl.
With mixer, combine shortening, both sugars, eggs and vanilla in another bowl. Add flour mixture to shortening mixture, using a fork or spoon; do not use mixer.
Add chocolate morsels.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen cookies.

title: barbequed chicken
directions: Season	to
your
taste the chicken using garlic powder (not garlic
salt),
seasoning
salt,
black pepper and salt. Cook over coals
on grill, turning until meat is almost done. Then dip pieces into bowl containing barbecue sauce to which 1 heaping tablespoonful black pepper and 1 heaping tablespoonful salt
has been
added.
Replace
over coals and cook, turning once.
Take up and put into large frying pan and cover.
Heat until thoroughly hot.
Serves 6 to 9 hungry fellows.

title: cottage cheese filled tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes, cut slices from top and scoop out center. Sprinkle with salt inside to chill.
Combine remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fill tomato cups.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce.

title: queso fundido
directions: Cook sausage in a small skillet until no longer pink. Drain well on paper towels.
Combine cheeses, sour cream, and chili peppers in a large bowl; stir in cooked sausage.
Spread in a 1-quart baking dish.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20-25 minutes or till cheese is melted and bubbly, stirring once.
Top with chopped sweet pepper, tomato, and sliced ripe olives.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips.
Serves 8.

title: meat loaf barbecue style
directions: Combine crumbs, beef, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce; mix well.
Form into loaf.
Put in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan.
Combine remaining tomato sauce with remaining ingredients.
Pour over loaf.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand for a few minutes before serving.

title: grandmother pieper's orange sherbet
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Freeze in an ice cream freezer according to manufacturer's instructions.
Makes 2 quarts. Contains about 160 calories per 1/2 cup.
It's rich and creamy.

title: overnight morning rolls
directions: Place dinner rolls (unthawed) in an angel food or Bundt pan. Sprinkle with dry pudding mix.
Bring butter, brown sugar and cinnamon to a boil.
Cool.
Pour over rolls and sprinkle with nuts. Cover with aluminum foil.
Let rise overnight on counter.
Next morning, bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Invert on plate and remove pan after 5 minutes.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix the cream cheese, 1 tablespoon milk and sugar with wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.
Pour 1 cup milk in mixing bowl.
Add pudding; mix until well blended.
Stir in pumpkin and spices; spread over cream cheese layer.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and nuts, as desired.

title: cracker salad
directions: Dice all vegetables very finely.
Place 1 sleeve of Ritz crackers on the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Spread onion and bell pepper over layer of Ritz.
Top with mayonnaise.
Spread the other sleeve of Ritz over mayonnaise.
Top with tomatoes and cucumbers.
Pour bottle of salad dressing over vegetables.
Finish with final sleeve of Ritz crackers.
Chill and serve.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Season cereal crumbs with salt to taste.
Dip chicken pieces in Pet milk, then in crumbs.
Place, skin side up, on foil covered cookie sheet.
Cover with foil; pinch edges together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
If chicken is larger, may need longer time. Remove foil; cook 15 minutes.

title: cheese tacos
directions: Cook onion in 2 tablespoons of oil until tender but not brown. Stir in undrained tomatoes, chili peppers and oregano.
Simmer about 20 minutes until very thick.
In skillet, dip tortillas in 2 tablespoons of hot oil about 10 seconds or just until limp.
Drain on paper towel.
Cut cheese in about 12 strips.
Place 1 strip of cheese and 2 tablespoons of sauce down center of each tortilla; overlap edges.
Arrange on baking sheet seam side up.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 8 minutes.
Uncover; bake 3 to 4 minutes more.
Open tortillas and add sour cream.
Roll up. Serves 6.

title: oven stew
directions: Spread hamburger in bottom of casserole dish.
Place sliced potatoes and carrots on top.
Then mix in cans of tomato soup and 1/2 can water (or milk if preferred).
Use basil when browning hamburger and can add onion to taste.
