Add salt and pepper before placing in oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, depending on oven.
Add cheese last 15 minutes.
Dish is done when potatoes are tender.
Will take less time if potatoes are preboiled.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, then drain.
Add spices, onion, garlic, pepper, tomato paste and beans.
Simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Layer bottom of baking dish with chips, then mixture, more chips and beef mixture, etc.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot!!

title: josh and greg's hot july pepperoni pie
directions: In a 2-quart glass round baking dish, combine spaghetti, eggs and Parmesan cheese.
Press mixture against bottom of dish to form the "crust."
Microwave on High power 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, or until heated.
Add cottage cheese; spoon over top of spaghetti.
Arrange pepperoni slices over cottage cheese layer.
Spread sauce evenly over top.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cover; microwave on High power for 7 to 10 minutes, or until mixture is hot.
Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese over top.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: banana bars
directions: In large bowl of mixer, beat banana, margarine, sugar, cinnamon and vanilla at high speed until well blended.
Beat in egg.
Combine flour and baking powder.
Stir in flour mixture until well blended.
Spread evenly in well greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack and cut into 30 bars.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and Crisco until sugar dissolves.
Add beaten eggs.
Sift together the flour and baking powder.
Add flour and milk alternately to first mixture.
Add flavorings. Place in cold oven and turn on to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together all the ingredients, except crackers and margarine.
Crush the crackers and mix together with the melted margarine.
Top the vegetable mixture with the buttered crackers. Cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Cool.
Refrigerate covered. The spices can be left in the cider for 5 to 7 days.
Heat to serve.

title: apricot coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; set aside 1/2 cup for top.
Add eggs and milk to remaining crumb mixture.
Stir.

title: lovers' wedding cake
directions: Put flour of love, good looks and sweet temper into a well-furnished house.
Beat the butter of youth to a cream.
Mix together blindness of faults, self-forgetfulness, powdered with dry humor into sweet argument and add them to the above.
Pour in gently rippling laughter and common sense.
Work it all together until well mixed.
Then bake gentle forever.

title: black beans and rice
directions: Soak beans according to package directions; drain off water. Place beans in a large pot.
Add enough fresh water to cover beans by about 2 inches.
Add carrot, onions, chicken broth, salt substitute and cayenne pepper.
Bring to boil, then reduce heat and simmer covered until beans are done (at least 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Stir occasionally and check for adequate water level. Prepare rice according to package directions.
Serve beans on top of rice.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground chuck.
Mix with meat, taco sauce, rice and chilies. Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan crushed chips, meat and cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbling.

title: praline-topped sweet potatoes
directions: Bake sweet potatoes at 350° for about 1 hour.
Peel, slice and place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Place rhubarb in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with sugar.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat
eggs;
add
sugar,
corn meal, vinegar and melted margarine.	Pour
into
pie shell and bake at 350° until done, about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole(for crock-pot)
directions: Place layer of potatoes first, then vegetables, in crock-pot. Place meat on top.
Mix tomato soup and water together; pour over top of meat.
Cover; cook on low for 7 to 9 hours (high 3 to 4 hours).
Stir occasionally.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and turn into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Combine soup, milk and pepper. Stir in chicken, vegetables, and mushrooms. Pour into greased 2
quart baking dish. Combine cereal, margarine, and thyme. Sprinkle over top of mixture. Bake at 350 for 35 to 40 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: oatmeal jumbos
directions: Pour enough boiling water over raisins to cover; let stand 10 minutes.
Drain.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves into bowl.
Add shortening, sugar, egg and water.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in raisins and oatmeal.
Roll dough out on lightly floured board or canvas to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut with floured 3-inch round cutter.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Heat cider and cinnamon stick in large pan.
Bring to boil and simmer, covered, 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Keep hot over low heat or reheat in small batches.
Makes 20 cups.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Stir vinegar, sugar and other dry ingredients together.
Pour over cucumbers, peppers and onions.
Let stand in refrigerator 2 or 3 days before using.
Keeps in fridge indefinitely.

title: jean's spanish rice
directions: Brown rice in oil.
Add water, garlic, cominos and tomato sauce.
When it starts to boil, cover and reduce heat.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Do not uncover during cooking.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Chill all ingredients before combining.
Combine juices; add ginger ale last.

title: raisin cream pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, butter and salt until smooth.
Add milk and beaten egg yolks.
Cook until thick.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla, 1 teaspoon cream of tartar and 1 cup sugar.
Beat some more.
Put meringue on pies and brown in 375° oven.
Can divide recipe and make 1 pie.

title: chocolate cloud cake
directions: Sift together flour, cocoa, sugar, soda, salt and baking powder.
Stir until blended.
Add prunes, vanilla, eggs and milk. Stir just until blended.
Combine coffee and boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Stir into batter until blended.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients except pineapple, bananas and peanuts. Cook sauce until thickened.
Allow to cool, mix fruit and peanuts, pour dressing over fruit.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreo cookies in blender.
Set aside.
Combine and blend until thick the pudding mix, milk and vanilla.
Set aside. Combine margarine, whipped topping or Cool Whip, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Set aside.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease generously bottoms only of 2 loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Blend all ingredients on low speed one minute, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on medium speed one minute.
Pour into pans.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
(If using self-rising flour, omit salt, baking soda and baking powder.)

title: apricot mold
directions: Heat half can of nectar to mix with dry jello, then add rest of cool nectar when dissolved.
Pour half mixture into mold; place in refrigerator to firm.
Mix cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add oranges and mix with remainder of jello mix.
Put on top of firmed jello.
Refrigerate.
Cool Whip may be added to top just before serving.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in large bowl.
Mix in ginger and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Put in warm place until mixture bubbles (15 minutes).
Stir in remaining sugar, milk, salt and oil.
With mixer on low speed, beat in flour, 1 cup at a time, beating well after each cup.
Add last cup with heavy spoon.
Add flour until dough is heavy and stiff, but not too sticky to knead.
Kneading is not necessary.
Divide into 2 well-greased 1 pound coffee cans. Cover with well-greased plastic lids.
Let covered cans stand in warm place until dough rises and pops off lids (45 to 60 minutes). Put lids aside.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Crust will be very brown.
Brush top lightly with butter.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes on wire rack.
Loosen crust around edge with knife.
Remove from can and cool upright on rack.

title: strawberry pecan bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter and brown sugar, add 2 egg yolks then stir in flour.
Press into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 10 minutes.
Let stand few minutes then spread jam over crust.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add sugar and cinnamon. Fold in pecans and spread over crust and jam.
Bake 25 minutes more until topping is golden brown.
Cool slightly, then cut into bars.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, using an electric hand mixer, thoroughly mix all ingredients except the chocolate chips.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Pour cake batter into a well-greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Enjoy cake as is or frost after cooling with a favorite chocolate icing.
Yields 1 cake, 20 servings.

title: cauliflower-apple-raisin salad
directions: Plump raisins by soaking in hot water for 5 minutes.
Drain. Mix all ingredients and chill.
Makes 2 servings.
A sweet taste can be added with 1 package Sweet 'N Low.

title: mega tuna
directions: In a large bowl, place tuna, olives, broccoli florets, cheese, tomato, onion and almonds or sunflower seeds.
Toss lightly to mix ingredients.
In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise or salad dressing, milk, mustard, garlic powder, black pepper and hot pepper sauce.
Beat with a fork to blend.
Pour over broccoli-tuna mixture; gently fold until ingredients are lightly coated.
Chill well.
To serve, eat as a salad or use as a sandwich filler in pita breads or buns.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chinese noodles casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add tuna, soup, mushrooms and water; add noodles.
Put into a 12 x 6-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with potato chips and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. If you are using 9 x 13-inch pan, bake 40 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch pan. Put bread in bottom; sprinkle cooked, crumbled sausage over bread. Add cheese and mushrooms. Combine eggs, milk and seasonings. Pour over bread mixture. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: lemon icebox pie
directions: Mix lemonade and Eagle Brand milk together; fold in Cool Whip. Pour into crust.
Let chill 3 hours.
Store unused portions in icebox.

title: toffee cookie squares
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate bits and nuts, and put in large pan.
Mixture is crumbly.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Then melt chocolate bits and pour over top while cookies are still warm.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Do not cut until cold.

title: deer salami
directions: Mix together well.
Form a roll with a pound (half).
Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook beef, then add the rest.
Put in oven at 375° for 1 hour or until done.

title: christmas white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, sour cream, syrup, butter and salt in saucepan. Bring to

a boil slowly, stirring until sugar dissolves. Boil without stirring (cover saucepan) for 3 minutes over medium heat to 236° on candy thermometer or soft ball stage. Remove from heat. Let stand 15 minutes.
Do not stir.
Add vanilla. Beat until mixture starts to lose gloss or for about 8 minutes.
Stir in cherries and nuts.
Pour quickly into greased shallow pan (9 x 9-inch).
Cool and cut into squares.

title: pretzel-strawberry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let mixture cool.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix with all ingredients.
Place in pie crust and chill.

title: pecan cream cheese pie
directions: Beat the 1 cup sugar into cream cheese until mixture is smooth and creamy; add the chopped pecans.
Spread evenly in crumb crust. Bake in 325° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; spoon mixture of sour cream, sugar and vanilla evenly over top of pie.
Return to oven; increase temperature to 350° and bake 10 minutes longer. Garnish with pecan halves.
Chill before serving.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Mix all except noodles together with beater or blender.
Add noodles.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Use any size depending on how deep you want pudding (8 x 11-inch or 11 x 13-inch). Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° until done (approximately 1 hour).

title: williamsburg salad
directions: Soften gelatin
in 1/2 cup of cold water.
Add to boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add 1/2 cup of cold water, vinegar, salt, sugar and a few drops of green food coloring. Chill until mixture thickens.
Fold in other ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 8.

title: easy-filled cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy. Stir in milk and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture. Place 1 tablespoon of batter on ungreased cookie sheet. Place spoonful of any kind of pie filling on top of dough mixture and top with additional 1/2 tablespoon of dough. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Fill with any cookie or pie filling that you choose.

title: fiesta meat loaf
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in margarine until vegetables are tender.
Stir in chili sauce.
Combine 1/2 cup this mixture with ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit salad and mandarin oranges.
Drain pineapple juice (about 1 cup) and mix with instant vanilla pudding.
Set aside for dressing.
Mix all ingredients; add dressing and mix well. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Yields 6 servings.

title: holiday ham balls
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Place about 2 inches apart in pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Immediately remove from pan. Serve warm or cold.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: cheddar potato casserole
directions: Bring potatoes to room temperature.
If leftover, cold.
Beat egg yolks into potatoes until well mixed.
Stir in cheese, onion, pepper and seasonings.
Whip egg whites to soft peaks.
Fold into potatoes.
Spoon into well buttered casserole (1 1/2-quart). Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and let stand 2 hours. Combine the last 3 ingredients.
Heat this mixture.
Drain cukes. Pour sugar mixture over cukes.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator, then freeze.

title: 3-apple pie with rum sauce
directions: In medium saucepan over medium heat, boil the cider, uncovered, for 25 minutes or until reduced to 1 1/2 cups.
Remove 1/4 cup and reserve the rest for sauce.
Place apples in large saute pan and pour 1/4 cup of reduced cider and 2 tablespoons of rum over top.
Cook, covered, for 3 to 4 minutes.
Combine dry ingredients in small bowl.
Mix gently into apples with rubber spatula.

title: perfect rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine sugar, salt, yeast and 2 cups flour. In pan, heat margarine and water until very warm (120° to 130°). Beat liquid into dry mixture until blended.
Increase speed to medium.
Beat 2 minutes.
Beat in egg.
Continue beating 2 minutes more.
With spoon, stir in remaining 3 to 4 cups flour to make a soft dough.
Turn on floured surface.
Knead 10 minutes.
Shape into ball.
Let rest 10 minutes.
Shape and raise 1 hour.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 400° oven.

title: dot shook's chocolate fudge sauce
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa; add to margarine.
Heat to melt sugar. Add milk.
Cook to desired consistency.
May be reheated.
Great over pound cake or ice cream.

title: potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden.
Add water, milk, salt, and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in potatoes.
Serves 5.

title: crunchy squash casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except pecans.
Mix well and spoon into lightly greased casserole (1 1/2-quart). Sprinkle pecans over squash mixture. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: spinach-radish salad
directions: Combine spinach, watercress, radishes and onion in a large salad bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour dressing over salad; toss lightly.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 6 servings (46 calories per serving).

title: venison stew
directions: Heat oil in Dutch oven; brown meat.
Add onions, garlic, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaf, oregano, salt and pepper.
Simmer covered 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Add potatoes and carrots; cook until tender.
Mix flour and water; stir into stew. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Remove bay leaf.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Place chicken in bottom of a 9 x 11 casserole.
Mix together the soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Prepare 1 package Pepperidge Farm dressing by directions on package.
Put on top.
Bake at 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven or until bubbly and brown.

title: butter flake pie crust
directions: Sift flour, salt and sugar into bowl.
Cut in butter and shortening with a fork or pastry blender until mixture is consistency of corn meal.
Sprinkle water over mixture, a tablespoon at a time.
Mix lightly with a fork until pastry holds together and leaves sides of bowl clear.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Boil and drain macaroni.
Brown beef and onion together. Drain.
Layer all ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Place milk in large bowl.
Mix in shortening, molasses and salt.
Add yeast mixture.
Gradually mix in flour.
Let stand for 20 to 30 minutes, then knead for about 10 minutes or until smooth. Let rise until double in bulk in a greased bowl, covered with a damp cloth, about 1 1/2 hours at room temperature.
Knead lightly and form into loaves.
Makes 2 large or 3 small loaves.
Put in well-greased pan.
Let rise until almost double (about 1 hour). Bake at 375° for 40 minutes for small loaves, 50 minutes for larger loaves, or until done.
Can add raisins, if you like. Delicious.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake according to directions. Bake in a 13 x 9 pan. Cut cooled cake into small pieces. Place 1/2 cake pieces in bottom of deep bowl. Mix 1 package pudding with 2 cups milk. Pour over cake. Spread 1 container Cool Whip over pudding. Sprinkle 1/2 crushed candy over Cool Whip. Repeat the layers. Chill before serving. Serves 10 to 15.

title: pineapple sherbet
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water; dissolve over hot water. Combine buttermilk, 3/4 cup sugar, pineapple, vanilla and gelatin; mix well.
Turn into refrigerator tray.
Freeze until firm. Break in chunks; turn into chilled bowl.
Beat smooth with electric or rotary beater.
Beat egg white to soft peaks; gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating to stiff peaks.
Fold into pineapple mixture.
Return to cold tray.
Freeze firm.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: virgie's fig preserves cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add well beaten eggs.
Gradually add dry ingredients, sifted together.
Add preserves, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in loaf pan for 1 hour at 300°.
Frost with icing, if desired.

title: frozen cherry salad
directions: Drain fruit and reserve a few cherries and orange sections for garnish.
Let cream cheese stand at room temperature to soften or soften in microwave.
Beat until fluffy and blend in sour cream, sugar and salt.
Fold in fruits, marshmallows and pecans.
Pour into loaf pans and freeze.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix in casserole dish.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Sprinkle cheese on top.

title: ham-swiss rolls
directions: Mix butter, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion together to make filling.
Slice rolls in half; spread filling on each side.
Top with ham and cheese slices.
Close rolls, like sandwiches, and put back in tray and plastic bag purchased in.
Refrigerate until needed.
Remove plastic bag and heat in tray in oven or in toaster oven for approximately 10 minutes at 300°.

title: henry pencik's potato pancakes("bramborove placky")
directions: Peel potatoes.
Grate into mush.
Add eggs, salt, garlic, marjoram, parsley and about 1/4 cup milk.
Add flour to make batter thicker.
Mix well.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all together and chill before serving.

title: pineapple cottage cheese mold
directions: Drain pineapple.
To juice, add water to make 2 cups liquid. Boil.
Add jellos and salt.
Let cool until slightly thickened but not set.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Put in mold and chill.

title: granny southard's persimmon pudding
directions: Bake for 2 hours in moderate oven.

title: kristina's little hot dogs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease bottom of cookie sheet. Cut hot dogs into thirds.
Cut biscuits into halves.
Stretch out biscuit dough and wrap it around hot dog.
Place in greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 1/2 hour or until lite brown in color.

title: fresh blueberry pie filling
directions: Stir flour, sugar, vinegar and blueberries and place in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Blend sugar and cinnamon.
Grease 10-inch tube pan and dust with about 1 tablespoon of sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Also sprinkle over with 1 tablespoon chopped nuts.
Blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened.
Blend as directed on package.
Reserve 2 cups batter.
Pour remaining batter into pan.
Sprinkle with remaining sugar-cinnamon mixture and remaining nuts, then add the remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes, or until done.
Cool cake in pan, top side up, for 15 minutes, then invert on serving plate.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Beat well.
Bake in oven at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes in well greased pan.
You can use the recipe for any flavor you wish.
Use 1/2 pound melted country butter in place of oil; it will stay moist a long time and have a good flavor.

title: emerald isle shrimp salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Heat pineapple syrup to boiling and remove from heat.
Add gelatin to pineapple juice and stir until dissolved.
Add salt.

title: chili dog pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Combine baking mix, mustard and water in small mixing bowl.
Stir until dough forms.

With fingertips dipped in baking mix, press dough into bottom and up the sides of prepared dish; set aside. Quarter hot dogs by cutting in half lengthwise and again crosswise. Place hot dogs on dough.
Spoon chili over hot dogs.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 20 minutes or until heated through.

title: sesame asparagus
directions: Place asparagus in a skillet. Sprinkle with salt. Add 1/2-inch of water. Bring to boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until crisp-tender, about 4 minutes.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add other three ingredients and bring to boil (stirring constantly or it will stick).
To make a larger amount, you can double or triple recipe.

title: mandarin orange pie(icebox pie)
directions: Stir the Cool Whip, Eagle Brand, oranges and chopped pecans together.
Pour into graham cracker crusts and chill.
Better if it sits for 1 or 2 days.
Makes 2 pies.

title: raisin loaf
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add 1 cup flour and mix until spongy.
Let rise until light and frothy.
Add remaining ingredients and blend into spongy mixture.
This becomes a very firm loaf.
Spoon into greased loaf pan or bread tin and let rise until nearly doubled.
Bake at 375° at least 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese dip for fruit
directions: Beat all on high, adding enough milk to make dipping consistency. Chill.

title: supper on a bun
directions: Combine ingredients.
Cut French bread in half, lengthwise. Spread meat mixture on evenly over top of bread.
Wrap heavy-duty foil around side of loaf.
(Make boat.)
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cut and serve.

title: carole's cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together. Add eggs and vanilla. In a separate bowl, sift flour, soda, salt, baking powder and French vanilla pudding mix. Add to creamed mixture. Mix well. Add remaining ingredients. Drop by well rounded teaspoons full to cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for for 11 minutes. Yield: 90 cookies.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine drained hamburger and beans and cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Cool and pat with a paper towel.

title: quick cole slaw
directions: Chop and clean vegetables.
Mix all together.
Add noodles just before serving.

title: white bread
directions: Add yeast to one cup lukewarm water.
Let stand 10 minutes. Measure two cups of scalded milk and five cups of water into a large bowl.
Add salt, sugar and lard, then add yeast; stir.
Add flour a little at a time.
Stir.
When all flour has been added and mixed in.
Lay dough on floured board or table and knead into a medium dough.
Let dough raise until doubled in bulk.
Knead down and let rise again.
Put out on floured board.
Shape into loaves (1 1/2 pound dough).
Fork top for air holes.
Let rise.
Bake at 375° about 25 to 30 minutes.
Take out of pans.
Cover with wax paper and cover with towel until cool.
Makes 6 to 8 loaves.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Cook beef broth and water along with your tomato sauce, seasoning salt, black pepper and chopped onion. Then add your red potatoes; cook for 5 minutes. Then add cabbage and carrots for another 15 minutes or until potatoes and other vegetables are cooked.

title: fried mozzarella
directions: Cut cheeses into 4-inch squares 2-inches thick.
Roll in flour, dip into egg, roll in crumbs, again into egg, again into bread crumbs.
Fry in oil just long enough for bread crumbs to turn golden in color.
Serve immediately (with tomato sauce, if desired).
Serves 4.

title: eggnog
directions: Beat together egg and sugar.
Then beat in milk and flavoring of your choice.
Serve cold, sprinkled lightly with nutmeg.

title: corn souffle
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Pour into souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: *Chocolate lovers:
Add 3 to 4 tablespoons cocoa instead of vanilla.

title: pumpkin pecan pie (2)
directions: Combine eggs, pumpkin, sugar, syrup, milk, flour, vanilla, spice, and salt.

title: "westerner cake"
directions: Cream butter.
Add powdered sugar; beat until fluffy.
Add eggs; beat after each addition.
Sift flour; add to batter gradually.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool for 4 minutes and invert pan.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Melt down the marshmallows in the milk; cool.
Add whipped cream and the peaches.
Put into baked pie shell; chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Layer in a large bowl in the following order:
1/2 angel food crumbs, pie filling, 1/2 package of sliced strawberries, Jell-O mixture, remaining angel food crumbles, Cool Whip and remaining strawberries.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt.
Add softened margarine, blackberry jam and beat.
Then add one egg at a time.
Continue to beat until well mixed.
Add the vanilla and buttermilk with the soda.
Mix and pour into three greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350° until barely done and put on racks to cool.

title: whole wheat hot rolls
directions: If shortening is used, melt, then cool to lukewarm.
Beat eggs and mix with shortening, sugar and salt.
Add whole wheat flour; mix well.
Mix water and yeast; add to flour mixture and mix well. Add enough plain flour to make a dough like biscuit dough. Cover; let rise in refrigerator.
Make out into rolls.
Brush with butter; let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together butter or Crisco, oleo, cream cheese and sugar. Add remaining ingredients.
Put in cold oven and bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours (in a Bundt pan).

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie crust. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350°. Bake an additional 40 to 50 minutes.

title: squash puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add flour, enough to make batter stiff.
Drop in hot grease and cook until golden brown.

title: banana raisin bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
In food processor with chopping blade, combine the prunes and water.
Add 1/2 cup mashed banana, yogurt, egg whites and vanilla.
Process just until mixed.
Stir yogurt mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened.
Fold in raisins.
Use large spoon; divide batter into cups. If desired, cut 1/2 banana into 1/4-inch thick slices. Place 2 slices on top of each muffin and brush with lemon juice. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: 5-layer blueberry pie
directions: Mix softened cream cheese and sugar together, using electric mixer.
(This will be difficult at first, but keep mixing).
Spoon into pie shells.
Top with pie filling.
Sprinkle nuts onto pie filling.
Spread Cool Whip over nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pineapple yam peaks
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
Peel, mash fine and add remaining ingredients.
Cover each pineapple slice with a mound of potato one inch thick.
Top with marshmallow.
Brown in oven; temperature medium.
Ready to serve.

title: beef fajitas
directions: Mix all ingredients except steak and garlic.
Rub steak with garlic, then add to marinade mixture.
Let set, covered, for 1 hour.
Drain steak and grill with high heat.
Cook, turning meat every 30 seconds until medium rare.
Remove and set aside.
Grill onions and peppers with 1 tablespoon oil in large frying pan until slightly tender.
Slice steak into 1/2-inch strips across the grain.
Add to onions and peppers; cook for 5 minutes more adding 1/4 cup of marinade to decarmelize pan.
Serve with hot flour tortillas, cheese, lettuce, diced tomato, sour cream and salsa.

title: fiesta fajita or steak marinade
directions: Use equal portions of the ingredients to marinate the quantity of meat you are cooking.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours, turning steaks occasionally.
You can also marinate green peppers and onions before grilling.

title: koosa patties
directions: Lightly salt Koosa pulp and let water drain out (15 to 20 minutes).
Squeeze out remaining liquid.
Mix pulp and eggs together.
Add flour until you have the consistency of thick pancake batter.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Spoon mixture onto a hot buttered or oiled saute pan or griddle about the size of a small pancake.
Lightly brown on both sides.
Serve with fresh sliced tomatoes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grate zucchini.
Beat eggs; add sugar and oil, then add zucchini.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder and cinnamon; add to zucchini mixture and add vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Cook in two loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together and pour in sheet cake pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, peanut oil, water and eggs in mixer for 2 minutes.
Fold in pudding mix, nuts and chips.
Pour into greased and floured bundt pan and bake in 350 degree oven for 50 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water.
Drain.
Rinse in hot water. Drain again.
Place in large bowl.
Add all other ingredients and toss well.
Refrigerate overnight to allow vegetables to marinate.

title: hot dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Set aside.
In a large bowl, put shortening, sugar and salt.
Pour hot milk in and stir until shortening has melted. Add 1/2 cup ice water; stir well.
Add yeast mixture; mix well. Stir in flour.
Mix well. Dough will be soft.
Pour dough out on floured pastry sheet and knead lightly, about 1 minute.
Put dough in clean, well oiled bowl and set in a warm place until it doubles in bulk.
Knead 5 or 6 times and turn out on floured sheet.
Knead 5 or 6 times.
Shape into 15 rolls. Place in baking dish.
Rub top of rolls with cooking oil.
Set in a warm place until it doubles in bulk again. Bake at 350° until golden brown on top. Brush with butter when taken out of oven.

title: white icing
directions: Beat until stiff.
Frosts a 9 x 13-inch cake or you can frost a batch of tea cakes or other cookies.

title: pineapple supreme
directions: Blend ingredients together, mixing eggs, butter and sugar first.
Spoon into greased pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (uncovered). Serve
hot or cold.

title: chickpea soup
directions: Peel and crush garlic.
If using fresh tarragon, chop it finely.
Heat the oil and saute the garlic until it begins to brown.
Add the tarragon and tomatoes, roughly chopped, and lower the heat to simmer.
When ingredients come to a boil, cook for 25 minutes or so.
When the tomatoes are cooked, add the chickpeas and cook another 5 minutes.
Stir in the stock cube and no more than 1 1/4 cups water.
Season with salt and pepper to taste and serve.

title: cream of anything soup
directions: Make a roux of butter and flour; add milk and make a thick white sauce.
If cheese is used, add here and whisk to melt.
Mix in leftover cooked vegetables or meat; stir until smooth.
Add broth to desired consistency.
Season to taste.

title: mary's banana bread
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt together. Set aside.
Mash bananas and set aside.
Cream the sugar and shortening until well blended.
Add eggs and mix well. Add buttermilk and vanilla; mix well.
Add mashed bananas (about 1/2 at a time) and mix well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients (about 1/2 at a time) and mix well after each addition.
Add chopped nuts and stir in with spatula or spoon.
Spray loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray and pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour. (Toothpick inserted in center should come out clean.) Cool. Can freeze or refrigerate.

title: super bowl sunday dinner
directions: Thaw bread and let rise to double.
Brown the beef, onions and celery and let cool.
Roll out the bread dough to about 12 x 18-inches each.
Spread the cooled (not cold) meat, peppers and mushrooms on the dough, mostly in the middle.
Top with the Mozzarella.
Roll up, making sure the rolls are sealed.
Let rise again for about 1/2 hour and bake at 375°, until well browned (about 40 minutes).
Slice in very thick slices and use the heated sauce as a dip.

title: green beans mayonnaise
directions: This is done in two operations.
First, you fry the bacon and crumble into green beans; simmer for approximately 30 minutes.
Mix into the mayonnaise, the chopped hard-boiled egg, Worcestershire sauce, horseradish, salt, pepper, garlic powder and lemon juice. Set aside.
After beans have finished cooking, drain and spoon mixture over them.
Ah, 'tis fit for a king.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: yogurt dip
directions: Blend until smooth.
Then add 1 package of Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Put butter and onion in skillet and brown.
Stir in meat, salt and pepper; let cook about 5 minutes or until beef changes color. Add mushroom and vegetable soups.
Remove mixture from heat and add sour cream, mixing well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Mix biscuit dough following directions as you would for biscuits. Drop dough on top of meat mixture.
Sprinkle with poppy seed and bake until biscuits are done.

title: old-fashioned whoopie pies
directions: In a small bowl, combine cocoa and water; mix well.
Cool for 5 minutes.
In a mixing bowl, cream shortening and sugar.
Add cocoa mixture, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk; mix well.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls 2 inches apart onto greased baking sheets.
Flatten slightly with a spoon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until firm to the touch.
Remove to wire racks to cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: crab meat salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except lettuce; mix well.
Cover and chill 1 to 2 hours.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: corn puddin
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease Pyrex dish.
Mix all ingredients and bake until firm and golden brown or toothpick inserted comes out clean, about 30 minutes.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pastry lined pie pan.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in remaining ingredients. Pour cream mixture into pie pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer or until knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serve in wedges.

title: giant peanut butter oat cookie
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt in a medium bowl.
Mix in oats.
In another bowl, beat margarine and peanut butter on medium speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Beat in sugars until blended.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add oat mixture and stir by hand until well combined.
Shape mixture into 2-inch balls.
Place 6 balls on an ungreased cookie sheet and flatten each to 3 inches in diameter.
Bake at 350° for 9 1/2 minutes or until golden.
Cool completely on wire rack.
Makes about 24 big cookies.

title: microwave crunchy chocolate sauce
directions: In a 1-quart glass measure, measure milk.
Drop in chocolate. Microwave at High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Blend well.
Add sugar; stir to blend.
Microwave 1 to 2 minutes until mixture boils.
Add peanut butter and vanilla and stir until blended; serve warm or cool.

title: meringue shells a la heloise
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff and dry; slowly add sugar, then vanilla and vinegar.
Beat again until stiff and dry.
Place meringues on the back of an ungreased cookie sheet, keeping in mind they will double in size.
Make a well in the center of each and bake on the middle shelf of a 250° oven for 1 hour or more until they turn pinkish beige in color.
Test bottom of well with finger; it must not be too sticky.
Bake longer, if necessary. Using a spatula, remove from sheet the minute they come out of the oven.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Cook sugar, butter, and cream over medium heat until it boils, then cook for 5 minutes.
Take off heat and add marshmallows, chocolate chips, and vanilla.
Pour into plate, and let set until firm.

title: baked crab cakes
directions: Remove shells from crab but don't break lumps.
Combine crackers, parsley, Worcestershire, Tabasco, egg, 3/4 cup mayonnaise, Old Bay, salt and pepper and mix well.
Gently fold in crab; don't overmix!
Form into 6 cakes; place on foil covered cookie sheet and spoon reserved mayonnaise on each.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until golden brown.
Garnish with parsley and lemon.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix together pudding and milk.
Add both cartons of whipped topping.
Stir together very well.
Layer bottom of pan with graham crackers.
Spread 1/2 pudding mixture over crackers.
Add another layer of crackers.
Place rest of pudding mixture over this.
Put last layer of crackers over pudding and place icing over this.

title: charismatic carrots
directions: Saute parsley and onion in margarine for 5 minutes.
Add carrots, beef consomme and nutmeg.
Cook 15 minutes uncovered, then 15 minutes covered.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Combine sausage and cheese.
Add Bisquick and mix well.
Add small amount of water to moisten (1 to 2 teaspoons).
Roll into cocktail meatball size.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
May be frozen and reheated.
Enjoy!

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Blend together all ingredients, except raisins and nuts.
Then fold in raisins and nuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° until done.

title: easy beer stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange beef cubes and onions in a large Dutch oven.
Add pepper, soup, beer and gravy browner.
Mix gently and cover tightly.
Bake 2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Add potatoes, carrots and garlic powder.
Cover and return to oven for 1 hour or until vegetables are cooked.
On top of stove add peas and cook until done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sugar drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream softened butter and sugar together; add egg and beat until fluffy. Alternately mix flour and milk into egg mixture.
Add vanilla. Drop by teaspoon onto a cookie sheet.
For a sugary top, lightly flatten each cookie with the bottom of a glass which has been buttered and then dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° (moderate oven) for 18 to 20 minutes.
Remove from cookie sheet while still warm. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: baked mustard steak
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix salt and flour.
Pound 1/4 cup of this mix into the cube steaks.
Melt 4 tablespoons of butter.
Add cube steaks and brown well.
Place steaks in a large baking dish. Melt 2 tablespoons butter.
Add onions and cook until tender. Melt 2 tablespoons butter; saute mushrooms.
Spoon onions and mushrooms over browned steak.
Add remaining flour to butter and drippings remaining in the skillet.
Stir in bouillon and mustard and cook, stirring constantly until thick (make sure to get out all the lumps).
Add cream and mix well.
Pour sauce over the vegetables and meat.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours (test after 1 hour to see if it is done).

title: fruit dessert
directions: Combine fruit in large bowl.
In small bowl, combine dry pudding mix, milk and orange concentrate.
Beat well 1 to 2 minutes.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold in fruit mix.
Put in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve on lettuce or in cups.

title: mama's "icebox" rolls
directions: Add lard to hot mashed potatoes and hot potato water.
Let lard melt; add sugar and cold water.
When lukewarm, add yeast, then let stand 2 hours.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and egg whites and flour to make a stiff dough.
Let stand in a draft free room until mixture starts to rise. then put in "icebox" (refrigerator).
Form into round rolls and rise again until double (about 1 hour).
Place about 2 1/2 inches apart on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 400°, approximately 15 to 20 minutes, or until nicely brown.

title: fresh spring peach salad
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients in mixer bowl; blend slowly. Add peaches and pineapple.
Chill.

title: apple raisin loaves
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans (9 x 5 x 3-inch) or 3 smaller loaf pans.
In a large bowl, beat eggs, oil, apples, sugar, and vanilla on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally, 1 minute.
Add flour, baking soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, and cloves.
Beat on low speed, scraping bowl occasionally until moistened, about 1 minute.
Then beat on medium speed 1 1/2 to 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts and raisins.
Spread in pans.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. (Allow 55 to 60 minutes for larger loaves and approximately 45 minutes for smaller loaves.)
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans. Cool on wire rack.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, salt and peanuts in a 2-quart casserole dish and stir well.
Microwave on High 8 to 9 minutes; mix well.
Add butter and vanilla.
Blend thoroughly.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes.
Stir in soda and mix well.
Pour onto a greased cookie sheet.
Cool 1 hour.
Break into small pieces.

title: baked sole
directions: Place fish in greased baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup milk.
Bake in
a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Melt butter and flour. Blend gradually.
Add 1
cup milk.
Cook over low heat until smooth and thick, stirring constantly. Add sherry flavoring and cheese.
Pour over fish and broil until golden. Serves 4 to 6.

title: texas beef fajitas
directions: Combine lime juice, garlic and Worcestershire sauce. Marinate steak in this mixture at least 3 hours or overnight. Drain meat well and grill over charcoal until barely medium-rare.

title: jimmy carter cake
directions: Mix and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread cream cheese on bottom of baking dish.
Spread chili over cream cheese and sprinkle cheese over top.

title: jelly roll that rolls
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together until light.
Stir in flour, salt and baking powder; mix well.
Add boiling water, then extract. Pour into well oiled jelly roll pan and bake in a 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Turn out on cloth wrung from hot water.
Trim edges and spread with jelly.
Roll immediately.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: double-crispy chicken
directions: Measure crushed corn flakes into shallow dish or pan.
Set aside.

title: spaghetti squash dinner
directions: Slice squash the long way, scoop out seeds.
Bake face down in a buttered, aluminum lined tray at 375° for about 30 minutes (15 to 20 minutes at full power in microwave).
Let it cool, then scoop out the long strands inside.
While the squash is baking, saute onions with salt, garlic, pepper, sliced mushrooms and herbs.
When onions are soft, add tomatoes.
Cook until most liquid evaporates. Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for another 40 minutes.

title: baked nachos
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Layer glass baking dish with tortilla chips.
Mix beef, cheddar cheese soup and green chilies together and spread over torilla chips.
Spread sour cream over mixture. Sprinkle cheddar cheese over sour cream and top with tomatoes and black olives.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: honey oatmeal chewies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter flavor Crisco, granulated sugar, brown sugar, honey, egg, milk and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, coconut, raisins and walnuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes for soft cookies.

title: don and melba clary's pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Pinch half of the cake into a pan.
Crush the candy bars in their wrappers.
Mix the butter, egg yolks and sugar until creamy. Add the Cool Whip.
Spoon this mixture on top of the cake. Sprinkle 3 of the candy bars on top of this.
Repeat.
Serves 10 to 12.
Chill and store in refrigerator.

title: rex's sweet potato pie
directions: Bake potatoes until they stick tender with a fork.
Peel and mash with masher.
Add all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shells and bake at 350°.
This mixture will make two pies.
